ollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-features/terminator-zero-mattson-tomlin-batman-1235987299/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240831021820/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-features/terminator-zero-mattson-tomlin-batman-1235987299/ |archive-date=August 31, 2024 |access-date=September 2, 2024 |magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |publisher=[[MRC (company)#PMRC|PMRC]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last=Romano |first=Nick |title=''Terminator Zero'' exclusive first look takes the sci-fi saga to Tokyo |url=https://ew.com/terminator-zero-anime-first-look-mattson-tomlin-exclusive-8645307 |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |publisher=[[Dotdash Meredith]] |language=en |date=May 15, 2024 |access-date=May 16, 2024 |archive-date=May 31, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240531010022/https://ew.com/terminator-zero-anime-first-look-mattson-tomlin-exclusive-8645307 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://collider.com/predator-killer-of-killers-viking-animated-movie-explained-dan-trachtenberg/|work=Collider|title="Hard R Rating, Crazy Carnage": Dan Trachtenberg Unveils the Predator Franchise's New Animated Movie 'Killer of Killers'|author=Loftus, Meredith|date=April 8, 2025|accessdate=April 14, 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Robinson |first=Tasha |date=June 4, 2025 |title=Predator: Killer of Killers took inspiration from Arcane, Akira, and, er… Best in Show? |url=https://www.polygon.com/movies/603376/predator-killer-of-killers-inspiration-arcane-akira |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250710021229/https://www.polygon.com/movies/603376/predator-killer-of-killers-inspiration-arcane-akira |archive-date=July 10, 2025 |access-date=July 22, 2025 |website=Polygon |publisher=Vox Media}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Mathai | first=Jeremy | title=Predator: Killer Of Killers Director Explains Why The Yautja Look So Different In The New Movie [Exclusive] | website=SlashFilm | date=June 9, 2025 | url=https://www.slashfilm.com/1881600/why-yautja-look-different-predator-killer-of-killers-explained/ | access-date=June 11, 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Carter |first=Justin |date=2025-07-26 |title='Predator: Killer of Killers' Gets an Extended Ending Tonight |url=https://gizmodo.com/predator-killer-of-killers-gets-a-new-ending-tonight-2000634855 |access-date=2025-07-26 |website=Gizmodo |language=en-US}}</ref>

[[Universal Home Video]] and Japanese animation studio [[Gonzo (company)|Gonzo]] even personally tried to replicate the same animation process that was used from ''The Animatrix'', which led to the creation of ''[[Gankutsuou: The Count of Monte Cristo]]'' and ''[[The Chronicles of Riddick: Dark Fury]]''. The two projects were notably produced through collaborations with [[Mahiro Maeda]] and [[Peter Chung]], both of whom had worked in ''The Animatrix''.<ref name="GuideInfo">{{Cite book|date=April 22, 2005|script-title=ja:巌窟王コンプリート|trans-title=Gankutsuou Complete|language=ja|publisher=[[Media Factory]]|isbn=4-8401-1240-1}}</ref><ref name="GankutInfo">{{cite web|url=http://www.gankutsuou.com/world/introduction.html|script-title=ja:巌窟王 - World - Introduction|language=ja|publisher=Gankutsuou Website|access-date=January 27, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080204080534/http://www.gankutsuou.com/world/introduction.html|archive-date=February 4, 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="GankutStaff">{{cite web|url=http://www.gonzo.co.jp/works/gankutsuou/|script-title=ja:Works – 巌窟王|language=ja|publisher=[[Gonzo (company)|Gonzo]]|access-date=January 27, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171011100426/http://www.gonzo.co.jp/works/gankutsuou/|archive-date=October 11, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="GankutInterview1">{{cite web|url=http://www.gankutsuou.com/staff/interview/01_01.html|script-title=ja:巌窟王 – スペシャル対談＜キャラクター編＞ – 前田真宏 X 松原秀典|language=ja|publisher=Gankutsuou Website|access-date=January 27, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091123015416/http://www.gankutsuou.com/staff/interview/01_01.html|archive-date=November 23, 2009|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="GankutInterview2">{{cite web|url=http://www.gankutsuou.com/staff/interview/02_01.html|script-title=ja:巌窟王 – スペシャル対談＜キャラクター編＞ – 前田真宏 X 山下友弘, 神山修一, 高橋ナツコ|language=ja|publisher=Gankutsuou Website|access-date=January 27, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091028071210/http://www.gankutsuou.com/staff/interview/02_01.html|archive-date=October 28, 2009|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Cotter|first1=Padraig|title=Vin Diesel's Chronicles Of Riddick Anime Showed Pitch Black's Aftermath |url=https://screenrant.com/chronicles-riddick-dark-fury-anime-prequel-forgotten/
|website=[[Screen Rant]] |date=September 7, 2021 |access-date=September 7, 2021}}</ref>

Japanese anime has majorly influenced [[Walt Disney Animation Studios|Disney]], [[Pixar]] and [[DreamWorks Animation|DreamWorks]] productions. [[Glen Keane]], the animator for successful Disney films such as ''[[The Black Cauldron (film)|The Black Cauldron]]'' (1985), ''[[The Little Mermaid (1989 film)|The Little Mermaid]]'' (1989), ''[[Beauty and the Beast (1991 film)|Beauty and the Beast]]'' (1991), ''[[Aladdin (1992 Disney film)|Aladdin]]'' (1992), and ''[[Tangled]]'', has credited [[Hayao Miyazaki]] as a "huge influence" on Disney's animated films ever since ''[[The Rescuers Down Under]]'' (1990).<ref>Michael J. Lee (October 24, 2010), [http://movies.radiofree.com/interviews/tangled_glen_keane.shtml An Exclusive Interview With Glen Keane], RadioFree.com</ref> [[Gary Trousdale]] and [[Kirk Wise]], the directors of Disney films such as ''Beauty and the Beast'', ''[[Hunchback of Notre Dame (1996 film)|Hunchback of Notre Dame]]'' (1996), and ''[[Atlantis: The Lost Empire]]'' (2001), are fans of anime and have cited Miyazaki's works as a major influence on their own work.<ref name="Probe">{{cite news|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/feature/2001-05-15|title=Probing the ''Atlantis'' Mystery|first=Lee|last=Zion|date=May 15, 2001|work=[[Anime News Network]]|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20110629004303/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/feature/2001-05-15|archive-date=June 29, 2011|url-status=live|access-date=July 15, 2012}}</ref> Miyazaki's influence on Disney dates back to ''[[The Great Mouse Detective]]'' (1986), which was influenced by Miyazaki's ''[[Lupin III]]'' film ''[[Castle of Cagliostro]]'' (1979) and which in turn paved the way for the [[Disney Renaissance]].<ref name="mouseplanet2">{{cite web|last=Korkis|first=Jim|title=How Basil Saved Disney Feature Animation: Part Two|url=https://www.mouseplanet.com/9549/How_Basil_Saved_Disney_Feature_Animation_Part_Two|website=Mouse Planet|date=March 2, 2011|access-date=June 22, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Motamayor |first1=Rafael |title=Revisiting 'The Great Mouse Detective', the Unsung Kickstarter of the Disney Renaissance (And One of Disney's Creepiest Movies) |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/the-great-mouse-detective-revisited-2/ |access-date=2020-04-05 |work=[[/Film]] |date=2020-04-02}}</ref> It was especially inspired by the adventures of the 1994 Disney movie ''[[The Lion King]] [[Doraemon]].'' In particular, [[Roger Allers]] had stated in an interview that he went to Japan before 1988, the year the production of ''The Lion King'' started, and that he was very impressed by the adventures in Doraemon, and that ''The Lion King'' was greatly influenced by ''Doraemon''. [[Fujiko Fujio]], despite the controversy, later thanked Disney in 1995 for being impressed by Disney's ''The Lion King'' and praising ''Doraemon''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/title/tt29402528/?ref_=bo_rl_ti |title=''Doraemon: Nobita's Earth Symphony'' |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=[[IMDb]] |access-date=March 9, 2024}}</ref>

Controversy surrounded another Disney film, ''Atlantis: The Lost Empire'', which was alleged to have plagiarized the [[Studio Gainax]] anime series ''[[Nadia: The Secret of Blue Water]]'' (1990).<ref name="Probe" /><ref name=Notenki>{{cite news|url=https://www.gwern.net/docs/eva/2002-takeda-notenkimemoirs|title=The Notenki Memoirs: Studio Gainax And The Men Who Created ''Evangelion''|first=Takeda|last=Yasuhiro|date=March 25, 2019|work=Gwern|access-date=October 29, 2019}}</ref> ''Atlantis'' directors [[Gary Trousdale]] and [[Kirk Wise]] denied the allegation, but nevertheless acknowledged Miyazaki's films as a major influence on their work.<ref name=Probe />

Miyazaki's work deeply influenced Pixar co-founder [[John Lasseter]], who described how Miyazaki's influence upon his life and work began when he first saw ''Castle of Cagliostro''.<ref name="Brzeski">{{cite news|last1=Brzeski|first1=Patrick|title=John Lasseter Pays Emotional Tribute to Hayao Miyazaki at Tokyo Film Festival|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/john-lasseter-pays-emotional-tribute-743635|access-date=2014-11-10 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=2014-10-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170509210432/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/john-lasseter-pays-emotional-tribute-743635|archive-date=2017-05-09 |url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[Pete Docter]], director of the popular Pixar films ''[[Monsters, Inc.]]'' (2001) and ''[[Up (2009 film)|Up]]'' (2009) as well as a co-creator of other Pixar works, has also described anime, specifically Miyazaki, as an influence on his work.<ref name="pbs">[http://www.kpbs.org/news/2009/may/29/interview-director-peter-docter/ Interview with Up Director Peter Docter]. By [[Beth Accomando]]. [[KPBS (TV)|KPBS]]. Published May 29, 2009.</ref> [[Jennifer Lee (filmmaker)|Jennifer Lee]] and [[Chris Buck]] cited the influence of Miyazaki's anime productions on ''[[Frozen (2013 film)|Frozen]]'' (2013), stating that they were inspired by their sense of "epic adventure and that big scope and scale and then the intimacy of funny quirky characters."<ref>{{cite news |title=Frozen creators: It's Disney – but a little different |url=https://metro.co.uk/2013/12/08/frozen-creators-its-disney-but-a-little-different-4221547/ |access-date=2019-06-14 |work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |date=2013-12-08}}</ref> [[Chris Sanders (director)|Chris Sanders]] and [[Dean DeBlois]] described Miyazaki's flight and pacifist themes as an influence for creating ''[[How to Train Your Dragon (2010 film)|How to Train Your Dragon]]'' (2010). [[Joel Crawford (director)|Joel Crawford]], the director of ''[[Puss in Boots: The Last Wish]]'' (2022), cited ''[[Akira (1988 film)|Akira]]'' (1988) as an influence on the design of the characters and action within the film. Additionally, the film utilized 2D animation to "highlight the personal touch of hand-drawn animation that is found in traditional anime", as noted by ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'''s Jazz Tangsay.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tangcay |first1=Jazz |title=How 'Puss in Boots: The Last Wish' Found Inspiration in Anime Classic 'Akira' |url=https://variety.com/2022/artisans/news/puss-in-boots-last-wish-joel-crawford-anime-akira-1235463407/ |website=Variety |date=2022-12-16 |access-date=2023-02-14}}</ref>

The [[DC Animated Movie Universe]] and [[Marvel Animated Features]] franchises of [[direct-to-video]] animations possesses plentiful anime-style or anime-based films, in no small part due to many of the films actually having their animation outsourced and produced by Japanese studios, such as [[Madhouse, Inc.]], [[TMS Entertainment]], and [[Studio 4°C]]; notable examples of this distinction include ''[[Marvel Animated Features#Hulk vs.|Hulk vs.]],'' ''[[Marvel Animated Features#Planet Hulk|Planet Hulk]],'' ''[[Marvel Animated Features#Thor: Tales of Asgard|Thor: Tales of Asgard]],'' ''[[Marvel Animated Features#Next Avengers: Heroes of Tomorrow|Next Avengers: Heroes of Tomorrow]]'', ''[[Justice League: The Flashpoint Paradox]]'', ''[[Justice League Doom]]'', ''[[Green Lantern: First Flight]]'', ''[[Green Lantern: Emerald Knights]]'', ''[[Superman vs. The Elite]]'', ''[[Superman: Unbound]]'', ''[[Catwoman: Hunted]]'', and many installments of the [[DC Universe Animated Original Movies]].<ref>{{cite web|date=February 23, 2010|title=When It's Time To Collect, It's Only Heroes Who Pay|url=http://www.pajiba.com/film_reviews/justice-league-crisis-on-two-earths-review.php|access-date=July 23, 2017|website=pajiba.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Thill|first=Scott|title=Justice League: Doom Dissects Batman's Paranoia|url=https://www.wired.com/2012/02/justice-league-doom/|access-date=July 23, 2017|website=wired.com}}</ref><ref name="Catwoman: Hunted">{{cite web|date=2021-08-17|title='Catwoman: Hunted' Sets Voice Cast (Exclusive)|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/catwoman-hunted-voice-cast-dc-1234998303/|work=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2021-08-17|archive-date=2021-08-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210817161115/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/catwoman-hunted-voice-cast-dc-1234998303/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>[https://m.the-numbers.com/movies/franchise/DC-Animated-Movie-Universe "Box Office History for DC Animated Movie Universe Movies."] The Numbers. Retrieved September 9, 2023.</ref><ref>{{Cite web |author1=Adam Holmes |date=2024-01-18 |title=Crisis On Infinite Earths Is Ending DC's Tomorrowverse, And The Producer Revealed This Has Been 'Reluctantly' Planned Since The Beginning |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/interviews/crisis-on-infinite-earths-ending-dc-tomorrowverse-butch-lukic-planned-beginning |access-date=2024-01-19 |website=CINEMABLEND |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Stone |first=Sam |date=May 12, 2020 |title=Justice League Dark Writer Eulogizes the DC Animated Universe |url=https://www.cbr.com/justice-league-dark-writer-eulogizes-dc-animated-universe/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200522144048/https://www.cbr.com/justice-league-dark-writer-eulogizes-dc-animated-universe/ |archive-date=May 22, 2020 |access-date=May 13, 2020 |website=Comic Book Resources}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Giardina |first=Carolyn |date=February 17, 2019 |title='Bohemian Rhapsody' Wins Pair of Trophies at Sound Editors' Golden Reel Awards |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/mpse-golden-reel-award-nominations-2019-complete-list-winners-1181255/feature-animation-7/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220629205156/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/mpse-golden-reel-award-nominations-2019-complete-list-winners-1181255/feature-animation-7/ |archive-date=June 29, 2022 |access-date=June 29, 2022 |website=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=DeMott|first=Rick|title=Ratatouille Cooks Up Most Annie Nominations|url=http://www.awn.com/news/awards/ratatouille-cooks-most-annie-nominations|access-date=March 29, 2011|newspaper=AWN News|date=December 3, 2007|archive-date=November 5, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111105234554/http://www.awn.com/news/awards/ratatouille-cooks-most-annie-nominations|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=MARVEL ANIMATION: THE FUTURE|url=http://www.comicscontinuum.com/stories/0701/23/marvelanimation.htm|work=Comics Continuum|access-date=May 18, 2011|archive-date=September 29, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110929115102/http://www.comicscontinuum.com/stories/0701/23/marvelanimation.htm|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=mfa>{{cite web|last=Harvey|first=James|title=Direct-To-Video "Marvel Animated Features" Line Plans For Future Releases|url=http://marvel.toonzone.net/news.php?action=fullnews&id=65|work=Marvel Animation Age|publisher=toonzone.net|access-date=April 1, 2011|archive-date=December 2, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202222510/http://marvel.toonzone.net/news.php?action=fullnews&id=65|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=ap>{{cite news|last=Arnold|first=Thomas K.|title=Lionsgate sets 'Invincible Iron Man'|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/lionsgate-sets-invincible-iron-man-141920|access-date=March 14, 2014|newspaper=The Hollywood Reporter|date=November 3, 2006|agency=AP|archive-date=February 6, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150206042617/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/lionsgate-sets-invincible-iron-man-141920|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="AWN">{{cite web|url=http://news.awn.com/index.php?ltype=top&newsitem_no=23001 |title=Marvel Promotes Eric Rollman To President, Marvel Animation |access-date=May 6, 2008 |work=AWN Headline News |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090125185240/http://news.awn.com/index.php?ltype=top&newsitem_no=23001 |archive-date=January 25, 2009}}</ref><ref name=shh>{{cite news|title=Marvel Entertainment's Upcoming Slate|url=http://www.superherohype.com/features/94603-marvel-entertainments-upcoming-slate|access-date=March 14, 2014|newspaper=Superhero Hype|date=August 7, 2007|archive-date=July 15, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715003414/http://www.superherohype.com/features/94603-marvel-entertainments-upcoming-slate|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="ign0">{{cite news |last=McCutcheon |first=David |date=November 7, 2008 |title=Hulk Versus DVD |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2008/11/07/hulk-versus-dvd |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141215024631/http://www.ign.com/articles/2008/11/07/hulk-versus-dvd |archive-date=December 15, 2014 |access-date=November 8, 2013 |newspaper=IGN |publisher=IGN Entertainment}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title =Exclusive: Marvel's Upcoming Animation Slate | first =Scott | last =Collura | url =http://www.ign.com/articles/2007/01/18/exclusive-marvels-upcoming-animation-slate | newspaper =ign.com | publisher =IGN Entertainment | date =January 18, 2007 | access-date =August 9, 2013 | archive-date =March 13, 2022 | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20220313085536/https://www.ign.com/articles/2007/01/18/exclusive-marvels-upcoming-animation-slate | url-status =live}}</ref><ref name=awn0>{{cite news|last=Moody|first=Annemarie|title=Lionsgate Brings Speed Racer, Marvel To NATPE|url=http://www.awn.com/news/lionsgate-brings-speed-racer-marvel-natpe|access-date=March 14, 2014|newspaper=Animation World Network|date=December 15, 2008|archive-date=November 26, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126065440/https://www.awn.com/news/lionsgate-brings-speed-racer-marvel-natpe|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="amg">{{cite web |title=Next Avengers: Heroes of Tomorrow |url=http://www.allmovie.com/movie/next-avengers-heroes-of-tomorrow-v455413 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220313130324/https://www.allmovie.com/movie/next-avengers-heroes-of-tomorrow-v455413 |archive-date=March 13, 2022 |access-date=September 10, 2016 |website=All Movie |publisher=All Media Guide}}</ref><ref name=nar>{{cite news |last=Fritz |first=Steve |date=January 27, 2009 |title=Animated Shorts – 'Hulk Vs.' Director Frank Paur, More |url=http://www.newsarama.com/2045-animated-shorts-hulk-vs-director-frank-paur-more.html |newspaper=newsarama.com |publisher=TechMediaNetwork |access-date=November 8, 2013 |archive-date=March 17, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140317110430/http://www.newsarama.com/2045-animated-shorts-hulk-vs-director-frank-paur-more.html |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>Fletcher, Brenden. (July 8, 2008) [http://www.fpsmagazine.com/blog/2008/07/lionsgate-hulk-vs-wolverine-and-thor.php Lionsgate: Hulk vs. Wolverine and Thor] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090222152656/http://fpsmagazine.com/blog/2008/07/lionsgate-hulk-vs-wolverine-and-thor.php |date=February 22, 2009}}. Frames Per Second.</ref><ref name=ds>{{cite news|last=Langshaw|first=Mark|title='Planet Hulk' coming to DVD in February|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/comics/news/a187370/planet-hulk-coming-to-dvd-in-february.html|access-date=May 15, 2014|newspaper=Digital Spy|date=November 17, 2009|archive-date=August 26, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140826113930/http://www.digitalspy.com/comics/news/a187370/planet-hulk-coming-to-dvd-in-february.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=msp>{{cite news|last=Marshall|first=Rick|title='Planet Hulk' Review|url=http://splashpage.mtv.com/2010/02/02/planet-hulk-review/|access-date=May 15, 2014|newspaper=MTV Splash Page|date=February 2, 2010|archive-date=October 1, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001152755/http://splashpage.mtv.com/2010/02/02/planet-hulk-review/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Tabu |first=Hannibal |date=August 8, 2007 |title=The Dark Knight, Iron Man, Speed Racer: August 8th Comic Reel Wrap |url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article&id=11119 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160312025235/http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article&id=11119 |archive-date=March 12, 2016 |access-date=2014-03-15 |newspaper=Comic Book Resources}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Anderson |first=Jeffrey M. |date=2013-12-17 |title=Thor: Tales of Asgard |url=https://www.commonsensemedia.org/movie-reviews/thor-tales-of-asgard |publisher=[[Common Sense Media]] |access-date=2014-07-01 |archive-date=July 14, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714223130/https://www.commonsensemedia.org/movie-reviews/thor-tales-of-asgard |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=White |first=Cindy |date=2011-05-05 |title=Thor Tales of Asgard Blu-ray Review |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2011/05/05/thor-tales-of-asgard-blu-ray-review|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110507031427/http://bluray.ign.com/articles/116/1166272p1.html|archive-date=May 7, 2011 |publisher=[[IGN]] |access-date=2011-05-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=O'Ehley |first=James |date=2011-05-16 |title=THOR: TALES OF ASGARD (2011) |url=http://www.scifimoviepage.com/dvd/thor_tales_of_asgard-dvd.html |publisher=Sci-Fi Movie Page |access-date=2014-07-01 |archive-date=July 15, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715084920/http://www.scifimoviepage.com/dvd/thor_tales_of_asgard-dvd.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Davis Kho |first=Nancy |date=2008-12-15 |title=Next Avengers: Heroes of Tomorrow |url=https://www.commonsensemedia.org/movie-reviews/next-avengers-heroes-of-tomorrow |publisher=[[Common Sense Media]] |access-date=2014-07-01 |archive-date=July 14, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714164541/https://www.commonsensemedia.org/movie-reviews/next-avengers-heroes-of-tomorrow |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldsfinestonline.com/news.php?action=fullnews&showcomments=1&id=445 |title=Lauren Montgomery on "Green Lantern: First Flight" |author=Harvey, James |publisher=worldsfinestonline.com |date=2009-05-14 |access-date=2009-05-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Harvey|first=Jim|title=George Newbern Talks Playing Superman, New Media From "Superman Versus The Elite"|url=http://www.worldsfinestonline.com/2012/05/george-newbern-talks-playing-superman-new-media-from-superman-versus-the-elite/ |work=World's Finest |access-date=2013-08-11 |date=2012-05-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Harvey |first=Jim |url=http://www.worldsfinestonline.com/2013/03/blu-ray-dvd-package-artwork-for-superman-unbound-animated-feature-release/ |title=Blu-Ray, DVD Package Artwork For "Superman: Unbound" Animated Feature Release |publisher=Worldsfinestonline.com |date=2013-03-04 |access-date=January 30, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://variety.com/2013/video/reviews/dvd-review-superman-unbound-1200416024/ | title=Review: 'Superman: Unbound' |work=variety.com |date=2013-04-29 | access-date=January 30, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.commonsensemedia.org/movie-reviews/superman-unbound | title=Superman: Unbound | work=commonsensemedia.org |date=2013-05-10 | access-date=January 30, 2015}}</ref>

====Video games====
''[[Pac-Man (franchise)|Pac-Man]]'', a Japanese video game franchise, has an [[Pac-Man (TV series)|American cartoon]] that was produced by [[Hanna-Barbera]]. Made in 1982, the cartoon was very faithful to the source material in terms of plotline, characters and their names, and references to the original games.<ref name="Daytime">{{Cite book |last=Hyatt |first=Wesley |url=https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofda00hyat/page/332/mode/2up |title=The Encyclopedia of Daytime Television |date=1997 |publisher=Watson-Guptill Publications |isbn=978-0823083152 |page=332 |access-date=19 March 2020}}</ref> It also stands out as the very first [[List of television series based on video games|cartoon based on a video game, as well as the first cartoon to be based from a Japanese franchise]].<ref>{{cite magazine |title=100 Defining Moments in Video Games|magazine=[[Game Informer]]|date=August 2001|issue=100|pages=51}}</ref><ref name="Cash-Box">{{Cite magazine |last=Ressner |first=Jeffrey |date=20 November 1982 |title=Stan Jarocki: Expanded Player Base Is The Key To The Future |url=https://archive.org/details/cashbox44unse_23/page/56 |magazine=[[Cash Box]] |publisher=Cash Box Pub. Co. |pages=52–56 (56)}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |title=Look out, Saturday morning TV! Here comes... Pac-Man-imation! |magazine=[[Electronic Fun with Computers & Games]] |date=February 1983 |volume=1 |issue=4 |pages=44–6 |url=https://archive.org/details/Electronic_Fun_with_Computer_Games_Vol_01_No_01_1982-11_Fun_Games_Publishing_US/page/n43/mode/2up}}</ref><ref name="HBPacMan">{{cite book |last=Browsh|first=Jared Bahir|year=2022|orig-year=first published 2022|title=Hanna-Barbera: A History |publisher=  McFarland |isbn=978-1476675794}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |last=Sennett |first=Ted |url=https://archive.org/details/artofhannabarber00teds/page/236/mode/2up |title=The Art of Hanna-Barbera: Fifty Years of Creativity |date=1989 |publisher=Studio |isbn=978-0670829781 |page=236 |access-date=2 June 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |last=Lenburg |first=Jeff |url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9780816038312/page/307/mode/2up |title=The Encyclopedia of Animated Cartoons |date=1999 |publisher=Checkmark Books |isbn=0-8160-3831-7 |page=307 |access-date=6 June 2020}}</ref> The cartoon's success also led to a Halloween special and a [[Christmas Comes to Pac-Land|Christmas special]] that follows the same animation style and character design.<ref>{{Cite web |year=1998 |title=Pac-Man Halloween Special, The @ Toonarific cartoons |url=http://www.toonarific.com/show.php?show_id=2727 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040624113553/http://www.toonarific.com/show.php?show_id=2727 |url-status=dead |archive-date=June 24, 2004 |access-date=June 9, 2012 |website=Toonarific.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thoughtco.com/pac-man-game-1779412|title = The Story Behind Pac-Man, a Super Popular Video Game of the '80s}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2010/SHOWBIZ/TV/12/10/geekiest.holiday.movies.go/|title = Geeks' most beloved holiday classics}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |last=Erickson |first=Hal |title=Television Cartoon Shows: An Illustrated Encyclopedia, 1949 Through 2003 |date=2005 |publisher=McFarland & Co |isbn=978-1476665993 |edition=2nd |pages=600–602}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Pac-Man - Warner Archive Announces 'The Complete 1st Season' on DVD! |url=http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Pac-Man-Season-1/16433 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120125070616/http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Pac-Man-Season-1/16433 |archive-date=2012-01-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Pac-Man – Warner Archive is Now Selling the Second and Final Season...Santa Included! |url=http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Pac-Man-Season-2/17478 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141024184619/http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Pac-Man-Season-2/17478 |archive-date=2014-10-24}}</ref>

''[[Captain N: The Game Master]]'' is a [[crossover (fiction)|crossover]] cartoon series that focuses upon several video games that were originally created in Japan, including ''[[Kid Icarus]]'', ''[[Mega Man (video game)|Mega Man]]'', ''[[Castlevania]]'', ''[[Donkey Kong]]'', ''[[Metroid (video game)|Metroid]]'', ''[[The Adventures of Bayou Billy]]'', ''[[Dragon Quest]]'', ''[[The Legend of Zelda]]'', and ''[[Wizards & Warriors]]'', among others; the animation itself has been heavily styled by anime despite the series itself being predominantly an American media project.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.nintendolife.com/news/2019/09/feature_10_strangest_moments_in_captain_n_the_game_master | title=10 Strangest Moments in Captain N: The Game Master | date=21 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Perlmutter |first1=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1538103739 |pages=109–110}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Erickson |first1=Hal |title=Television Cartoon Shows: An Illustrated Encyclopedia, 1949 Through 2003 |date=2005 |edition=2nd |publisher=McFarland & Co |isbn=978-1476665993 |pages=178–179}}</ref><ref name="RSCN">{{cite magazine | url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/flashback-nintendo-entertains-gamers-with-captain-n-the-game-master-cartoon-124904/ | title=Flashback: Nintendo's Gamer Cartoon 'Captain N: The Game Master' | magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] | date=3 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{citation|url=http://www.nintendoplayer.com/feature/the-man-behind-captain-nintendo/ |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130916223607/http://www.nintendoplayer.com/the-man-behind-captain-nintendo/ |archive-date=2013-09-16 |publisher=Nintendo Player |title=The Man Behind Captain Nintendo |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=User Account |url=https://archive.org/details/@duke_togo?tab=uploads |website=archive.org |publisher=Nintendo |access-date=12 October 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.destructoid.com/captain-n-concept-art-reveals-paperboy-as-the-main-hero/ | title=Captain N concept art reveals Paperboy as the main hero | date=24 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=1992-01-13|title=A sampling of the programming wares at INTV|work=[[Broadcasting & Cable|Broadcasting]]|url=https://worldradiohistory.com/hd2/IDX-Business/Magazines/Archive-BC-IDX/92-OCR/BC-1992-01-13-OCR-Page-0014.pdf|access-date=2021-11-12}}</ref>

While the ''[[Mario (franchise)|Mario]]'' franchise is originally a Japanese IP, it also has popular influence in [[Italy]], [[Canada]], and the United States, which led to animated co-productions in the form of ''[[The Super Mario Bros. Super Show!]]'', ''[[The Adventures of Super Mario Bros. 3]]'', ''[[Super Mario World (TV series)|Super Mario World]]'', and most recently, ''[[The Super Mario Bros. Movie]]''.<ref>{{cite web |author=Emad Ahmed |date=September 5, 2018 |title=When Sonic and Mario dominated children's television |url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-05-09-when-sonic-and-mario-dominated-childrens-television |access-date=March 24, 2019 |website=Eurogamer}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |last=Perlmutter |first=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1-5381-0373-9 |page=566}}</ref><ref name="BoysLife">{{Cite journal |last=Angelle |first=Denny |date=September 1989 |title=What's New on TV |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=z2YEAAAAMBAJ |journal=[[Boys' Life]] |volume=79 |issue=9 |page=16 |access-date=21 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=11 September 1989 |title=For kids: A 'Chip' off the Disney block |work=[[USA Today]] |page=3D}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=McWhertor |first=Michael |date=8 May 2019 |title=The Super Mario Bros. Super Show People Once Tried to Make Bizarre Metroid and Castlevania Cartoons |url=https://www.polygon.com/2019/5/8/18536769/super-mario-bros-power-hour-metroid-castlevania-cartoons-dic |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210624200411/https://www.polygon.com/2019/5/8/18536769/super-mario-bros-power-hour-metroid-castlevania-cartoons-dic |archive-date=24 June 2021 |access-date=19 June 2021 |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Healy |first=Michelle |date=1 February 1989 |title=Nintendo hungry? Try the cereal |work=[[USA Today]] |page=1D |quote=''The Super Mario Brothers Super Show'', a syndicated TV program for kids, airs in September. It will feature live action and animation.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=17 May 1989 |title='Super' Man |work=[[USA Today]] |page=3D |quote=Capt. Lou Albano, the bizarre wrestling manager, has been cast to play Mario, one of the two Brooklyn plumber brothers. Thursday, in anticipation of a big announcement bash, Albano will appear on "Live With Regis & Kathie Lee" to shed his beard.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |date=28 August 1989 |title=Syndication Marketplace |url=https://www.worldradiohistory.com/Archive-BC/BC-1989/BC-1989-08-28.pdf |url-status=live |journal=[[Broadcasting & Cable|Broadcasting]] |volume=117 |issue=9 |page=42 |archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20170628035522/http://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-BC/BC-1989/BC-1989-08-28.pdf |archive-date=28 June 2017 |access-date=11 December 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Puig |first=Claudia |date=17 April 1989 |title=MOVIES |url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1989-04-17-ca-1885-story.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210316234533/https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1989-04-17-ca-1885-story.html |archive-date=16 March 2021 |access-date=14 April 2022 |work=Los Angeles Times}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Kesten |first=Lou |date=16 May 1989 |title=Newsday – The Nintendo Virus Invades Children's Television (Part 2) |url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/99716488/newsday-the-nintendo-virus-invades/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220414063143/https://www.newspapers.com/clip/99716488/newsday-the-nintendo-virus-invades/ |archive-date=14 April 2022 |access-date=14 April 2022 |work=Newsday |page=138}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Walsh |first1=Mark |title=TV Stations Faulted for Dearth of Educational Fare |url=https://www.edweek.org/education/tv-stations-faulted-for-dearth-of-educational-fare/1992/10 |access-date=8 March 2021 |work=Education Week |date=7 October 1992 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Andrews |first=Edmund L. |date=4 March 1993 |title='Flintstones' and Programs Like It Aren't Educational, F.C.C. Says |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1993/03/04/us/flintstones-and-programs-like-it-aren-t-educational-fcc-says.html |access-date=24 December 2023 |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=13 January 1992|title=A sampling of the programming wares at INTV|work=[[Broadcasting & Cable|Broadcasting]]|url=https://worldradiohistory.com/hd2/IDX-Business/Magazines/Archive-BC-IDX/92-OCR/BC-1992-01-13-OCR-Page-0014.pdf|access-date=12 November 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Olsen |first=Mathew |date=February 3, 2020 |title=The Virtual Console Convinced Nintendo to Make a New Mario Movie |url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/miyamoto-explains-how-the-virtual-console-convinced-nintendo-to-make-a-new-mario-movie |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203155924/https://www.usgamer.net/articles/miyamoto-explains-how-the-virtual-console-convinced-nintendo-to-make-a-new-mario-movie |archive-date=February 3, 2020 |access-date=February 3, 2020 |website=[[USGamer]]}}</ref><ref name="Minotti2018">{{Cite web |last=Minotti |first=Mike |date=January 9, 2018 |title=Nintendo's Miyamoto explains how Illumination won Mario movie rights |url=https://venturebeat.com/2018/02/09/nintendos-miyamoto-explains-how-illumination-won-mario-movie-rights/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210003253/https://venturebeat.com/2018/02/09/nintendos-miyamoto-explains-how-illumination-won-mario-movie-rights/ |archive-date=February 10, 2018 |access-date=January 9, 2018 |website=[[VentureBeat]]}}</ref><ref name="Sony">{{Cite news |last=Vary |first=Adam |date=December 11, 2014 |title=Sony Pictures Lands "Mario Bros." Movie Rights From Nintendo, Leaked Emails Show |work=[[BuzzFeed News]] |url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/adambvary/sony-nintendo-mario-bros-movie#.duwkpjZgV |url-status=live |access-date=December 11, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141212093710/http://www.buzzfeed.com/adambvary/sony-nintendo-mario-bros-movie#.duwkpjZgV |archive-date=December 12, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Fritz |first1=Ben |last2=Mochizuki |first2=Takashi |date=November 14, 2017 |title=Mario Bros. Set to Jump to Big Screen in Movie Deal with Universal's Illumination |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/mario-bros-set-to-jump-to-big-screen-in-movie-deal-with-universals-illumination-1510675881 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20171114213739/https://www.wsj.com/articles/mario-bros-set-to-jump-to-big-screen-in-movie-deal-with-universals-illumination-1510675881 |archive-date=November 14, 2017 |access-date=September 23, 2021 |website=[[The Wall Street Journal]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Blair |first=Gavin J. |date=January 31, 2018 |title='Mario' Movie to Be Produced by Nintendo and Illumination |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/mario-movie-be-produced-by-nintendos-shigeru-miyamoto-illumination-1080822 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210306110724/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/mario-movie-be-produced-by-nintendos-shigeru-miyamoto-illumination-1080822 |archive-date=March 6, 2021 |access-date=January 31, 2018 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref> Meanwhile, in Mario's home country, Japan, [[List of non-video game media featuring Mario#Anime|numerous anime projects]]<ref>{{cite web|title=ゲームアニメ大行進 (その12)|url=http://www5d.biglobe.ne.jp/~t-suzuki/vol.12/gma_12.htm|publisher=BIGLOBE|access-date=October 14, 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20041125030616/http://www5d.biglobe.ne.jp/~t-suzuki/vol.12/gma_12.htm|archive-date=November 25, 2004}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://themushroomkingdom.net/mania/anime_amada.shtml|title=TMK {{!}} Mario Mania {{!}} Super Mario Bros. (Amada series)|website=themushroomkingdom.net|access-date=2024-10-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/youtube-miRbUMpdgJE|title=【てれびっこ】スーパーマリオワールド マリオとヨッシーの冒険ランド [SMW: Mario & Yoshi's Adventure Land (Bandai Terebikko)]|date=April 15, 2016|via=Internet Archive}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://minusworld.co.uk/2017/03/29/mario-terebikko/|title=A Super Mario World Re-Telling, Released on VHS and Controlled with a Fake Telephone|first=Oliver|last=Jameson|date=March 29, 2017|access-date=March 25, 2019|archive-date=March 25, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190325140034/https://minusworld.co.uk/2017/03/29/mario-terebikko/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt8922116/|title=Super Mario World: Mario & Yoshi's Adventure Land|date=10 August 1991|via=www.imdb.com|access-date=21 August 2019|archive-date=8 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190408152118/https://www.imdb.com/title/tt8922116/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.a-suma.com/old/video/smabc.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200911082513/http://www.a-suma.com/old/video/smabc.htm|url-status=live|archive-date=September 11, 2020|title=スーパーマリオ ＡＢＣのうたビデオ|quote=英語はネイティブによる完璧な発音・発声で、 マリオの声はＮＨＫの教育番組でお馴染み、Gerri Sorrells（ジェリーソーレス）さんが当てている。 パッケージの「ＡＢＣ」のルビも「エイビースィー」と完璧な発音。|date=September 9, 2024}}</ref><ref name="Gerri 1">{{cite web|title=Gerri Sorrells|date=November 2003|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/life/2003/11/01/people/gerri-sorrells/|publisher=The Japan Times|access-date=May 1, 2021|archive-date=May 1, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210501163923/https://www.japantimes.co.jp/life/2003/11/01/people/gerri-sorrells/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=英語ナレーターボイスサンプル:ジェリー・ソーレス Gerri Sorrells|url=http://www.narrator.jp/page/narrators/gerrisorrells.html|publisher=Narrator.jp|access-date=May 1, 2021|archive-date=May 1, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210501163923/http://www.narrator.jp/page/narrators/gerrisorrells.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.a-suma.com/video/mkmv.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120326111108/http://www.a-suma.com/video/mkmv.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=March 26, 2012|title=マリオビデオ＞マリオ・カービィ 名作ビデオ|date=March 26, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt3522602/|title=Mario Kirby Meisaku Video|via=www.imdb.com|access-date=2017-02-16|archive-date=2017-02-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170217142740/http://www.imdb.com/title/tt3522602/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesniped.com/2011/06/05/mario-kirby-meisaku-vhs-video/|title=Mario Kirby Meisaku VHS Video|date=June 5, 2011|website=Rare Video Games Auctions, Sales & Pricing|access-date=August 21, 2019|archive-date=September 21, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200921065912/https://gamesniped.com/2011/06/05/mario-kirby-meisaku-vhs-video/|url-status=dead}}</ref> and a [[Super Mario Bros.: The Great Mission to Rescue Princess Peach!|1986 anime film]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=O'Neal |first1=Chris |title=Super Mario Bros. at 35: A Look Back at the Series' Anime Legacy |url=https://www.cbr.com/super-mario-bros-anniversary-anime/ |accessdate=4 October 2020 |work=CBR.com |date=April 12, 2020 |archive-date=17 May 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200517071802/https://www.cbr.com/super-mario-bros-anniversary-anime/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |date=15 June 1986 |title=Overseas Readers Column: "Super Mario Bros." Coming In The Movies |url=https://onitama.tv/gamemachine/pdf/19860615p.pdf#page=12 |magazine=[[:ja:ゲームマシン|Game Machine]] |publisher=[[:ja:アミューズメント通信社|Amusement Press, Inc.]] |page=22 |issue=286}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Plunkett |first1=Luke |title=There was a Good Super Mario Bros. Movie. Let's Watch it! |url=https://kotaku.com/there-was-a-good-super-mario-bros-movie-lets-watch-it-5903602 |accessdate=4 October 2020 |work=Kotaku |date=April 19, 2012 |archive-date=7 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201007131408/https://kotaku.com/there-was-a-good-super-mario-bros-movie-lets-watch-it-5903602 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Innes|first=Ruby|date=April 19, 2022|title=Diehard Fans Have Completely Remastered A Forgotten Mario Movie In 4K|url=https://www.kotaku.com.au/2022/04/super-mario-bros-the-great-mission-to-rescue-princess-peach/|access-date=May 10, 2022|website=[[Kotaku|Kotaku Australia]]|archive-date=May 10, 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220510140529/https://www.kotaku.com.au/2022/04/super-mario-bros-the-great-mission-to-rescue-princess-peach/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Peters |first=Megan |date=April 11, 2023 |title=New Super Mario Movie Features Callback to a 1986 Anime |url=https://comicbook.com/anime/news/super-mario-movie-easter-egg-anime/ |access-date=2024-01-11 |website=ComicBook.com}}</ref> have depicted the titular character and his brother, some of which actually follow the plot lines from the original video games.

While the ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog (franchise)|Sonic the Hedgehog]]'' franchise is originally a Japanese IP, it also has popular influence in [[Italy]], [[France]], [[Canada]], and the United States, which led to animated co-productions in the form of ''[[Adventures of Sonic the Hedgehog]]'' (1993–1996),<ref>{{cite web|title=''Adventures of Sonic the Hedgehog''|url=http://dhxmedia.com/shows/animation/sonicthehedgehogadventuresof.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150317103740/http://dhxmedia.com/shows/animation/sonicthehedgehogadventuresof.html|archive-date=March 17, 2015|access-date=June 18, 2021|publisher=DHX Media|quote=Sonic the Hedgehog, the most fearless hero on Planet Mobius, uses his supersonic speed and teenage irreverence to thwart the comedically despicable Dr. Robotnik. Sonic's idolizing little buddy, Tails, tags along on every fast-action, gag-driven adventure.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Emad Ahmed |date=September 5, 2018 |title=When Sonic and Mario dominated children's television |url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-05-09-when-sonic-and-mario-dominated-childrens-television |access-date=March 24, 2019 |website=Eurogamer}}</ref> the [[Sonic the Hedgehog (TV series)|TV series of the same name]] (1993–1994),<ref>{{cite web|last=Plant|first=Gaz|date=October 18, 2013|title=Feature: A Supersonic History of Sonic Cartoons|url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2013/10/feature_a_supersonic_history_of_sonic_cartoons|access-date=June 19, 2021|website=Nintendo Life}}</ref><ref>Way Past Cool!: A Conversation with Ben Hurst, Sonic The Hedgehog – The Complete Series. Brian Ward. [[Cookie Jar Entertainment]]. Burbank, California. 2007. B000M8N41W.</ref> ''[[Sonic Underground|Underground]]'' (1999),<ref>{{cite book |last1=Erickson |first1=Hal |title=Television Cartoon Shows: An Illustrated Encyclopedia, 1949 Through 2003 |date=2005 |publisher=McFarland & Co |isbn=978-1476665993 |edition=2nd |pages=757–760}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=SAGE - Sonic Amateur Games Expo 2008|url=http://www.sagexpo.org|access-date=2013-10-22 |publisher=Sagexpo.org}}</ref> ''[[Sonic Boom (TV series)|Boom]]'' (2014–2017)<ref name=blog1>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.sega.com/2013/10/02/sonic-boom-working-title-a-new-animated-series-coming-fall-2014/|title=Sonic Boom (Working Title) – A New Animated Series Coming Fall 2014|date=2013-10-02 |publisher=[[Sega]].com|access-date=2014-02-06 |archive-date=2015-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905185122/http://blogs.sega.com/2013/10/02/sonic-boom-working-title-a-new-animated-series-coming-fall-2014/|url-status=dead}}</ref> and ''[[Sonic Prime|Prime]]'' (2022–2024).<ref>{{cite web|last=Shin|first=Sophia|date=February 1, 2021|title=Sonic the Hedgehog Speeds Over to Netflix in the All-New Animated Series 'Sonic Prime'|url=https://about.netflix.com/en/news/sonic-the-hedgehog-speeds-over-to-netflix-in-the-all-new-animated-series|access-date=February 1, 2021|website=Netflix Media Center|language=en}}</ref><ref name="Polygon">{{cite web|last1=McWhertor|first1=Michael|date=December 10, 2020|title=New Sonic the Hedgehog animated series coming to Netflix|url=https://www.polygon.com/2020/12/10/22167777/netflix-sonic-the-hedgehog-new-animated-series-date|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210201192302/https://www.polygon.com/2020/12/10/22167777/netflix-sonic-the-hedgehog-new-animated-series-date|archive-date=February 1, 2021|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]}}</ref> Meanwhile, in Sonic's home country, Japan, two [[anime|animated]] projects exist in form of the [[Sonic the Hedgehog (OVA)|anime movie of the same name]] (1996),<ref>{{cite web |date=September 9, 1999 |title=Sonic the Hedgehog DVD! |url=http://www.advfilms.com/advhome/catalog/news.html |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/19991115144335/http://www.advfilms.com/advhome/catalog/news.html |archive-date=November 15, 1999 |access-date=June 18, 2021 |publisher=[[ADV Films]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=studioぴえろ 作品年表(OVA) |url=http://pierrot.jp/archive/ova/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091214192604/http://pierrot.jp/title/list_ova.html |archive-date=December 14, 2009 |access-date=January 18, 2021 |publisher=[[Pierrot (company)|Studio Pierrot]] |language=ja}}</ref> and ''[[Sonic X|X]]'' (2003–2005).<ref name="them">{{cite web|last=Jones|first=Tim|title=Sonic X|url=http://www.themanime.org/viewreview.php?id=355|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140915060412/http://themanime.org/viewreview.php?id=355|archive-date=September 15, 2014|access-date=June 19, 2021|publisher=THEM Anime}}</ref><ref name="famguy12">{{cite magazine|date=March 18, 2003|title=アニメ『ソニックX』の制作発表会が開催！|url=https://www.famitsu.com/game/news/1139336_1124.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141019045655/http://www.famitsu.com/game/news/1139336_1124.html|archive-date=October 19, 2014|access-date=June 19, 2021|magazine=[[Famitsu]]|language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=これまでの話|url=https://www.tv-tokyo.co.jp/anime/sonic_x/story.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304055035/http://www.tv-tokyo.co.jp/anime/sonic_x/story.html|archive-date=March 4, 2016|access-date=June 19, 2021|publisher=[[TV Tokyo]]|language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=ソニックＸ|url=https://www.kids-station.com/programs/KS00094127|url-status=dead|access-date=June 19, 2021|publisher=[[Kids Station]]|language=ja|archive-date=September 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200903165542/https://www.kids-station.com/programs/KS00094127}}</ref><ref name="producer">{{Cite web|last=Rasmussen|first=David|date=February 12, 2006|title=mr. michael haigney interview (4kids)|url=https://animeboredom.co.uk/anime-articles/80|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070217075303/http://www.animeboredom.co.uk/anime-articles/80|archive-date=February 17, 2007|access-date=April 30, 2014|publisher=Anime Boredom}}</ref>

While ''[[Mega Man]]'' is a Japanese property to begin with, there are two animated television series featuring the titular character and is based on the franchise, ''[[Mega Man (1994 TV series)|Mega Man]]'' (1994), an American cartoon co-produced by [[Ruby-Spears Productions]] and [[Ashi Productions]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-12-20 |title=アニメ『ロックマン USA』アマプラほかで配信開始。1994年にアメリカで放送された『ロックマン』原作のアニメが日本初上陸。日本語字幕に対応 |url=https://www.famitsu.com/article/202412/28306 |access-date=2025-09-04 |website=[[Famitsu]] |language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Perlmutter |first1=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1538103739 |pages=384–385}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |year=2011 |title=Joe Ruby on the American Mega Man cartoon! |url=https://siphersaysstuff.tumblr.com/post/8519989554/joerubyinterview |access-date=August 22, 2022 |website=Sipher Says Stuff |publisher=[[Tumblr]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Iikura-Gross|first=Ken|title=Japan Finally Gets to Watch the 1994 Mega Man Animated Series|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2025-01-05/japan-finally-gets-to-watch-the-1994-mega-man-animated-series/.219437|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=6 January 2024|access-date=12 January 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news| newspaper=[[Business Wire]] | title=Capcom's cartoon cavalcade begins this fall. | date=September 25, 1995 | url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/article-1G1-17469403/capcom-cartoon-cavalcade-begins.html | access-date=2010-02-14}}</ref> and ''[[Mega Man: Fully Charged|Fully Charged]]'' (2018), an American-Canadian [[Computer-generated imagery|CGI]] cartoon co-produced by [[Man of Action Studios]], Dentsu Entertainment USA, and [[DHX Media|DHX Studios Vancouver]]. Both cartoons notably draw inspiration from the [[Mega Man#Original series|"Classic" series]] from the original video games.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Carpenter|first1=Nicole|title=Mega Man Animated Series Will Introduce Alter-Ego; New Image Revealed|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/05/26/mega-man-animated-series-will-introduce-alter-ego-new-image-revealed|website=IGN|access-date=January 4, 2018|date=May 26, 2016}}</ref><ref name="AVClub">{{Cite news|url=https://www.avclub.com/cartoon-network-picks-up-new-mega-man-animated-series-1798259864|title=Cartoon Network picks up new Mega Man animated series|last=Gerardi|first=Matt|work=The A.V. Club|date=April 3, 2017|access-date=July 21, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-03/new-mega-man-animated-series-to-air-on-cartoon-network-in-2018-or-later/.114266|title=New Mega Man Animated Series to Air on Cartoon Network in 2018 or Later|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 3, 2017|access-date=May 21, 2017}}</ref><ref name="Premiere">{{cite web|url=https://collider.com/mega-man-fully-charged-release-date/|title='Mega Man: Fully Charged' to Premiere on Cartoon Network This August|website=Collider|last=Trumbore|first=Dave|date=July 18, 2018|access-date=July 18, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syfy.com/syfywire/mega-man-fully-charged-animated-series-debuts-first-trailer|title=Mega Man: Fully Charged animated series debuts first trailer|first=Andrew|last=Wheeler|work=[[Syfy Wire]]|publisher=[[NBCUniversal Cable Entertainment Group]]|date=July 21, 2018|access-date=July 21, 2018|archive-date=June 13, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210613110332/https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/mega-man-fully-charged-animated-series-debuts-first-trailer|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.themmnetwork.com/blog/2015/9/27/man-of-action-entertainments-duncan-rouleau-talks-mega-man|title=Man of Action Entertainment's Duncan Rouleau Talks Mega Man|date=September 28, 2015 |publisher=The Mega Man Network}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/05/mega-man-animated-series-dhx-man-of-action-1201762975/|title=DHX Media Boards 'Mega Man' Animated TV Series Based On Classic Video Game|first=Ross|last=Lincoln|date=May 26, 2016|access-date=July 9, 2018|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nerdist.com/the-new-mega-man-animated-series-will-have-a-more-optimistic-blue-bomber/|title=The New MEGA MAN Animated Series Will Have a More Optimistic Blue Bomber|first=Dan|last=Casey|date=August 18, 2016|access-date=July 9, 2018|work=[[Nerdist Industries|Nerdist]]|publisher=[[Legendary Entertainment|Legendary Digital Networks]]|archive-date=August 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820192201/https://nerdist.com/the-new-mega-man-animated-series-will-have-a-more-optimistic-blue-bomber/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nerdist.com/the-new-mega-man-animated-series-will-have-a-more-optimistic-blue-bomber/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820192201/https://nerdist.com/the-new-mega-man-animated-series-will-have-a-more-optimistic-blue-bomber/|title=The New MEGA MAN Animated Series Will Have a More Optimistic Blue Bomber|first=Dan|last=Casey|date=August 18, 2016|access-date=July 9, 2018|archive-date=August 20, 2016|work=[[Nerdist Industries|Nerdist]]|publisher=[[Legendary Entertainment|Legendary Digital Networks]]|quote=Created in 1987, Mega Man is standing on the precipice of his thirtieth anniversary, and Capcom is celebrating by partnering with Disney XD and Man of Action Entertainment for a brand new animated series launching in 2017.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockman-corner.com/2016/08/new-mega-man-cartoon-to-air-on-disney.html|title=New Mega Man Cartoon to Air on Disney XD; Stars an "Optimistic Blue Bomber"|work=Rockman Corner|date=August 19, 2016|access-date=July 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockman-corner.com/2017/01/a-couple-updates-about-new-mega-man.html|title=A Couple Updates About the New Mega Man Cartoon|work=Rockman Corner|date=January 23, 2017|access-date=July 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Hayes|first1=Matthew|t