'''Larissa de Macedo Machado''' (born 30 March 1993),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dicionariompb.com.br/anitta |title=Perfil: Anitta |publisher=[[Dicionário Cravo Albin da Música Popular Brasileira]] |language=pt |access-date=31 March 2018 |archive-date=3 November 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103140014/http://www.dicionariompb.com.br/anitta |url-status=dead }}</ref> known professionally as '''Anitta''' ({{IPA|pt-BR|audio=Pt-br-Anitta.ogg|ɐˈnitɐ|lang}}), is a Brazilian [[singer]], songwriter, dancer, actress, and occasional television host. One of Brazil's most prominent artists, she became known for her versatile style and mixing genres such as [[Pop music|pop]], [[Funk carioca|funk]], [[reggaeton]] and [[electronic music]]. She has received [[List of awards and nominations received by Anitta|numerous accolades]], including one [[Brazilian Music Awards|Brazilian Music Award]], four [[Latin American Music Awards]], three [[MTV Music Video Awards]], nine [[MTV Europe Music Awards]], two [[Guinness World Records]], and nominations for two [[Grammy Award]] and ten [[Latin Grammy Awards]], in addition to being the [[List of Brazilian entries on the Billboard Hot 100|Brazilian female singer with the most entries]] on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. She has been referred to as the "[[Honorific nicknames in popular music|Queen of Brazilian Pop]]".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Stern |first=Bradley |date=2018-08-29 |title=Meet Anitta: the Queen of Brazilian Pop |url=https://www.papermag.com/anitta-queen-of-brazilian-pop-2599818510.html#rebelltitem3 |access-date=2024-02-11 |website=Paper |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240229061055/https://www.papermag.com/anitta-queen-of-brazilian-pop#rebelltitem7#rebelltitem3 |archive-date=29 February 2024}}</ref><ref name="instyle">{{cite web |url=https://www.instyle.com/anitta-singer-interview-2023-7963970 |title=The Duality of Anitta |last=Kaplan |first=Ilana |date=September 14, 2023 |website=InStyle |access-date=May 4, 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230920080345/https://www.instyle.com/anitta-singer-interview-2023-7963970 |archive-date=September 20, 2023}}</ref>

Shortly after the release of her debut single, "[[Meiga e Abusada]]" (2012), Anitta signed a recording contract with [[Warner Music Group|Warner Music Brazil]] and released her [[Anitta (album)|self-titled debut album]] in 2013, which entered at number one and was certified platinum in Brazil. It produced the hit singles "[[Show das Poderosas]]" and "Zen", her first number-one on the [[Brasil Hot 100|''Billboard'' Brasil Hot 100]] and [[Latin Grammy Awards|Latin Grammy]] nomination. In 2014, she released her second studio album ''[[Ritmo Perfeito]]'' alongside the live album ''[[Meu Lugar]]'' to further commercial success. Her third studio album, ''[[Bang! (Anitta album)|Bang]]'' (2015), spawned the top-ten singles "[[Deixa Ele Sofrer]]” and "[[Bang (Anitta song)|Bang]]" and cemented Anitta’s standing as a major star on the Brazilian record charts. In 2017, Anitta released her first song fully in [[Spanish language|Spanish]], "[[Paradinha (song)|Paradinha]]", which accelerated her crossover to Spanish-language Latin and reggaeton genres, and released a project entitled ''CheckMate'', featuring several international collaborations and hits such as "[[Downtown (Anitta and J Balvin song)|Downtown]]" and "[[Vai Malandra]]". Her [[trilingual]] fourth studio-[[visual album]], ''[[Kisses (album)|Kisses]]'' (2019), earned a nomination for the [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Urban Music Album]].

Anitta's diamond-certified fifth studio album, ''[[Versions of Me]]'' (2022), contained the lead single "[[Envolver]]”, which topped the [[Brazil Songs|''Billboard'' Brazil Songs]] chart and became her breakthrough hit internationally. The song peaked at number one on the [[Billboard Global Excl. U.S.|''Billboard'' Global Excl. U.S.]] chart and number two on the [[Billboard Global 200|''Billboard'' Global 200]], making Anitta the first Brazilian artist to lead a global music chart. It also garnered her a [[Guinness World Record]] for being the first solo Latin artist and the first Brazilian act to reach number one on [[Spotify]]'s Global Top 200 chart. She became the first Brazilian artist to win the [[American Music Award for Favorite Latin Artist]] and the [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Latin]] for "Envolver"; she won the latter award two more consecutive times for "[[Funk Rave]]" and "[[Mil Veces]]" from her sixth studio album, ''[[Funk Generation]]'' (2024), which earned her first [[2024 Brazilian Music Award|Brazilian Music Awards]] win for Release in a Foreign Language. She also earned her second [[Grammy Awards|Grammy]] ([[67th Annual Grammy Awards|2025]]) nomination for [[Grammy Award for Best Latin Pop Album|Best Latin Pop Album]]; previously, Anitta had been nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]] at the [[65th Annual Grammy Awards]] and featured on ''[[Forbes]]''<nowiki/>'s 2023 [[Forbes 30 Under 30|30 Under 30]].

Anitta has been described by the media as a [[sex symbol]] and is considered as one of the most influential artists in the world on social networks,<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |title=Billboard elege Anitta como 15ª artista mais influente do mundo |url=https://exame.com/casual/anitta-e-eleita-a-15a-artista-mais-influente-do-mundo-pela-billboard/ |access-date=2024-11-11 |website=[[Exame]] |language=pt-br}}</ref> featuring on the [[Time 100 Next]] list. She is also known for her [[Philanthropy|philanthropic]] work. The causes she promotes include [[climate change]], [[Nature conservation|conservation]], the [[Environmental protection|environment]], [[Right to health|health]], and [[right to food]]; she also dedicates herself to advocating for [[LGBTQ movements|LGBT]], [[Indigenous rights|indigenous]] and [[women's rights]].

==Early life==
Larissa de Macedo Machado was born and raised in [[Honório Gurgel]], a Rio de Janeiro neighborhood with one of the lowest [[Human Development Index|HDIs]].<ref name="instyle" /><ref name="auto">{{Cite web |first=Guilherme |last=Alves |title=Vencedores do Prêmio Jovem Brasileiro 2016 e 2015 |url=http://www.breaktudo.com/vencedores-do-premio-jovem-brasileiro-2016 |work=BreakTudo |date=7 October 2016 |access-date=11 October 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304172425/https://www.breaktudo.com/vencedores-do-premio-jovem-brasileiro-2016/ |archive-date=4 March 2018 |language=pt-br |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="auto1">{{cite web |last=Torres |first=Leonardo |title=Anitta lançará álbum de inéditas em duas versões: de estúdio e ao vivo |url=http://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-lancara-album-de-ineditas-em-duas-versoes-de-estudio-e-ao-vivo |publisher=Portal POPLine |access-date=6 August 2016 |date=6 May 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140727112748/http://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-lancara-album-de-ineditas-em-duas-versoes-de-estudio-e-ao-vivo/ |archive-date=27 July 2014 |url-status=live |language=pt-BR}}</ref> She is the youngest daughter of Míriam Macedo and Mauro Machado of [[Afro-Brazilians|Afro-Brazilian]] descent.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://blackbraziltoday.com/in-brazil-no-one-is-white-says-anitta/ | title='In Brazil, no one is white', says Anitta &#124; Black Women of BRazil | date=6 March 2017 }}</ref> Her parents later divorced, with her mother obtaining custody.<ref name="family">{{cite web |last=Gomes |first=Lais |date=11 July 2014 |title=Com casa cheia, Anitta lança o DVD 'Meu lugar' em show no Rio |url=http://ego.globo.com/noite/noticia/2014/07/anitta-faz-lancamento-de-dvd-em-show-lotado-no-rio.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180714111304/http://ego.globo.com/noite/noticia/2014/07/anitta-faz-lancamento-de-dvd-em-show-lotado-no-rio.html |archive-date=14 July 2018 |access-date=6 August 2016 |publisher=[[TV Globo]] |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref name="sdp">{{cite news |title=Anitta comemora os 10 milhões de visualizações de 'Show das poderosas': 'Amo muito' |work=Extra Online |date=30 May 2013 |url=http://extra.globo.com/tv-e-lazer/musica/anitta-comemora-os-10-milhoes-de-visualizacoes-de-show-das-poderosas-amo-muito-8545131.html |access-date=6 August 2016 |language=pt-BR |archive-date=11 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180911072859/https://extra.globo.com/tv-e-lazer/musica/anitta-comemora-os-10-milhoes-de-visualizacoes-de-show-das-poderosas-amo-muito-8545131.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Her brother, Renan Machado, is one of her music producers and jointly manages her career.<ref name="brother">{{cite web |title=Mães lindas de Anitta e Arthur Aguiar roubam a cena; veja quem está no 'Tamanho Família' de 24/7 |date=24 July 2016 |url=http://gshow.globo.com/Bastidores/noticia/2016/07/maes-lindas-de-anitta-e-arthur-aguiar-roubam-cena-veja-quem-esta-no-tamanho-familia-de-247.html |publisher=[[TV Globo]] |access-date=6 August 2016 |language=pt-BR |archive-date=14 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180714111226/http://gshow.globo.com/Bastidores/noticia/2016/07/maes-lindas-de-anitta-e-arthur-aguiar-roubam-cena-veja-quem-esta-no-tamanho-familia-de-247.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

She began her singing when she was 8, joining the choir of Saint Luzia’s Parish in her neighborhood at her maternal grandparents’ insistence.<ref name="auto"/> She took her first English classes at 11, having demonstrated above-average intelligence and an interest in an academic career. Her mother’s teacher later gave her free dance lessons.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2013-07-07 |title=Anitta: O primeiro beijo, a emoção com o telefonema de Ivete e outras histórias contadas no bairro onde ela cresceu |url=https://extra.globo.com/famosos/anitta-primeiro-beijo-emocao-com-telefonema-de-ivete-outras-historias-contadas-no-bairro-onde-ela-cresceu-8938380.html |access-date=2025-02-14 |website=Extra Online |language=pt-BR}}</ref>

After graduating from [[Colégio Pedro II]], she finished a technical course in public administration in high school.<ref name="auto1" /><ref name="church">{{cite web |url=https://extra.globo.com/famosos/anitta-primeiro-beijo-emocao-com-telefonema-de-ivete-outras-historias-contadas-no-bairro-onde-ela-cresceu-8938380.html |date=7 July 2013 |title=Anitta: O primeiro beijo, a emoção com o telefonema de Ivete e outras histórias contadas no bairro onde ela cresceu |publisher=[[Globo.com]] |access-date=1 August 2020 |archive-date=30 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230330064008/https://extra.globo.com/famosos/anitta-primeiro-beijo-emocao-com-telefonema-de-ivete-outras-historias-contadas-no-bairro-onde-ela-cresceu-8938380.html |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2013, she decided to pursue her artistic career and won the "Best New Artist" award given by the Associação Paulista de Críticos de Arte, an organization based in [[São Paulo]], [[Brazil]], that honors the best in the Brazilian arts.<ref name="award and arts">{{cite web |title=Cantora Anitta é eleita a revelação do ano na música pela APCA - Notícias - UOL Entretenimento |url=http://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2013/12/10/cantora-anitta-e-eleita-a-revelacao-do-ano-pela-apca.htm |access-date=6 August 2016 |language=pt-BR |archive-date=13 September 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160913033907/http://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2013/12/10/cantora-anitta-e-eleita-a-revelacao-do-ano-pela-apca.htm |url-status=live }}</ref>

Anitta's stage name was inspired by the character "Anita" in the book ''[[Presença de Anita]],'' adapted as a teleseries by [[TV Globo]] in 2001.<ref name="auto" /> She thought the character was "amazing" because "[Anita] could be sexy without looking vulgar; girl and woman at the same time".<ref name="auto" /><ref name="auto2">{{Cite web |title=EMA 2015: Anitta se consagra e ganha prêmio "Worldwide Act: Latin America" |url=http://www.portalpopline.com.br/ema-2015-anitta-se-consagra-e-ganha-premio-worldwide-act-latin-america/ |work=Portal Pop Line |access-date=11 October 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151026225517/http://www.portalpopline.com.br/ema-2015-anitta-se-consagra-e-ganha-premio-worldwide-act-latin-america/ |archive-date=26 October 2015 |url-status=live |language=pt}}</ref>

Anitta speaks several languages: [[Brazilian Portuguese|Portuguese]] (her native language), English and [[Spanish language|Spanish]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Qual o segredo para o inglês de Anitta ser tão bom? Veja resposta e dicas para ajudar no aprendizado |url=https://br.noticias.yahoo.com/qual-o-segredo-para-o-215400737.html |access-date=2023-03-05 |website=br.noticias.yahoo.com |language=pt-BR |archive-date=26 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226004601/https://br.noticias.yahoo.com/qual-o-segredo-para-o-215400737.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Nonato |first=Amanda |date=2022-08-23 |title=4 segredos de Anitta para aprender idiomas |url=https://blog.descubraomundo.com/dicas/4-segredos-de-anitta-para-aprender-idiomas/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230305160351/https://blog.descubraomundo.com/dicas/4-segredos-de-anitta-para-aprender-idiomas/ |archive-date=5 March 2023 |access-date=2023-03-05 |website=Blog Descubra o Mundo |language=pt-BR}}</ref> as well as some [[Italian language|Italian]] and [[French language|French]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Com músicas em 5 línguas, Anitta usou aplicativos para aprender italiano |url=https://www.uol.com.br/splash/noticias/2021/07/01/com-musicas-em-5-linguas-anitta-usou-aplicativos-para-aprender-italiano.htm |access-date=2023-03-05 |website=Splash |language=pt-br |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226004601/https://www.uol.com.br/splash/noticias/2021/07/01/com-musicas-em-5-linguas-anitta-usou-aplicativos-para-aprender-italiano.htm |archive-date=26 February 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta fala três línguas em vídeo da Vogue México gravado na Itália |url=https://vogue.globo.com/celebridades/noticia/2022/12/anitta-fala-tres-linguas-em-video-da-vogue-mexico-gravado-na-italia.ghtml |access-date=2023-03-05 |website=Vogue |date=15 December 2022 |language=pt-br |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230427005953/https://vogue.globo.com/celebridades/noticia/2022/12/anitta-fala-tres-linguas-em-video-da-vogue-mexico-gravado-na-italia.ghtml |archive-date=27 April 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Santos |first=Emily |date=17 July 2022 |title=Fluente em inglês e espanhol e com francês e italiano intermediários: como Anitta se vira em tantos idiomas? |url=https://g1.globo.com/educacao/noticia/2022/07/17/fluente-em-ingles-e-espanhol-e-com-frances-e-italiano-intermediarios-como-anitta-se-vira-em-tantos-idiomas.ghtml |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221128220158/https://g1.globo.com/educacao/noticia/2022/07/17/fluente-em-ingles-e-espanhol-e-com-frances-e-italiano-intermediarios-como-anitta-se-vira-em-tantos-idiomas.ghtml |archive-date=28 November 2022 |access-date=2023-03-05 |website=G1 |language=pt-br}}</ref> Furthermore, she has taken [[Japanese language|Japanese]] classes and plans to learn [[Korean language|Korean]].<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Gshow |first1=Priscilla Massena Do |last2=Rio |title=Poderosa! Anitta estuda japonês e dá dica para quem quer cantar em inglês |url=http://gshow.globo.com/programas/mais-voce/So-na-web/noticia/2015/04/poderosa-anitta-estuda-japones-e-da-dica-para-quem-quer-cantar-em-ingles.html |access-date=2023-03-05 |website=Mais Você |language=pt-br |archive-date=26 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226004559/https://gshow.globo.com/programas/mais-voce/So-na-web/noticia/2015/04/poderosa-anitta-estuda-japones-e-da-dica-para-quem-quer-cantar-em-ingles.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta aprende japonês para turnê internacional: 'Queria falar todas as línguas' |url=https://www.purepeople.com.br/noticia/anitta-aprende-japones-para-turne-internacional-queria-falar-todas-as-linguas_a51408/1 |website=Pure People |date=13 April 2015 |language=br |access-date=May 4, 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226004607/https://www.purepeople.com.br/noticia/anitta-aprende-japones-para-turne-internacional-queria-falar-todas-as-linguas_a51408/1 |archive-date=26 February 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://portalfamosos.com.br/perguntada-sobre-colaboracao-com-bts-anitta-responde-adoraria-acho-que-teria-que-aprender-coreano/ |last=Pereira |first=Samuel |date=2021-11-13 |title=Perguntada sobre colaboração com BTS, Anitta responde: "adoraria, acho que teria que aprender coreano" |website=Portal Famosos Brasil |access-date=2023-03-05 |language=pt-BR |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220524000238/https://portalfamosos.com.br/perguntada-sobre-colaboracao-com-bts-anitta-responde-adoraria-acho-que-teria-que-aprender-coreano/ |archive-date=24 May 2022 }}</ref>

==Career==

===2012–2013: Debut album and initial success===
Anitta's career as a professional singer started in 2010, when she was introduced to the [[funk carioca]] producer Renato Azevedo, known as Batutinha.<ref name="instyle" /> She was invited to record some demo tapes for him, as he had seen some of her home videos on YouTube. She then signed a contract with independent label Furacão 2000, which was specialized on releasing [[Brazilian funk]] music.<ref name="instyle" /> She then released her debut single "Eu Vou Ficar", which was played on local radio stations in Rio de Janeiro and the song was included in the compilation album ''Armagedom'', which included other artists from the musical scene.{{Citation needed|date=August 2024}} With advice by her producer, she decided to put another "t" in her stage name, which was inspired by Brazilian television series ''[[Presença de Anita]]''.<ref name="auto1"/><ref name="song1">{{cite web|last=Essinger|first=Silvio|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/anitta-preparada-da-vez-9110966|title=Anitta, a preparada da vez|work=[[O Globo]]|language=pt-BR|date=21 July 2013|access-date=6 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330170154/https://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/anitta-preparada-da-vez-9110966|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> A year later, the song "Fica Só Olhando" was included on the ''Armagedom II'' release.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://imusica.com.br/album.aspx?id=354463 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130917070137/http://imusica.com.br/album.aspx?id=354463 |url-status=dead |archive-date=17 September 2013 |title=Armagedon II (Ao Vivo) |publisher=iMúsica |date=7 March 2017}}</ref> Her first televised appearance was on 16 May 2012, on TV program ''Cante se Puder'', on SBT, where she performed inside a glass of beer.<ref>{{cite news |last=João Paulo Dell Santo |first=João |title=Fast food vira tema de provas do "Cante se Puder" |url=https://rd1.com.br/fast-food-vira-tema-de-provas-do-cante-se-puder/ |work=RD1 |access-date=25 February 2019 |date=15 May 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170528040223/https://rd1.com.br/fast-food-vira-tema-de-provas-do-cante-se-puder/ |archive-date=28 May 2017}}</ref> In June 2012, she chose to not renew the Furacão 2000 contract and signed with [[K2L Entertainment]].<ref name="song1"/>

In January 2013, Anitta signed a recording contract with [[Warner Music Brasil]] and released the single "[[Meiga e Abusada]]".<ref name="instyle" /><ref name="auto1"/><ref name="song1"/> The song was then added to the telenovela [[Amor à Vida]]'s soundtrack and became one of the most requested songs in Brazilian radio stations in early 2013. A music video for the song was shot in Las Vegas, and directed by American director [[Blake Farber]].<ref name="song1"/> The song was chosen as lead single of her [[Anitta (album)|self-titled debut album]] was released in June 2013.<ref name="1stalbum">{{cite web |title='Mulheres estão tomando lugar dos homens no funk', diz MC Anitta |url=http://oglobo.globo.com/megazine/mulheres-estao-tomando-lugar-dos-homens-no-funk-diz-mc-anitta-8037896 |access-date=6 August 2016 |language=pt-BR |date=17 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330170150/https://oglobo.globo.com/megazine/mulheres-estao-tomando-lugar-dos-homens-no-funk-diz-mc-anitta-8037896 |archive-date=30 March 2019}}</ref>

In June 2013, the music video for "[[Show das Poderosas]]" became the most watched music video on YouTube in Brazil, surpassing 160 million views in less than a week after the release. The impact also helped the song to make it onto charts, which remained for many weeks at the top of the best selling music in [[iTunes]] Brazil, and making it the third most played song on the radio in the country during 2013.<ref name="sdp"/><ref name="fame">{{cite magazine |title=What to Expect at the Rio 2016 Opening Ceremony |url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2016/08/what-to-expect-at-the-rio-2016-opening-ceremony.html |first=Shannon G. |last=Sims |magazine=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste Magazine]] |date=5 August 2016 |access-date=6 August 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817140423/https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2016/08/what-to-expect-at-the-rio-2016-opening-ceremony.html |archive-date=17 August 2016 |url-status=dead}}</ref> At the time, with that, the singer's fee per presentation increased to US$10.000.<ref name="1stalbum"/>

===2014–2015: ''Meu Lugar'' and ''Ritmo Perfeito''===
[[File:38 - Anitta (38) (15861414503).jpg|thumb|left|Anitta during a concert in February 2015]]
Anitta announced in 2013 that she would start her first concert tour on that year. The sales to the tickets for the special series of shows, went on sale in November 2013.<ref>{{cite web |language=pt |title=Ingressos para gravação do DVD de Anitta custam de R$ 40 a R$ 160 |trans-title=Tickets for Anitta's DVD recording cost from R$ 40 to R$ 160 |url=http://g1.globo.com/rio-de-janeiro/musica/noticia/2013/11/ingressos-para-gravacao-do-dvd-de-anitta-custam-de-r-40-r-160.html |publisher=G1 |access-date=27 March 2014 |date=29 November 2013 |archive-date=23 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180723064126/http://g1.globo.com/rio-de-janeiro/musica/noticia/2013/11/ingressos-para-gravacao-do-dvd-de-anitta-custam-de-r-40-r-160.html |url-status=live }}</ref> The event took place in [[Rio de Janeiro]] at [[HSBC Arena (Rio de Janeiro)|HSBC Arena]] on 15 February 2014, and was attended by about 10,000 people.<ref>{{cite web |language=pt |last=Costa |first=Mariana |title=Em novo DVD, Anitta reduz presença do funk e faz novos arranjos para hits |url=http://musica.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2014/02/16/em-novo-dvd-anitta-reduz-presenca-do-funk-e-faz-novos-arranjos-para-hits.htm |publisher=[[Universo Online]] |access-date=27 March 2014 |date=16 February 2014 |archive-date=23 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180723122530/https://musica.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2014/02/16/em-novo-dvd-anitta-reduz-presenca-do-funk-e-faz-novos-arranjos-para-hits.htm |url-status=live }}</ref> The album was previously titled ''Fantástico Mundo de Anitta'' (Anitta's World),<ref>{{cite web |last=Costa |first=Mariana |title=DVD ao vivo de Anitta terá referências a Tim Burton e Cirque du Soleil |url=http://musica.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2014/02/05/dvd-ao-vivo-de-anitta-tera-referencias-a-tim-burton-e-cirque-du-soleil.htm |publisher=[[Universo Online]] |access-date=6 August 2016 |date=5 February 2014 |language=pt |archive-date=23 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180723122905/https://musica.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2014/02/05/dvd-ao-vivo-de-anitta-tera-referencias-a-tim-burton-e-cirque-du-soleil.htm |url-status=live }}</ref> but was later renamed to ''Meu Lugar'' (My Place), after the release of the song "Quem Sabe" on iTunes.<ref name="quem">{{cite web |title=Meu Lugar (Deluxe Version) de Anitta no Apple Music |date=3 June 2014 |url=https://music.apple.com/br/album/meu-lugar-ao-vivo-deluxe-version/873859012 |publisher=[[iTunes Store]] |access-date=6 August 2016 |archive-date=23 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180723072542/https://itunes.apple.com/br/album/meu-lugar-deluxe-version/id873859012 |url-status=live }}</ref> The song "Blá Blá Blá" was released as the lead single from the album on 23 March 2014.<ref name="blah">{{cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/tr/song/bl%C3%A1-bl%C3%A1-bl%C3%A1-extended-remix/946224706?l=tr |title=Anitta - Blá Blá Blá |access-date=May 4, 2025 |publisher=[[iTunes Store]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250504162258/https://music.apple.com/tr/song/bl%C3%A1-bl%C3%A1-bl%C3%A1-extended-remix/946224706?l=tr |archive-date=May 4, 2025}}</ref> Despite the success in minor proportions, the song reached the number two on the Hot 100 Airplay chart in Brazil.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.billboard.com.br/tipo_lista/top-100/20140712/ |title=Too 100 Billboard Brasil - Semanal |magazine=[[Billboard Brasil]] |access-date=5 July 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140809062138/http://www.billboard.com.br/tipo_lista/top-100/20140712/ |archive-date=9 August 2014 |url-status=dead}}</ref> The album was released on 4 June 2014, just a day after the release of her second studio album, ''[[Ritmo Perfeito]]''.

The second single from the project was a song featuring rapper [[Projota]] titled "Cobertor", which reached a number 43 on Brazilian charts.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.billboard.com.br/tipo_lista/top-100/20140913 |title=Top semanal Billboard |date=13 September 2014 |access-date=31 December 2016 |magazine=[[Billboard Brasil]] |archive-date=6 March 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306025322/http://billboard.com.br/tipo_lista/top-100/20140913/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> The following single "Na Batida" was released on 31 July 2014. Its music video reached 1 million views on YouTube after just 24 hours.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.portaldenoticias.net/novo-clipe-de-anitta-atinge-1-milhao-de-views-em-menos-de-24-horas-assista |title=Clipe de Anitta atinge 1 milhão de views |date=31 July 2014 |access-date=31 December 2016 |publisher=Portal de Notícias |archive-date=31 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331065551/https://www.portaldenoticias.net/novo-clipe-de-anitta-atinge-1-milhao-de-views-em-menos-de-24-horas-assista/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The single had a minor success on charts, peaking at number four on the Hot 100 Airplay chart.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.billboard.com.br/tipo_lista/top-100/20140920 |title=Top semanal Billboard |date=20 September 2014 |access-date=31 December 2016 |magazine=[[Billboard Brasil]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141026212936/http://www.billboard.com.br/tipo_lista/top-100/20140920/ |archive-date=26 October 2014 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Other singles released from the album were "Ritmo Perfeito" and "No Meu Talento", featuring [[MC Guimê]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://portalpopline.com.br/continuacao-de-ritmo-perfeito-anitta-tambem-vai-lancar-clipe-para-musica-no-meu-talento-veja-previa |title=Continuação de "Ritmo Perfeito"? Anitta também vai lançar clipe para música "No Meu Talento": veja prévia |date=11 December 2014 |publisher=Portal POPLine |last=Torres |first=Leonardo |language=pt |access-date=31 December 2016 |archive-date=28 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328002331/http://portalpopline.com.br/continuacao-de-ritmo-perfeito-anitta-tambem-vai-lancar-clipe-para-musica-no-meu-talento-veja-previa/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In April 2014, she made her acting debut as Helena Boccato in comedy film ''[[Copa de Elite]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://m.todateen.uol.com.br/fun-cinema-e-tv/musicos-que-ja-tiveram-papeis-cinema |title=15 músicos que já tiveram papéis no cinema |publisher=Todateen |date=26 January 2016 |language=pt |access-date=31 December 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160409193848/http://m.todateen.uol.com.br/fun-cinema-e-tv/musicos-que-ja-tiveram-papeis-cinema/ |archive-date=9 April 2016 |url-status=dead}}</ref> In August 2014, she founded her own management company, Rodamoinho Produções Artísticas. In December, she also starred as goddess Solaris in television film ''Didi e o Segredo dos Anjos''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://gshow.globo.com/Foi-dada-a-largada/noticia/2014/11/dos-palcos-para-telinha-anitta-aparece-poderosa-em-filme.html |title=Anitta: do palco para as telinhas, Anitta aparece poderosa em filme - Anitta Notícias |publisher=gshow.globo.com |date=10 November 2014 |access-date=31 December 2016 |archive-date=14 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211114080723/http://gshow.globo.com/Foi-dada-a-largada/noticia/2014/11/dos-palcos-para-telinha-anitta-aparece-poderosa-em-filme.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

===2015–2016: ''Bang'' and collaborations===
[[File:2016 Summer Olympics opening ceremony 1035385-Cropped and edited.jpg|thumb|Anitta with singers [[Caetano Veloso]] (left) and [[Gilberto Gil]] (right) performing at the [[2016 Summer Olympics opening ceremony]]]]
Her third studio album ''[[Bang (Anitta album)|Bang]]'' was released in October 2015. It was selected by ''[[Billboard Brasil]]'' as one of the most anticipated albums of the year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.portalfamosos.com.br/anitta-lexa-sandy-e-wanessa-estao-entre-os-lancamentos-mais-esperados-para-2015-pela-billboard-brasil |title=Anitta, Sandy e Wanessa estão entre os lançamentos mais esperados para 2015 pela Billboard Brasil |language=pt |access-date=1 November 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829131646/http://www.portalfamosos.com.br/anitta-lexa-sandy-e-wanessa-estao-entre-os-lancamentos-mais-esperados-para-2015-pela-billboard-brasil/ |archive-date=29 August 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Album's cover art was shot by [[Giovanni Bianco]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.portalpopline.com.br/bang-anitta-divulga-novas-fotos-promocionais-do-seu-novo-album/ |title=Bang: Anitta divulga novas fotos promocionais do seu novo álbum |language=pt |access-date=1 November 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151007091356/http://www.portalpopline.com.br/bang-anitta-divulga-novas-fotos-promocionais-do-seu-novo-album/ |archive-date=7 October 2015 |url-status=dead}}</ref> ''Bang'' debuted at number three on the Brazilian albums chart with 40,000 copies sold in the first week.<ref name="ABPD">{{cite web |url=http://www.portalpopline.com.br/bang-novo-album-da-anitta-recebe-certificado-de-ouro/ |publisher=Portal POPLine |title=Anitta recebe certificado de ouro com novo álbum 'Bang' |language=pt |access-date=6 August 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170708065924/http://portalpopline.com.br/bang-novo-album-da-anitta-recebe-certificado-de-ouro/ |archive-date=8 July 2017 |url-status=dead}}</ref> The album sold 300,000 copies as of May 2016, surpassing sales of her debut album, which has sold 170,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web |title=Anitta: a construção de uma estrela |date=29 April 2016 |access-date=6 August 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160430033856/https://issuu.com/ubc-uniaobrasileiradecompositores/docs/revistaubc28/12 |archive-date=30 April 2016 |url=https://issuu.com/ubc-uniaobrasileiradecompositores/docs/revistaubc28/12 |author=SOLER, Alessandro |publisher=União Brasileira de Compositores |language=pt}}</ref> It was also certified Platinum by the Associação Brasileira de Produtores de Discos (ABPD).<ref name="record">{{cite web |title=Poderosa! Anitta quebra recorde de vendas na carreira com 'Bang' |date=14 May 2016 |url=http://multishow.globo.com/musica/materias/anitta-quebra-recorde-de-vendas-com-bang.htm |publisher=Globo.com |access-date=6 August 2016 |archive-date=27 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327223331/http://multishow.globo.com/musica/materias/anitta-quebra-recorde-de-vendas-com-bang.htm |url-status=live }}</ref> The first single of the album, "[[Deixa Ele Sofrer]]", which was released on 16 July 2015, and reached the top of the iTunes Brazil chart.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://portalpopline.com.br/deixa-ele-sofrer-novo-single-da-anitta-data-de-lancamento-revelada/ |title="Deixa Ele Sofrer": novo single da Anitta data de lançamento revelada |date=11 December 2014 |language=pt |publisher=Portal POPLine |author=Torres, Leonardo |access-date=25 October 2015 |archive-date=26 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180826052023/http://portalpopline.com.br/deixa-ele-sofrer-novo-single-da-anitta-data-de-lancamento-revelada/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The song also made Anitta the first Brazilian singer to occupy the top of [[Spotify|Spotify Brazil]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Anitta se torna a primeira cantora brasileira a ocupar o ranking do Spotify |url=http://www.purepeople.com.br/noticia/anitta-se-torna-a-1-cantora-brasileira-a-ocupar-o-topo-do-ranking-do-spotify_a67957/1 |publisher=Pure People |access-date=6 August 2016 |date=6 May 2015 |archive-date=8 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180708192847/http://www.purepeople.com.br/noticia/anitta-se-torna-a-1-cantora-brasileira-a-ocupar-o-topo-do-ranking-do-spotify_a67957/1 |url-status=live }}</ref>

The album lead single, "[[Bang (Anitta song)|Bang]]", was her first international success, staying at number one on iTunes and Spotify for several days, and its music video becoming an international [[viral video]] and receiving over 320 million views on YouTube.<ref name="eonline">{{cite web |first=Diana |last=Marti |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/785793/5-things-to-know-about-anitta-olympic-opening-ceremony-performer |title=5 Things To Know About Anitta, Olympic Opening Ceremony Performer |date=6 August 2016 |access-date=31 March 2018 |publisher=[[E! Online]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220505180822/https://www.eonline.com/news/785793/5-things-to-know-about-anitta-olympic-opening-ceremony-performer |archive-date=5 May 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.directlyrics.com/brazils-anitta-releases-english-version-of-bang-and-the-usa-better-get-ready-for-it-news.html |title=Brazil's Anitta Releases English Version Of "BANG" And The USA Better Get Ready For It! [Listen] |last=Apaza |first=Kevin |date=6 June 2016 |access-date=6 August 2016 |publisher=Direct Lyrics |archive-date=10 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181110080401/https://directlyrics.com/brazils-anitta-releases-english-version-of-bang-and-the-usa-better-get-ready-for-it-news.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Other singles released from the album were "Essa Mina É Louca" and "Cravo e Canela".<ref name="auto1"/> In October 2015, the artist won the [[MTV Europe Music Awards|EMA Worldwide Act Latin America]], being the first Brazilian artist to win the award.<ref name="auto2"/> A collaboration with [[Jota Quest]] and [[Nile Rodgers]], entitled "Blecaute", was released in November 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://odia.ig.com.br/diversao/2016-04-14/jota-quest-comemora-20-anos-de-carreira-com-show-na-fundicao-progresso.html |title=Jota Quest comemora 20 anos de carreira com show na Fundição Progresso |first=O |last=Dia |date=13 April 2016 |access-date=9 July 2017 |archive-date=8 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180708220737/https://odia.ig.com.br/diversao/2016-04-14/jota-quest-comemora-20-anos-de-carreira-com-show-na-fundicao-progresso.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://extra.globo.com/tv-e-lazer/musica/blecaute-nova-musica-de-jota-quest-tera-participacao-de-anitta-nile-rodgers-17946815.html |title='Blecaute', nova música de Jota Quest, terá a participação de Anitta e Nile Rodgers |language=Portuguese |date=11 February 2015 |website=Extra Online |access-date=25 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151103231624/https://extra.globo.com/tv-e-lazer/musica/blecaute-nova-musica-de-jota-quest-tera-participacao-de-anitta-nile-rodgers-17946815.html |archive-date=3 November 2015}}</ref>

In 2016, Anitta made her debut as a TV hostess, hosting the third season of cable television channel [[Multishow]] show ''Música Boa Ao Vivo''(Good Music:Live).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ego.globo.com/show/noticia/2016/04/anitta-estreia-como-apresentadora-do-musica-boa-ao-vivo-no-multishow.html |title=Anitta estreia como apresentadora do 'Música Boa ao Vivo', no Multishow |access-date=31 December 2016 |archive-date=3 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180103133413/http://ego.globo.com/show/noticia/2016/04/anitta-estreia-como-apresentadora-do-musica-boa-ao-vivo-no-multishow.html |url-status=live }}</ref> The singer was also featured on a remix of the song "[[Ginza (song)|Ginza]]", by singer [[J Balvin]].<ref name="eonline"/> In August 2016, she released a single titled "[[Sim ou Não]]" featuring Colombian singer [[Maluma (singer)|Maluma]], and performed at the [[2016 Summer Olympics opening ceremony]] along with Brazilian singers and composers [[Caetano Veloso]] and [[Gilberto Gil]].<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Flores |first=Griselda |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/anitta-rio-olympics-opening-ceremony-interview-7460998/ |title=Anitta 'Never Imagined' She'd Be Performing at Rio Olympics Opening Ceremony |date=3 August 2016 |access-date=6 August 2016 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |archive-date=12 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190112115247/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7460998/anitta-rio-olympics-opening-ceremony-interview |url-status=live }}</ref> The next month, she signed her first international contract with [[talent agency]] [[William Morris Endeavor]].<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/anitta-signs-with-william-morris-endeavor/ |title=Anitta Signs With William Morris Endeavor |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=29 September 2016 |access-date=14 May 2017 |archive-date=9 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709094940/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7525957/anitta-signs-with-william-morris-endeavor |url-status=live }}</ref> In November 2016, she won the Best Brazilian Act category at the [[2016 MTV Europe Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ego.globo.com/famosos/noticia/2016/11/anitta-vence-o-europe-music-awards-2016-como-melhor-artista-brasileira.html |title=Anitta vence o Europe Music Awards 2016 como melhor artista brasileira |publisher=globo.com |date=November 2016 |access-date=31 December 2016 |archive-date=8 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180708192304/http://ego.globo.com/famosos/noticia/2016/11/anitta-vence-o-europe-music-awards-2016-como-melhor-artista-brasileira.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

Also in 2016, "Bang" was added to the annual video game series ''[[Just Dance 2017]]''. On 25 October 2016, [[Ubisoft|Ubisoft Brazil]] shot a flash mob in [[Paulista Avenue|Avenida Paulista]] ([[São Paulo]]), where many people danced to the routine of the game in order to promote the new instalment of the series. Ubisoft also promoted an exclusive pocket show with the singer for the release of the game. There, the singer sang and danced her track in game as demonstration. Meanwhile, she gave a lot of interviews, talking about her song was added the game soundtrack.<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 November 2016 |title=Just Dance 2017: Anitta fala sobre música e coreografia de 'Bang' |url=https://br.ign.com/just-dance-2017/41961/feature/just-dance-2017-anitta-fala-sobre-musica-e-coreografia-de-bang |access-date=13 July 2020 |website=IGN Brasil |language=pt-br |archive-date=15 July 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200715171226/https://br.ign.com/just-dance-2017/41961/feature/just-dance-2017-anitta-fala-sobre-musica-e-coreografia-de-bang |url-status=live }}</ref> and the song was selected for the digital qualifications of [[:it: Just Dance World Cup|2016 Just Dance World Championship]].

=== 2017–2018: ''Checkmate'', ''Solo'', international breakthrough and collaborations ===
[[File:Anitta Citibank Hall (37050520193).jpg|left|thumb|225x225px|Anitta performing at [[UnimedHall|Citibank Hall]] in São Paulo, October 2017]]
In January 2017, the singer was featured on singles including "[[Loka (song)|Loka]]", by female duo [[Simone & Simaria]], and featured on single "[[Você Partiu Meu Coração]]", recorded by [[Nego do Borel]] and featured [[Wesley Safadão]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Saiba por que o single 'Loka' beneficia tanto Anitta como Simone & Simaria |url=http://g1.globo.com/musica/blog/mauro-ferreira/post/saiba-porque-single-loka-beneficia-tanto-anitta-como-simone-simaria.html |work=[[G1 (website)|G1]] |date=6 January 2017 |access-date=22 May 2017 |language=pt |archive-date=28 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328005648/http://g1.globo.com/musica/blog/mauro-ferreira/post/saiba-porque-single-loka-beneficia-tanto-anitta-como-simone-simaria.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.itunes.apple.com/br/album/voc%C3%AA-partiu-meu-cora%C3%A7%C3%A3o-feat-anitta-wesley-safad%C3%A3o-single/id1193345107 |title=Nego do Borel - Você Partiu Meu Coração - Anitta - Wesley Safadão |work=[[iTunes Store]] |access-date=22 May 2017 |archive-date=28 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328010641/https://itunes.apple.com/br/album/voc%C3%AA-partiu-meu-cora%C3%A7%C3%A3o-feat-anitta-wesley-safad%C3%A3o-single/id1193345107 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In May 2017, "[[Switch (Iggy Azalea song)|Switch]]", a collaboration with Australian rapper [[Iggy Azalea]], became her first single in English to be released.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iggy Azalea Previews New Single 'Switch' Featuring Anitta: Watch |url=http://www.idolator.com/7661823/iggy-azalea-anitta-new-single-switch |work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |date=25 April 2017 |access-date=11 May 2017 |archive-date=26 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026184129/https://www.idolator.com/7661823/iggy-azalea-anitta-new-single-switch |url-status=dead }}</ref> The same month, she released a single in both Portuguese and Spanish titled "[[Paradinha (Anitta song)|Paradinha]]".<ref>{{cite web |title=Iggy Azalea Previews New Single 'Switch' Featuring Anitta: Watch |url=http://www.idolator.com/7663504/anitta-new-single-paradinha |work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |access-date=11 May 2017 |language=pt |archive-date=26 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026184133/https://www.idolator.com/7663504/anitta-new-single-paradinha |url-status=dead }}</ref> In June of the same year, the American group [[Major Lazer]] released "[[Sua Cara]]", along with Anitta and [[drag queen]] singer [[Pabllo Vittar]]. The song is part of the band's fourth EP, ''[[Know No Better (EP)|Know No Better]]''. In a few hours, the video exceeded the mark of 5 million views on YouTube.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://veja.abril.com.br/entretenimento/anitta-e-pabllo-vittar-sao-super-empoderadas-em-musica-sua-cara |title=Anitta e Pabllo Vittar são super empoderadas na música 'Sua Cara' |work=[[Revista Veja]] |access-date=11 June 2017 |language=en |archive-date=21 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181121093759/https://veja.abril.com.br/entretenimento/anitta-e-pabllo-vittar-sao-super-empoderadas-em-musica-sua-cara/ |url-status=live }}</ref> After its release, the song became an international hit, appearing as one hundred most played in Global Spotify,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://portalpopline.com.br/sua-cara-single-entra-no-top-100-spotify-mundial |title="Sua Cara": single entra no Top 100 do Spotify mundial |access-date=18 October 2017 |language=pt |work=portalpopline.com.br |date=7 August 2017 |archive-date=28 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328020343/http://portalpopline.com.br/sua-cara-single-entra-no-top-100-spotify-mundial/ |url-status=live }}</ref> and spent more than five weeks on Billboard's [[Dance/Electronic Songs]] chart, making it the first Portuguese-language song to feature on that chart.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://portalpopline.com.br/sua-cara-major-lazer-anitta-e-pabllo-vittar-seguem-no-top-40-de-parada-da-billboard/ |title="Sua Cara": Major Lazer, Anitta e Pabllo Vittar seguem no Top 40 de parada da Billboard |access-date=18 October 2017 |language=pt |work=portalpopline.com.br |date=6 September 2017 |archive-date=28 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328020508/http://portalpopline.com.br/sua-cara-major-lazer-anitta-e-pabllo-vittar-seguem-no-top-40-de-parada-da-billboard/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The music video was also a hit, reaching more than 20 million views in one day.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8039129/pabllo-vittar-interview-brazil-lgbtq-issues-coca-cola-campaign |title=Pabllo Vittar Interview on LGBTQ Issues in Brazil & More |date=16 November 2017 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=28 April 2020 |archive-date=18 June 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190618213801/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8039129/pabllo-vittar-interview-brazil-lgbtq-issues-coca-cola-campaign |url-status=live }}</ref>
[[File:COMBATCHY - Espaço das Américas (38495130706).jpg|thumb|Anitta at the 'Combatchy' party, November 2017]]
On 3 September, Anitta released the single "[[Will I See You]]", a collaboration with American producer and songwriter [[Poo Bear]].<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7950086/anitta-will-i-see-you-poo-bear |title=Anitta Celebrates Poo Bear's Birthday With New Single 'Will I See You' |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=4 September 2017 |access-date=8 September 2017 |language=en |archive-date=17 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417022249/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7950086/anitta-will-i-see-you-poo-bear |url-status=live }}</ref> It was the first song of the singer's project entitled ''CheckMate'', in which she would release a new song a month. On 13 October, in partnership with [[Swedish people|Swedish]] DJ [[Alesso]], Anitta released the second song from ''CheckMate'', titled "[[Is That for Me]]".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/musica/noticia/anitta-divulga-clipe-de-is-that-for-me-musica-em-parceria-com-alesso.ghtml |title=Anitta divulga clipe de 'Is that for me', música em parceria com Alesso |date=13 October 2017 |access-date=17 October 2017 |language=pt |archive-date=8 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180808104500/https://g1.globo.com/musica/noticia/anitta-divulga-clipe-de-is-that-for-me-musica-em-parceria-com-alesso.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> On 19 November, the singer released, in her second collaboration with [[J Balvin]], another track from the ''CheckMate'' project, "[[Downtown (Anitta and J Balvin song)|Downtown]]". The composition became an international success, entering in the "Top 50 Global", list of the 50 most executed songs in the world, making Anitta the first Brazilian to appear in the ranking.<ref>{{cite web |access-date=26 November 2017 |title=Anitta é a primeira brasileira a chegar ao top 50 global do Spotify, com a música 'Downtown' |date=25 November 2017 |url=https://f5.folha.uol.com.br/celebridades/2017/11/anitta-e-a-primeira-brasileira-a-chegar-ao-top-50-global-do-spotify-com-a-musica-downtown.shtml |language=pt |archive-date=16 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190116101817/https://f5.folha.uol.com.br/celebridades/2017/11/anitta-e-a-primeira-brasileira-a-chegar-ao-top-50-global-do-spotify-com-a-musica-downtown.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref> On 18 December 2017, Anitta released a new single, "[[Vai Malandra]]", featuring MC Zaac, [[Maejor]], [[Tropkillaz]] and DJ Yuri Martins; this was the fourth and last song from the ''CheckMate'' project.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://leodias.odia.ig.com.br/2017-12-18/vai-malandra-e-a-minha-grande-tacada-conta-anitta.html |title="Vai Malandra' é a minha grande tacada", conta Anitta |first=O |last=Dia |date=15 December 2017 |access-date=19 December 2017 |archive-date=22 December 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222051717/http://leodias.odia.ig.com.br/2017-12-18/vai-malandra-e-a-minha-grande-tacada-conta-anitta.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 1 January 2018, singer Anitta attracted over 2.4 million people to [[New Year's Eve in Copacabana|her concert]] in [[Copacabana, Rio de Janeiro|Copacabana]], [[Rio de Janeiro]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2018-01-01 |title=Anitta canta para 2,4 milhões de pessoas em Copacabana |url=https://www.ofuxico.com.br/galerias/anitta-canta-para-2-4-milhoes-de-pessoas-em-copacabana/ |access-date=2023-05-12 |website=OFuxico |language=pt-br |archive-date=12 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230512194833/https://www.ofuxico.com.br/galerias/anitta-canta-para-2-4-milhoes-de-pessoas-em-copacabana/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta coloca a multidão para rebolar em grande baile funk após virada em Copacabana |url=https://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2018/01/01/anitta-coloca-a-multidao-para-rebolar-em-grande-baile-funk-apos-virada-em-copacabana.htm |access-date=2023-05-12 |website=entretenimento.uol.com.br |date=January 2018 |language=pt-br |archive-date=12 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230512194831/https://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2018/01/01/anitta-coloca-a-multidao-para-rebolar-em-grande-baile-funk-apos-virada-em-copacabana.htm |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-01-01 |title=Réveillon de Copacabana leva público de 2,4 milhões de pessoas à praia |url=https://oglobo.globo.com/rio/reveillon-de-copacabana-leva-publico-de-24-milhoes-de-pessoas-praia-22244222 |access-date=2023-05-12 |website=O Globo |language=pt-BR |archive-date=12 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230512194830/https://oglobo.globo.com/rio/reveillon-de-copacabana-leva-publico-de-24-milhoes-de-pessoas-praia-22244222 |url-status=live }}</ref> In January, another collaboration with [[J Balvin]], "[[Machika]]", was released.<ref name="billboard.com">{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/j-balvin-anitta-jeon-machika-premiere-8095054/ |title=J Balvin, Anitta & Jeon Are War-Ready in 'Machika' Premiere: Watch |date=19 January 2018 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=28 April 2020 |archive-date=30 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210730022917/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8095054/j-balvin-anitta-jeon-machika-premiere |url-status=live }}</ref>

Two months later, she released another single in Spanish, titled "[[Indecente]]".<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/anitta-indecente-audio-premiere-8261888/ |title=Anitta Drops New Single 'Indecente': Listen |date=26 March 2018 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=28 April 2020 |archive-date=12 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210412233748/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8261888/anitta-indecente-audio-premiere |url-status=live }}</ref> In April, she debuted her new TV show on Multishow titled ''Anitta Entrou no Grupo''. In June, she performed at [[Rock in Rio]] festival in Lisbon.<ref name="billboard.com" /> She also made concerts in [[nightclubs]] in Paris and London as part of the Made in Brazil tour.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rfi.fr/br/franca/20180627-anitta-maior-artista-pop-brasileira-cantora-trianon-tremer-paris |title="Anitta é a maior artista pop brasileira atualmente": cantora faz Trianon tremer em Paris |date=26 June 2018 |website=Rfi.fr |access-date=28 April 2020 |archive-date=12 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210412133357/https://www.rfi.fr/br/franca/20180627-anitta-maior-artista-pop-brasileira-cantora-trianon-tremer-paris |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-radar/meet-anitta-brazilian-pop-megastar-music-world-underestimates-powerful-women-like-2349938 |title=Meet Anitta, the Brazilian pop megastar: 'the music world underestimates powerful women like me' {{pipe}} NME |website=[[NME]] |date=6 July 2018 |access-date=28 April 2020 |archive-date=18 September 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200918001543/https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-radar/meet-anitta-brazilian-pop-megastar-music-world-underestimates-powerful-women-like-2349938 |url-status=live }}</ref> The same month, she released a single titled "[[Medicina (Anitta song)|Medicina]]".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/07/best-new-songs-of-the-week-the-1975-anitta-ausdap-tyler.html |title=5 Best New Songs of the Week: The 1975, A$AP Rocky & Tyler the Creator, Anitta |date=26 July 2018 |website=Vulture.com |access-date=26 November 2018 |archive-date=31 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531104742/https://www.vulture.com/2018/07/best-new-songs-of-the-week-the-1975-anitta-ausdap-tyler.html |url-status=live }}</ref> "Medicina" featured her for the second time in the [[Just Dance (video game series)|''Just Dance'' series]] with two exclusive routines for the same track.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Just Dance 2019 – Just Dance Unlimited adiciona música "Medicina" de Anitta; Confira mais adições do mês de março |url=https://switch-brasil.com/just-dance-2019-just-dance-unlimited-adiciona-musica-medicina-de-anitta-confira-mais-adicoes-do-mes-de-marco/ |access-date=13 July 2020 |website=Switch Brasil |date=7 March 2019 |language=pt-BR |archive-date=13 July 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200713045235/https://switch-brasil.com/just-dance-2019-just-dance-unlimited-adiciona-musica-medicina-de-anitta-confira-mais-adicoes-do-mes-de-marco/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The latest one was presented at ''[[Just Dance 2019]]'' World Cup in Brasil.<ref>{{Cite web |date=31 March 2019 |title=Nova coreografia de Medicina, da Anitta, será lançado em Just Dance Unlimited |url=https://br.ign.com/just-dance-2019/72053/news/nova-coreografia-de-medicina-da-anitta-sera-lancado-em-just-dance-unlimited |access-date=13 July 2020 |website=IGN Brasil |language=pt-br |archive-date=7 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107225505/https://br.ign.com/just-dance-2019/72053/news/nova-coreografia-de-medicina-da-anitta-sera-lancado-em-just-dance-unlimited |url-status=live }}</ref> In September, she was featured on a single by production duo Seakret, "Perdendo a Mão", featuring Jojo Maronttinni.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.otvfoco.com.br/nova-musica-de-anitta-perdendo-a-mao-e-uma-indireta-para-o-ex-thiago-magalhaes/ |title=Nova música de Anitta, 'Perdendo a Mão', é uma indireta para o ex Thiago Magalhães |date=12 September 2018 |website=TV Foco |access-date=26 November 2018 |archive-date=27 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181127022408/https://www.otvfoco.com.br/nova-musica-de-anitta-perdendo-a-mao-e-uma-indireta-para-o-ex-thiago-magalhaes/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Later that same month, she debuted as one of the coaches on ''[[La Voz... México]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://laverdadnoticias.com/espectaculos/Ellos-son-los-nuevos-coaches-de-La-Voz-Mexico-20180520-0052.html |title=Ellos son los nuevos coaches de 'La Voz... México' |website=La Verdad Noticias |access-date=26 November 2018 |archive-date=27 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327090625/https://laverdadnoticias.com/espectaculos/Ellos-son-los-nuevos-coaches-de-La-Voz-Mexico-20180520-0052.html |url-status=live }}</ref> The next month, she was featured on Colombian singer [[Greeicy Rendón]]'s single "Jacuzzi".<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/greeicy-anitta-jacuzzi-video-8481658/ |title=Greeicy & Anitta's 'Jacuzzi' Video: Watch |date=25 October 2018 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=28 April 2020 |archive-date=4 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210304133439/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8481658/greeicy-anitta-jacuzzi-video |url-status=live }}</ref> In November, Anitta released a multilingual [[extended play]] (EP) titled ''Solo'', which has three songs in different languages, among them "[[Veneno (song)|Veneno]]" and "Não Perco Meu Tempo". Anitta also announced that all songs on the EP would have their respective music videos, which were released simultaneously on the same date as the EP and was the subject of a Shots Studios-produced docu-series titled ''[[Vai Anitta]]'', which aired on [[Netflix]].<ref name="instyle" /><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/anitta-ep-solo-videos-8484156/ |title=Anitta Releases Epic Tri-Lingual EP 'Solo': Watch |date=9 November 2018 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=28 April 2020 |archive-date=17 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210417160052/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8484156/anitta-ep-solo-videos |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="auto3">{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2018/digital/news/netflix-anitta-brazil-singer-series-1202871262/ |title=Netflix Orders Docu-Series on Anitta, Brazilian Music and Social Star, From Shots Studios (EXCLUSIVE) |last=Spangler |first=Todd |date=12 July 2018 |work=Variety |access-date=14 September 2018 |language=en-US |archive-date=14 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211114080726/https://variety.com/2018/digital/news/netflix-anitta-brazil-singer-series-1202871262/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/solo-as-curiosidades-por-tras-do-lancamento-triplo-da-anitta-e-clipes-de-goals-nao-perco-meu-tempo-e-veneno/ |title="Solo": as curiosidades por trás do lançamento triplo da Anitta e clipes de 'Goals", "Não Perco Meu Tempo" e "Veneno" |date=9 November 2018 |website=Portalpopline.com.br |language=pt-BR |access-date=29 March 2020 |archive-date=29 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329222853/https://portalpopline.com.br/solo-as-curiosidades-por-tras-do-lancamento-triplo-da-anitta-e-clipes-de-goals-nao-perco-meu-tempo-e-veneno/ |url-status=live }}</ref>
<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.midiaexclusiva.com/2022/10/anitta-envolver-2022-download.html |title=Anitta – Envolver 2022 |date=23 October 2022 |website=midiaexclusiva.com |access-date=23 October 2022 |archive-date=23 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221023100326/https://www.midiaexclusiva.com/2022/10/anitta-envolver-2022-download.html}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/anitta-performs-envolver-2022-mtv-vmas-1235132015/ |title=Anitta Performs global hit "envolver" & gives master class in twerking at the 2022 VMAs |last=Flores |first=October 28, 2022 |magazine=Billboard |access-date=May 4, 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220829024646/https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/anitta-performs-envolver-2022-mtv-vmas-1235132015/ |archive-date=August 29, 2022}}</ref>

=== 2019–2020: ''Kisses and Brasileirinha'' ===
[[File:Anitta-2019.png|thumb|225x225px|Anitta performing in [[Brasília]] in 2019]]
The year 2019, in Anitta's career, was marked by musical partnerships and participation in tracks by other singers.

In February 2019, the artist released five songs: "Terremoto" (whose music video is based on "[[I'm Still in Love with You (Sean Paul song)|I'm Still in Love with You]]" by [[Sean Paul]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/anitta-thank-u-next-cover-spotify-singles-8494691/ |title=Anitta's 'Thank U, Next' Cover: Listen |date=23 January 2019 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=28 April 2020 |archive-date=4 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210304125824/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8494691/anitta-thank-u-next-cover-spotify-singles |url-status=live }}</ref>) with [[Kevinho]]; "[[Bola Rebola]]" (single similar to "[[Vai Malandra]]") with Tropkillaz, [[J Balvin]] and MC Zaac; a re-recording of "Zé do Caroço" with producers Jetlag; "Te Lo Dije" with [[Natti Natasha]] and "Favela Chegou" with [[Ludmilla (singer)|Ludmilla]]. On 15 March, the song "[[R.I.P. (Sofía Reyes song)|R.I.P]]." Mexican [[Sofía Reyes]] with participation of Brazilian and British [[Rita Ora]].

On 5 April, the singer's fourth studio album, entitled ''[[Kisses (album)|Kisses]]'', was released. It was her first visual and trilingual album.<ref name="instyle" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2019/03/20/anitta-anuncia-kisses-album-trilingue-com-dez-musicas-para-5-de-abril.htm |title=Anitta anuncia "Kisses", álbum trilingue com dez músicas, para 5 de abril |website=Entretenimento |language=pt-br |access-date=29 March 2020 |archive-date=1 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101101458/https://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2019/03/20/anitta-anuncia-kisses-album-trilingue-com-dez-musicas-para-5-de-abril.htm |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Citation |title=Kisses by Anitta |date=5 April 2019 |url=https://music.apple.com/nz/album/kisses/1458018493 |language=en-au |access-date=29 March 2020 |archive-date=9 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210209154413/https://music.apple.com/nz/album/kisses/1458018493 |url-status=live }}</ref> In the [[United States]], the album reached the fourth position on the [[Latin Pop Albums]] and number 16 on the [[Top Latin Albums]] charts.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/anitta/chart-history/lpp/ |title=Anitta |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=29 March 2020 |archive-date=8 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220408111054/https://www.billboard.com/artist/anitta/chart-history/lpp/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/anitta/chart-history/lcm/ |title=Anitta |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=29 March 2020 |archive-date=9 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220409145042/https://www.billboard.com/artist/anitta/chart-history/lcm/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In [[Spain]], the album reached forty-sixth position on the [[PROMUSICAE]] list. The album's lead single, "Poquito", with American rapper [[Swae Lee]], was released in conjunction with the album.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thehypestuff.com/musica/anitta-e-swae-lee-liberam-single-pouquito/ |title=Anitta e Swae Lee liberam single "Poquito" |last=Maia |first=Simony |date=5 April 2019 |website=The Hype Stuff |language=pt-BR |access-date=29 March 2020 |archive-date=29 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329222908/https://www.thehypestuff.com/musica/anitta-e-swae-lee-liberam-single-pouquito/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

Anitta is present in the soundtrack of the film [[UglyDolls]] that was released in April of the same year. The singer appears on the track "Ugly" which was recorded in three languages: English, Spanish and Portuguese.<ref>{{Citation |title=UglyDolls (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) por Vários intérpretes |date=26 April 2019 |url=https://music.apple.com/br/album/uglydolls-original-motion-picture-soundtrack/1457278808 |language=pt-br |access-date=29 March 2020 |archive-date=30 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130124900/https://music.apple.com/br/album/uglydolls-original-motion-picture-soundtrack/1457278808 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 14 June [[Madonna]] launches [[Madame X (album)|Madame X]], where Anitta participates in the track "[[Faz Gostoso (Madonna song)|''Faz Gostoso''"]], a re-recording by Portuguese singer [[Blaya]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/blog/mauro-ferreira/post/2019/04/17/anitta-canta-no-album-de-madonna-um-funk-portugues-lancado-em-2018-na-voz-da-cantora-luso-brasileira-blaya.ghtml |title=Anitta canta no álbum de Madonna um funk português lançado em 2018 na voz da cantora luso-brasileira Blaya |website=G1.globo.com |date=17 April 2019 |language=pt-br |access-date=29 March 2020 |archive-date=27 September 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927114439/https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/blog/mauro-ferreira/post/2019/04/17/anitta-canta-no-album-de-madonna-um-funk-portugues-lancado-em-2018-na-voz-da-cantora-luso-brasileira-blaya.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref>

Anitta again partnered with [[Major Lazer]], - the first in 2017 on the song "[[Sua Cara]]" - this time on "[[Make It Hot (Major Lazer and Anitta song)|Make It Hot"]], a track released on 19 June and featured on the group's ''Music Is the Weapon'' album.<ref>{{Citation |title=Make It Hot - Single por Major Lazer & Anitta |date=19 June 2019 |url=https://music.apple.com/br/album/make-it-hot-single/1466720570 |language=pt-br |access-date=29 March 2020 |archive-date=30 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330003956/https://music.apple.com/br/album/make-it-hot-single/1466720570 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 21 June, the song "Pa 'lante" was released along with Alex Sensation and [[Luis Fonsi]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-esta-no-top-10-do-itunes-em-cinco-paises-com-tres-musicas-diferentes/ |title=Anitta está no Top 10 do iTunes em cinco países, com três músicas diferentes |last=Torres |first=Leonardo |date=21 June 2019 |website=Portalpopline.com.br |language=pt-BR |access-date=29 March 2020 |archive-date=26 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026184821/https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-esta-no-top-10-do-itunes-em-cinco-paises-com-tres-musicas-diferentes/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 11 July, "[[Muito Calor]]" was launched, a partnership between Anitta and the singer [[Ozuna (singer)|Ozuna]]. The song was part of the singer's third studio album, entitled ''[[Nibiru (album)|Nibiru]]'', but was removed for reasons that have not been clarified. On 6 September, the partnership between Anitta and Léo Santana, "Contatinho", was launched. The song was recorded live, as the opening song of Léo Santana's DVD, called ''Levada do Gigante''. Still in September, on the 30th, together with the group [[The Black Eyed Peas|Black Eyed Peas]], they released the single "Explosion". In the same month, Anitta signed with [[Skol|Skol Beats]] to become the brand's head of creativity and innovation.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Assinatura |first=Sem |date=2019-09-30 |title=Anitta se torna head de criatividade e inovação da Skol Beats |url=https://www.meioemensagem.com.br/marketing/anitta-se-torna-head-de-criatividade-e-inovacao-da-skol-beats |access-date=2023-01-12 |website=Meio e Mensagem - Marketing, Mídia e Comunicação |language=pt-BR |archive-date=12 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230112155717/https://www.meioemensagem.com.br/marketing/anitta-se-torna-head-de-criatividade-e-inovacao-da-skol-beats |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 4 October, she collaborated with the singer Vitão, "Complicado".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://jornaldebrasilia.com.br/clica-brasilia/musica/complicado-novo-single-de-vitao-conta-com-a-participacao-de-anitta/ |title="Complicado", novo single de Vitão, conta com a participação de Anitta |last=Brasília |first=Redação Jornal de |date=4 October 2019 |website=Jornaldebrasilia.com.br |language=pt-BR |access-date=29 March 2020 |archive-date=14 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200114234114/https://jornaldebrasilia.com.br/clica-brasilia/musica/complicado-novo-single-de-vitao-conta-com-a-participacao-de-anitta/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Anitta recorded the song "Pantera" for the soundtrack to the movie [[Charlie's Angels (2019 film)|Charlie's Angels]], released in October, the executive production of the soundtrack was written by [[Ariana Grande]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://veja.abril.com.br/entretenimento/anitta-lanca-musica-para-a-adaptacao-de-as-panteras/ |title=Anitta lança música para a adaptação de 'As Panteras' |website=Veja.abril.com.br |date=11 October 2019 |language=pt-BR |access-date=29 March 2020 |archive-date=29 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329222853/https://veja.abril.com.br/entretenimento/anitta-lanca-musica-para-a-adaptacao-de-as-panteras/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-10-11 |title=Produzida por Ariana Grande, trilha sonora do filme "As Panteras" tem música de Anitta e participações de Normani e Nicki Minaj |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/produzida-por-ariana-grande-trilha-sonora-do-filme-as-panteras-tem-musica-de-anitta-e-participacoes-de-normani-e-nicki-minaj/ |access-date=2022-12-29 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=29 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221229212833/https://portalpopline.com.br/produzida-por-ariana-grande-trilha-sonora-do-filme-as-panteras-tem-musica-de-anitta-e-participacoes-de-normani-e-nicki-minaj/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In the same month, the artist started the Brasileirinha project, which had released songs in Portuguese only until December. The first single released was the song "Some Que Ele Vem Atrás" in partnership with the singer [[Marília Mendonça]], the music video was recorded live during the 26th edition of the Brazilian Music Multishow Award. "Combatchy" was released in November as a second single, the song features singers [[Lexa (singer)|Lexa]], [[Luísa Sonza]] and MC Rebecca. On 23 November, she participated in the opening show of the [[Copa Libertadores|Copa Libertadores de América]] Final that took place in [[Peru]] alongside Colombian singer [[Sebastián Yatra|Sebástian Yatra]] and Argentine singers [[Fito Páez]] and [[Tini (singer)|Tini]], performing the song "Y Dale Alegría A Mi Corazón". The third single from the Brasileirinha project, "Meu Mel", in partnership with the trio [[Melim]], was released on 13 December; "Até o Céu", a duet with [[MC Cabelinho]] and the last track of the project, was made available on 20 December.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/blog/mauro-ferreira/post/2019/12/20/anitta-chega-ate-o-ceu-com-mc-cabelinho-no-quarto-single-do-projeto-brasileirinha.ghtml |title=Anitta chega 'até o céu' com MC Cabelinho no quarto single do projeto 'Brasileirinha' |website=G1.globo.com |date=20 December 2019 |language=pt-br |access-date=29 March 2020 |archive-date=3 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103213725/https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/blog/mauro-ferreira/post/2019/12/20/anitta-chega-ate-o-ceu-com-mc-cabelinho-no-quarto-single-do-projeto-brasileirinha.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref>

In June 2020, Anitta signed a recording contract with [[Warner Records]]<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=18 June 2020 |title=Anitta Signs With Warner Records, Will Soon Launch US Debut Album |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/international/9405316/anitta-signs-warner-records-announcement |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |access-date=18 September 2020 |archive-date=3 July 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200703143404/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/international/9405316/anitta-signs-warner-records-announcement |url-status=live }}</ref> in the U.S., ahead of her U.S. debut album expected to release later in 2020. The album will be executive produced by [[Ryan Tedder]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Exposito |first=Suzy |date=18 June 2020 |title=Brazilian Pop Star Anitta Announces New Deal With Warner Music |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-latin/anitta-warner-music-2020-album-ryan-tedder-1017183/ |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |language=en-US |access-date=20 June 2020 |archive-date=24 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230224192544/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-latin/anitta-warner-music-2020-album-ryan-tedder-1017183/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In August 2020, Anitta released her first single in [[Italy]] with [[Fred De Palma|Fred de Palma]], "Paloma" which became one of the most shazamed songs of the month in the country, and becoming the song by a Brazilian artist in the highest position on the Italian charts.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-08-16 |title=Anitta é a mais nova estrela da Itália: "Paloma" alcança novo pico no Spotify |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-estrela-italia-paloma-alcanca-novo-pico-spotify/ |access-date=2022-12-29 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=29 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221229212829/https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-estrela-italia-paloma-alcanca-novo-pico-spotify/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In August 2020 she was also featured on WC No Beat's album on a track called "Cena de Novela" alongside [[Djonga]] & PK and also featured on the trap song "Tá Com o Papato" of Papatinho with Dfideliz & BIN.<ref>{{Cite web |title=TOP 10 ITALYA - Shazam |url=https://www.shazam.com/charts/top-200/italy |website=Top Shazam Italy |access-date=19 August 2020 |archive-date=12 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112034654/https://www.shazam.com/charts/top-200/italy |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 18 September 2020, Anitta began a new phase in her international career, releasing "[[Me Gusta (Anitta song)|Me Gusta]]" in collaboration with [[Cardi B]] and [[Myke Towers]]. The song reached the 14th position on the [[iTunes]] chart in the [[United States]] and 32 on [[Spotify]] United States.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-09-18 |title=Anitta entra pela primeira vez no Top 20 do iTunes nos Estados Unidos |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-top-20-itunes-estados-unidos/ |access-date=2023-02-23 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=28 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201028180240/https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-top-20-itunes-estados-unidos/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-09-19 |title=Anitta no Mundo: "Me Gusta" estreia com mais de 2 milhões de plays no Spotify e surprende nos EUA |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-no-mundo-me-gusta-estreia-com-mais-de-2-milhoes-de-plays-no-spotify-e-surprende-nos-eua/ |access-date=2023-02-23 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=23 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230223172009/https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-no-mundo-me-gusta-estreia-com-mais-de-2-milhoes-de-plays-no-spotify-e-surprende-nos-eua/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Additionally, the song debuted with over 2 million plays in the top 200 in 38 countries on Spotify and 87 countries on [[Apple Music]], as well as on the global charts of both platforms at 24 and 90, respectively.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.metropoles.com/entretenimento/musica/anitta-bate-justin-bieber-e-lady-gaga-com-me-gusta-em-parceria-com-cardi-b |date=2020-09-19 |title=Anitta bate Justin Bieber e Lady Gaga com Me Gusta, em parceria com Cardi B |website=Metrópoles |access-date=2023-02-23 |language=pt-BR |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026184137/https://www.metropoles.com/entretenimento/musica/anitta-bate-justin-bieber-e-lady-gaga-com-me-gusta-em-parceria-com-cardi-b |archive-date=26 October 2023}}</ref> Furthermore, the song debuted on various [[Billboard charts]]. "Me Gusta" became Anitta's first entry on the [[Billboard Hot 100]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-09-28 |title=Com o hit 'Me Gusta', Anitta é a oitava brasileira a entrar na Billboard Hot 100 |url=https://istoe.com.br/com-o-hit-me-gusta-anitta-e-a-oitava-brasileira-a-entrar-na-billboard-hot-100/ |access-date=2022-12-29 |website=ISTOÉ Independente |language=pt-br |archive-date=29 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221229212829/https://istoe.com.br/com-o-hit-me-gusta-anitta-e-a-oitava-brasileira-a-entrar-na-billboard-hot-100/}}</ref>  In September 2020, Anitta questioned [[Google]] about the meaning of the [[word]] "Patroa" in [[Brazilian Portuguese|Portuguese]], as following Google's previous definition the word meant that "Patrão" ([[Masculine]]) was the owner or boss, while the word "Patroa" ([[Femininity|Feminine]]) was defined as the boss's wife. The singer thus managed to get the [[University of Oxford]] to change the definition of the word in the [[dictionary]] and how it was displayed in [[Google Search|Google searches]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-09-18 |title=Anitta pressiona, dicionário obedece e altera definição de "patroa" |url=https://exame.com/tecnologia/anitta-pressiona-google-obedece-e-muda-definicao-de-patroa/ |access-date=2023-01-31 |website=Exame |language=pt-br |archive-date=31 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230131182952/https://exame.com/tecnologia/anitta-pressiona-google-obedece-e-muda-definicao-de-patroa/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== 2021–2022: ''Versions of Me'' and worldwide recognition and success ===
In March 2021, Anitta and [[Maluma]] were part of the Remix of "Mi Niña" with [[Wisin]], [[Myke Towers]] and [[Los Legendarios]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-03-04 |title=Anitta e Maluma estão no remix de "Mi Niña" {{!}} Acesso Cultural |url=https://acessocultural.com.br/2021/03/anitta-e-maluma-estao-no-remix-de-mi-nina/ |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=acessocultural.com.br |language=pt-BR |archive-date=16 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416145059/https://acessocultural.com.br/2021/03/anitta-e-maluma-estao-no-remix-de-mi-nina/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 14 April 2021, Anitta joined [[Wisin]], [[Maluma]] and [[Myke Towers]] and opened the [[Latin American Music Awards of 2021|Latin American Music Awards]] with the remix of "Mi Niña".<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Rouhani |first=Neena |date=2021-04-16 |title=Wisin & Myke Towers Open the 2021 Latin AMAs With Anitta & Maluma |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/2021-latin-amas-wisin-myke-towers-anitta-maluma-9557180/ |access-date=2023-01-15 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=15 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230115215529/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/2021-latin-amas-wisin-myke-towers-anitta-maluma-9557180/ |url-status=live }}</ref>  In May, the [[Latin Grammy Award records|Latin Grammy]] organized the event "Ellas y su Musica", which seeks to honor women in the world of Latin music, Anitta performed "[[Girl from Rio (song)|Girl from Rio]]".<ref>{{Cite web |title=LATIN GRAMMY CELEBRA ELLAS Y SU MÚSICA FIRST EVER TWO-HOUR SPECIAL TO AIR SUNDAY, MAY 9 AT 8P/7C ON UNIVISION |url=https://www.latingrammy.com/en/recording-academy/press-release/latin-grammy-celebra-ellas-y-su-m-sica-first-ever-two-hour-special |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=Latin GRAMMYs |language=en |archive-date=15 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230115215528/https://www.latingrammy.com/en/recording-academy/press-release/latin-grammy-celebra-ellas-y-su-m-sica-first-ever-two-hour-special |url-status=dead }}</ref> In May, Anitta together with Puerto Rican singer and rapper [[Lunay (singer)|Lunay]] released the song "Todo o Nada". The song entered the top 100 of all [[Latin America|Latin American countries]] and [[Spain]], top 50 in 5 countries, having several highlights on the [[Billboard charts]] as well.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-08-03 |title=Lunay e Anitta escalam paradas da Billboard |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/lunay-anitta-escalam-paradas-billboard/ |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=15 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230115215518/https://portalpopline.com.br/lunay-anitta-escalam-paradas-billboard/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.metropoles.com/entretenimento/musica/confira-os-numeros-da-carreira-internacional-de-anitta |date=2021-07-08 |title=Radiografia! Veja os números da carreira internacional de Anitta |website=Metrópoles |access-date=2023-01-15 |language=pt-BR |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220129093754/https://www.metropoles.com/entretenimento/musica/confira-os-numeros-da-carreira-internacional-de-anitta |archive-date=29 January 2022}}</ref>

In June 2021, Anitta released her first single in [[France]] with [[Dadju]], "Mon Soleil", The song became one of the most heard songs on the [[French language|French-speaking]] charts, becoming the highest position by a Brazilian artist. The song earned Anitta two nominations in the main categories at the [[NRJ Music Award]]s.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-07-24 |title=Anitta faz história e entra no top 10 músicas mais ouvidas da França |url=https://oglobo.globo.com/ela/gente/anitta-faz-historia-entra-no-top-10-musicas-mais-ouvidas-da-franca-25124874 |access-date=2022-12-29 |website=O Globo |language=pt-BR |archive-date=29 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221229212830/https://oglobo.globo.com/ela/gente/anitta-faz-historia-entra-no-top-10-musicas-mais-ouvidas-da-franca-25124874 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-10-11 |title=NRJ Music Awards 2021 : les nommés dans chaque catégorie, à découvrir - NRJ Music Awards {{!}} TF1 |url=https://www.tf1.fr/tf1/nrj-music-awards/news/nrj-music-awards-2021-les-nommes-dans-chaque-categorie-a-decouvrir-83256593.html |access-date=2022-12-29 |website=MYTF1 |language=fr |archive-date=29 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221229212827/https://www.tf1.fr/tf1/nrj-music-awards/news/nrj-music-awards-2021-les-nommes-dans-chaque-categorie-a-decouvrir-83256593.html |url-status=live }}</ref> In June 2021, Anitta released her second single in [[Italian language|Italian]] with [[Fred De Palma|Fred de Palma]], "Un Altro Ballo". The partnership became one of the most heard songs on the Italian charts, just not surpassing the success of its first single in the country.<ref>{{Cite web |last=lanaitalia |date=2021-09-30 |title=As músicas italianas mais tocadas no verão de 2021 |url=https://lanaitalia.com.br/musicas-italianas-mais-tocadas-no-verao-de-2021/ |access-date=2022-12-29 |website=Lá na Itália |language=pt-BR |archive-date=29 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221229212832/https://lanaitalia.com.br/musicas-italianas-mais-tocadas-no-verao-de-2021/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Dias |first=Surenã |date=2021-07-29 |title=Anitta está no 'Top 10' das mais tocadas do Spotify francês |url=https://mixme.com.br/anitta-esta-no-top-10-das-mais-tocadas-do-spotify-frances/ |access-date=2022-12-29 |website=MIX ME |language=pt-BR |archive-date=29 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221229212832/https://mixme.com.br/anitta-esta-no-top-10-das-mais-tocadas-do-spotify-frances/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Also in June 2021, the singer joined the board of directors of startup [[Nubank]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Nubank |first=Redação |date=2021-06-21 |title=Anitta é a nova membro do conselho do Nubank |url=https://blog.nubank.com.br/anitta-nubank-membro-conselho/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=Fala, Nubank |language=pt-br |archive-date=10 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230410183123/https://blog.nubank.com.br/anitta-nubank-membro-conselho/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In July 2021, in addition to performing and winning some awards at the [[Heat Latin Music Awards]], Anitta was honored with a special recognition award for her contribution to female empowerment.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Roiz |first=Jessica |date=2021-07-02 |title=Anitta, Karol G, CNCO & More Win Big at Heat Latin Music Awards 2021: Full List |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/heat-latin-music-awards-2021-winners-list-9596160/ |access-date=2023-01-15 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=14 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221114183319/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/heat-latin-music-awards-2021-winners-list-9596160/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Diario |first=El Nuevo |date=2021-07-02 |title=Así se vivió la sexta edición de los Heat Latin Music Awards en Playa Juanillo |url=https://elnuevodiario.com.do/asi-se-vivio-la-sexta-edicion-de-los-heat-latin-music-awards-en-playa-juanillo/ |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=El Nuevo Diario (República Dominicana) |language=es |archive-date=15 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230115215520/https://elnuevodiario.com.do/asi-se-vivio-la-sexta-edicion-de-los-heat-latin-music-awards-en-playa-juanillo/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Anitta and [[Lunay (singer)|Lunay]] performed "Todo o Nada" on 22 July, at [[Premios Juventud]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-07-23 |title=Sem beijo! Anitta e Lunay cantam no Premios Juventud |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/sem-beijo-anitta-lunay-cantam-premios-juventud/ |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=15 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230115215523/https://portalpopline.com.br/sem-beijo-anitta-lunay-cantam-premios-juventud/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 11 September, Anitta performed several songs at the [[Triller Fight Club]] in [[Florida]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Chan |first=Tim |date=2021-09-11 |title=Snoop Dogg, Anitta to Perform at Triller Fight Club Tonight: Here's How to Watch the PPV Event Online |url=https://www.billboard.com/culture/product-recommendations/triller-fight-club-september-2021-watch-online-free-9628044/ |access-date=2023-01-15 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=15 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230115215519/https://www.billboard.com/culture/product-recommendations/triller-fight-club-september-2021-watch-online-free-9628044/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In partnership with [[Burger King]], Anitta performed "[[Girl from Rio (song)|Girl from Rio]]" at the [[2021 MTV Video Music Awards|MTV Video Music Awards]] on 12 September, in addition to winning her own commercial for her vegan hamburger in her name, which was widely publicized on [[American TV]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=VMA: Anitta faz apresentação patrocinada pelo BK |url=https://www.bpmoney.com.br/noticias/negocios/vma-anitta-faz-apresentacao-patrocinada-pelo-bk |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=VMA: Anitta faz apresentação patrocinada pelo BK |date=13 September 2021 |language=pt-BR |archive-date=15 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230115221029/https://www.bpmoney.com.br/noticias/negocios/vma-anitta-faz-apresentacao-patrocinada-pelo-bk |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta vira estrela do Burger King nos EUA como Larissa |url=https://observatoriodatv.uol.com.br/colunas/edianez-parente/anitta-vira-estrela-do-burger-king-eua-e-batiza-combo-como-larissa-machado |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=observatoriodatv.uol.com.br |date=13 September 2021 |language=pt-BR |archive-date=15 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230115215522/https://observatoriodatv.uol.com.br/colunas/edianez-parente/anitta-vira-estrela-do-burger-king-eua-e-batiza-combo-como-larissa-machado |url-status=live }}</ref> Anitta appeared, for the first time, at the [[Met Gala|Met Gala 2021]], in September alongside Brazilian entrepreneur in the footwear sector [[Alexandre Birman]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta participa do Met Gala 2021 |url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/noticia/2021/09/13/anitta-participa-do-met-gala-2021.ghtml |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=G1 |date=13 September 2021 |language=pt-br |archive-date=15 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230115215524/https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/noticia/2021/09/13/anitta-participa-do-met-gala-2021.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 18 October 2021, Anitta joined [[Billie Eilish]], [[Blackpink|BlackPink]], [[Barack Obama]], [[Pope Francis]]co, [[Jaden Smith]] and others for the [[YouTube Originals]] special that aims to raise awareness about climate change on the planet, ''Dear Earth''. The singer performed her single "[[Girl from Rio (song)|Girl from Rio]]".<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Mamo |first=Heran |date=2021-10-18 |title=Watch Billie Eilish, BLACKPINK, Anitta, Lil Dicky & More in 'Dear Earth' YouTube Originals Trailer |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/dear-earth-youtube-originals-trailer-billie-eilish-blackpink-anitta-lil-dicky-9646937/ |access-date=2023-01-12 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=12 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230112155737/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/dear-earth-youtube-originals-trailer-billie-eilish-blackpink-anitta-lil-dicky-9646937/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-10-24 |title=Anitta e BLACKPINK fazem performances exclusivas no "Dear Earth" |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-blackpink-performances-exclusivas-dear-earth/ |access-date=2023-01-12 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=12 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230112155723/https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-blackpink-performances-exclusivas-dear-earth/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In September, alongside [[Charli XCX]], Anitta joined as a mentor in the singing competition held by [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] and [[Samsung Galaxy]], Billboard NXT.<ref>{{Cite magazine |author=Billboard Staff |date=2021-10-18 |title=Billboard and Samsung Galaxy Announce Anitta as Next Billboard NXT Celebrity Mentor |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/billboard-nxt-samsung-galaxy-anitta-mentor-9646622/ |access-date=2023-01-15 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=15 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230115215522/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/billboard-nxt-samsung-galaxy-anitta-mentor-9646622/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 14 November, Anitta made a surprise appearance at the [[2021 MTV Europe Music Awards|MTV Europe Music Awards]], talking to host [[Saweetie]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-11-14 |title=MTV EMA 2021: veja a participação de Anitta na premiação |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/mtv-ema-2021-veja-a-participacao-de-anitta-na-premiacao/ |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=15 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230115224034/https://portalpopline.com.br/mtv-ema-2021-veja-a-participacao-de-anitta-na-premiacao/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In November 2021, Anitta performed the opening performance of the [[22nd Annual Latin Grammy Awards|Latin Grammy]] alongside [[Gloria Estefan]] and [[Carlinhos Brown]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Garcia |first=Thania |date=2021-11-19 |title=Gloria Estefan, Anitta & More Kick Off 2021 Latin Grammys With Epic Opening Medley |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/gloria-estefan-anitta-2021-latin-grammys-opening-medley-1234999874/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231193526/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/gloria-estefan-anitta-2021-latin-grammys-opening-medley-1234999874/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Alongside [[Jeremy Scott]] and dressed as [[Moschino]], Anitta attended the [[amfAR gala|amfAR benefit gala]] in November.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Com look Moschino, Anitta participa do amfAR Gala Los Angeles 2021 |url=https://vogue.globo.com/moda/noticia/2021/11/com-look-moschino-anitta-participa-do-amfar-gala-los-angeles-2021.html |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=Vogue |date=23 September 2022 |language=pt-br |archive-date=3 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230203125453/https://vogue.globo.com/moda/noticia/2021/11/com-look-moschino-anitta-participa-do-amfar-gala-los-angeles-2021.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

Anitta was one of the guests at the [[Community Organized Relief Effort|Community Organized Relief Effort (CORE)]] charity event, created by actor [[Sean Penn]], in addition to performing some songs, she also auctioned off an experience with her at her shows at the [[Brazilian Carnival]], where the winning bid was 110,000 dollars.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta participa de evento beneficente de Sean Penn e leiloa experiência no carnaval por US$ 110 mil |url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/noticia/2021/12/02/anitta-leiloa-experiencia-no-carnaval-por-us-110-mil-em-evento-beneficente-do-astro-sean-penn.ghtml |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=G1 |date=2 December 2021 |language=pt-br |archive-date=15 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230115215521/https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/noticia/2021/12/02/anitta-leiloa-experiencia-no-carnaval-por-us-110-mil-em-evento-beneficente-do-astro-sean-penn.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 9 December, alongside [[Pedro Sampaio]], she participated in the single "No Chão Novinha". The song debuted in the top 10 on the Brazilian chart, Top 30 on the Portuguese chart and Top 170 on the Global charts.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-12-11 |title=Pedro Sampaio e Anitta estreiam "No Chão Novinha" direto no Top 10 do Spotify Brasil |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/pedro-sampaio-e-anitta-estreiam-no-chao-novinha-direto-no-top-10-do-spotify-brasil/ |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=15 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230115215518/https://portalpopline.com.br/pedro-sampaio-e-anitta-estreiam-no-chao-novinha-direto-no-top-10-do-spotify-brasil/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In December, Anitta attended the Variety 2021 Music Hitmakers Brunch and handed the Crossover Award to [[Kali Uchis]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Littleton |first=Cynthia |date=2021-12-05 |title=Variety's Hitmakers Brunch Unites Music Industry Insiders to Celebrate the Soundtrack of 2021: 'We Dreamed of Moments Like This' |url=https://variety.com/2021/music/news/lil-nas-x-jack-harlow-bts-olivia-rodrigo-hitmakers-variety-1235126496/ |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=8 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230208211724/https://variety.com/2021/music/news/lil-nas-x-jack-harlow-bts-olivia-rodrigo-hitmakers-variety-1235126496/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Anitta, [[Saweetie]], [[Jack Harlow]] and [[24kGoldn]] were some of the performers at [[Miley's New Year's Eve Party]], hosted by [[Miley Cyrus]] and [[Pete Davidson]], on 31 December 2021.<ref>{{Cite magazine |author=Billboard Staff |date=2021-12-21 |title=Brandi Carlile, Billie Joe Armstrong And More Set to Perform at 'Miley's New Year's Eve Party' |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/brandi-carlile-billie-joe-armstrong-perform-nbc-mileys-new-years-eve-party-1235012721/ |access-date=2023-01-15 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=1 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230201004331/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/brandi-carlile-billie-joe-armstrong-perform-nbc-mileys-new-years-eve-party-1235012721/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Anitta was part of the soundtrack of ''[[Fast and Furious 9]]'' with the song "Furiosa" and ''[[Sing 2]]'', with the song "Suéltate" featuring Sam i, [[Bia (rapper)|BIA]] & Jarina De Marco.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Here's the Star-Studded 'F9' Soundtrack Tracklist f/ ASAP Rocky, Jack Harlow, Pop Smoke, and More |url=https://www.complex.com/music/f9-soundtrack-tracklist |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=Complex |language=en |archive-date=14 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211214010749/https://www.complex.com/music/f9-soundtrack-tracklist |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2021-11-19 |title=Anitta participa de música do filme 'Sing 2' com Sam i, BIA e Jarina |url=http://entretenimento.r7.com/cinema-e-series/anitta-participa-de-musica-do-filme-sing-2-com-sam-i-bia-e-jarina-19112021 |access-date=2023-01-15 |website=R7.com |language=pt-br |archive-date=16 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230116000807/https://entretenimento.r7.com/cinema-e-series/anitta-participa-de-musica-do-filme-sing-2-com-sam-i-bia-e-jarina-19112021 |url-status=live }}</ref>
[[File:Anitta no Rock in Rio 2022 3.jpg|left|thumb|225x225px|Anitta performing at [[Rock in Rio]] 2019]]
On 3 January 2022, it was announced that Anitta had signed a worldwide publishing agreement with [[Sony Music Publishing]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sony Music Publishing Signs Global Pop Superstar Anitta to Global Deal|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/sony-music-publishing-signs-global-pop-superstar-anitta-to-global-deal-301452736.html|date=3 January 2022|access-date=3 January 2022|website=PR Newswire|archive-date=28 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221128050123/https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/sony-music-publishing-signs-global-pop-superstar-anitta-to-global-deal-301452736.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=4 January 2022|title=Sony Music Publishing signs global deal with Brazilian pop star Anitta|url=https://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/sony-music-publishing-signs-global-deal-with-brazilian-pop-star-anitta/|access-date=4 January 2022|website=Music Business Worldwide|language=en-US|archive-date=27 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230327100730/https://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/sony-music-publishing-signs-global-deal-with-brazilian-pop-star-anitta/|url-status=live}}</ref> Her Spanish single "[[Envolver]]" released by late 2021, topped the Global Top 200 on [[Spotify]] in March 2022, making Anitta the first Brazilian artist and the first Latin artist with a solo song to do so.<ref>{{cite web|title=First solo Latin artist to reach No.1 on Spotify|url=https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/697212-first-solo-latin-artist-to-reach-no-1-on-spotify|website=[[Guinness World Records]]|date=24 March 2022 |access-date=6 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220712125206/https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/697212-first-solo-latin-artist-to-reach-no-1-on-spotify |archive-date=12 July 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=25 March 2022 |title=Anitta Becomes First Brazilian Artist to Hit No. 1 on Spotify |url=https://www.bloomberglinea.com/2022/03/25/anitta-becomes-first-brazilian-artist-to-hit-no-1-on-spotify/ |access-date=27 March 2022 |website=Bloomberg Línea |language=en-US |archive-date=27 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327101154/https://www.bloomberglinea.com/2022/03/25/anitta-becomes-first-brazilian-artist-to-hit-no-1-on-spotify/ |url-status=live }}</ref> It also become the most streamed song in a single-day in 2022 (7.278 million) at the time.<ref>{{Cite web |last=M |first=Talia |date=2022-03-27 |title=Anitta's 'Envolver' Has The Highest Single Day Streams Of Any Song In 2022 - |url=https://whereisthebuzz.com/anittas-envolver-has-the-highest-single-day-streams-of-any-song-in-2022/ |access-date=2022-12-29 |website=whereisthebuzz.com |language=en-US |archive-date=29 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221229212836/https://whereisthebuzz.com/anittas-envolver-has-the-highest-single-day-streams-of-any-song-in-2022/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Anitta still reached the top on [[Deezer|Deezer Global]] and [[YouTube|YouTube Global]].<ref>{{Cite web |title='Envolver', de Anitta, também é número 1 mundial na plataforma Deezer |url=https://br.noticias.yahoo.com/envolver-anitta-tamb%C3%A9m-%C3%A9-n%C3%BAmero-191950658.html |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=br.noticias.yahoo.com |language=pt-BR |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231164403/https://br.noticias.yahoo.com/envolver-anitta-tamb%C3%A9m-%C3%A9-n%C3%BAmero-191950658.html |url-status=live }}</ref> "[[Envolver]]" even managed to top the [[Billboard Global Excl. U.S.|''Billboard'' Global Excl. U.S.]] chart, becoming the first Latin woman to do so with a solo song; she still remained at number two on the [[Billboard Global 200|''Billboard'' Global 200]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-04-04 |title=Anitta é #1 na parada da Billboard Global excluindo USA |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-e-1-na-parada-da-billboard-global-excluindo-usa/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231164413/https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-e-1-na-parada-da-billboard-global-excluindo-usa/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-04-06 |title="Envolver" de Anitta: No. 1 en Billboard Global Excl. U.S. |url=https://mundocelebrities.com/actualidad/2022/04/06/anitta-no-1-billboard/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |language=es |archive-date=5 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230205003608/https://mundocelebrities.com/actualidad/2022/04/06/anitta-no-1-billboard/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last1=Trust |first1=Gary |date=4 April 2022 |title=Anitta's 'Envolver' Hits No. 1 on Billboard Global Excl. U.S. Chart |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/anitta-envolver-number-one-billboard-global-excl-us-chart-1235055130/ |access-date=28 November 2022 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |language=en-US |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220405074053/https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/anitta-envolver-number-one-billboard-global-excl-us-chart-1235055130/ |archive-date=5 April 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Still with "[[Envolver]]" Anitta got several entries on the [[Billboard charts]], one of the main ones being her second entry on the [[Billboard Hot 100|Hot 100]], first solo entry, the song became the third highest entry of a Latin solo song on the chart, behind only "[[Telepatía]]" by [[Kali Uchis]] and "[[Provenza (song)|Provenza]]" by [[Karol G]] both at 25, making it the second-highest solo song entry entirely in Spanish by a Latin female artist.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Nascimento |first=Leonardo |date=2022-04-05 |title=Anitta faz sua primeira entrada solo na Billboard Hot 100 com "Envolver"; confira |url=https://www.nerdsite.com.br/musica/anitta-faz-sua-primeira-entrada-solo-na-billboard-hot-100-com-envolver-confira/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=NERD SITE |language=pt-BR |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231164405/https://www.nerdsite.com.br/musica/anitta-faz-sua-primeira-entrada-solo-na-billboard-hot-100-com-envolver-confira/ |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name="Anitta">{{Cite magazine |title=Anitta |url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/anitta/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=1 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220101142700/https://www.billboard.com/artist/anitta/chart-history/tfc/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The song received praise from the international press and entered several "best of the year" lists, such as the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] and more.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-04 |title=The 100 best songs of 2022 (complete with playlist!) |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/music/story/2022-12-04/best-2022-100-songs-beyonce-taylor-swift-bad-bunny |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=Los Angeles Times |language=en-US |archive-date=4 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221204200850/https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/music/story/2022-12-04/best-2022-100-songs-beyonce-taylor-swift-bad-bunny |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |author=Billboard Staff |date=2022-12-07 |title=The 100 Best Songs of 2022: Staff List |url=https://www.billboard.com/lists/best-songs-2022/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=12 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230112132256/https://www.billboard.com/lists/best-songs-2022/ |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Rolling Stone|Rolling Stones magazine]] named the song the 81st best reggaeton song of all time.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last1=Villa |first1=Ecleen Luzmila Caraballo, Jon Dolan, Ricardo Durán, Katelina Eccleston, Verónica Bayetti Flores, Julyssa Lopez, Moises Mendez II, Jennifer Mota, Gary Suarez, Lucas |last2=Caraballo |first2=Ecleen Luzmila |last3=Dolan |first3=Jon |last4=Durán |first4=Ricardo |last5=Eccleston |first5=Katelina |last6=Flores |first6=Verónica Bayetti |last7=Lopez |first7=Julyssa |last8=II |first8=Moises Mendez |last9=Mota |first9=Jennifer |date=2022-08-26 |title=100 Greatest Reggaeton Songs of All Time |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-reggaeton-songs-1234579826/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |archive-date=3 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221003203832/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-reggaeton-songs-1234579826/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In February 2022, Anitta performed at [[Premio Lo Nuestro 2022|Premios Lo Nuestro]] along with [[Justin Quiles]] the remix version of "[[Envolver]]", in addition to "No Chão Novinha".<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Flores |first=Griselda |date=2022-02-15 |title=Anitta, Justin Quiles, El Fantasma & More to Perform at Premio Lo Nuestro 2022 |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/premio-lo-nuestro-2022-performers-anitta-justin-quiles-1235031426/ |access-date=2023-01-13 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=13 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230113214654/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/premio-lo-nuestro-2022-performers-anitta-justin-quiles-1235031426/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 26 March, she took the [[Lollapalooza Brazil]] main stage alongside [[Miley Cyrus]] and performed together the single "[[Boys Don't Cry (Anitta song)|Boys Don't Cry]]" the live version became a track for the deluxe version of the album [[Attention: Miley Live|Attentions: Miley Live]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-03-29 |title=Anitta joins Miley Cyrus on stage in Brazil during concert dedicated to Taylor Hawkins |url=https://www.hola.com/us/celebrities/20220329330768/miley-cyrus-anitta-lollapalooza-brazil-performance-taylor-hawkins/ |access-date=2023-01-13 |website=HOLA |language=en-US |archive-date=23 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221123090346/https://www.hola.com/us/celebrities/20220329330768/miley-cyrus-anitta-lollapalooza-brazil-performance-taylor-hawkins/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Miley Cyrus announces deluxe version of her live album 'Attention: Miley Live' |url=https://www.aninews.in/news/entertainment/music/miley-cyrus-announces-deluxe-version-of-her-live-album-attention-miley-live20220426223520/ |access-date=2023-01-13 |website=ANI News |language=en |archive-date=13 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230113214652/https://www.aninews.in/news/entertainment/music/miley-cyrus-announces-deluxe-version-of-her-live-album-attention-miley-live20220426223520/ |url-status=live }}</ref> With the song "Boys Don't Cry", Anitta expanded her record as the Brazilian artist with the highest number of number-one hits worldwide on [[iTunes]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-01-30 |title="Boys Don't Cry" se torna a faixa de Anitta com mais #1s no iTunes ao redor do mundo |url=https://portalfamosos.com.br/boys-dont-cry-se-torna-a-faixa-de-anitta-com-mais-1s-no-itunes-ao-redor-do-mundo/ |access-date=2023-07-12 |website=Portal Famosos Brasil {{!}} PFBR |language=pt-BR |archive-date=6 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220206194952/https://portalfamosos.com.br/boys-dont-cry-se-torna-a-faixa-de-anitta-com-mais-1s-no-itunes-ao-redor-do-mundo/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The solo track reached the top spot in 45 countries.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Campos |first=Gabriela |date=2022-01-28 |title=Anitta lança "Boys Don't Cry"; confira marcos da faixa |url=https://tracklist.com.br/boys-dont-cry-anitta/127192 |access-date=2023-07-12 |website=Tracklist |language=pt-BR |archive-date=12 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230712061753/https://tracklist.com.br/boys-dont-cry-anitta/127192 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 31 March 2022, Anitta announced her fifth studio and second [[multilingual]] album, ''[[Versions of Me]]'', would be released on 12 April.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=anitta|number=1509581084001976322|title=Versions Of Me The album April 12th|date=31 March 2022|access-date=1 April 2022|archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/ACCFW|archive-date=15 October 2023|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Ryan Tedder]] executive produced the album.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Exposito |first=Suzy |date=2020-06-18 |title=Brazilian Pop Star Anitta Announces New Deal With Warner Music |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-latin/anitta-warner-music-2020-album-ryan-tedder-1017183/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |archive-date=24 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230224192544/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-latin/anitta-warner-music-2020-album-ryan-tedder-1017183/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The singles "[[Me Gusta (Anitta song)|Me Gusta]]" (featuring [[Cardi B]] and [[Myke Towers]]), "[[Girl from Rio (song)|Girl from Rio]]", "Faking Love" (featuring [[Saweetie]]), "[[Envolver]]", and "[[Boys Don't Cry (Anitta song)|Boys Don't Cry]]" preceded the album.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Empresário da Anitta mostra reação da cantora ao descobrir que novo álbum está pronto |url=https://gq.globo.com/Celebridades/noticia/2022/03/empresario-da-anitta-mostra-reacao-da-cantora-ao-descobrir-que-novo-album-esta-pronto.html |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=GQ |date=21 August 2022 |language=pt-br |archive-date=28 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230128065653/https://gq.globo.com/Celebridades/noticia/2022/03/empresario-da-anitta-mostra-reacao-da-cantora-ao-descobrir-que-novo-album-esta-pronto.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Becoming the first Brazilian pop album to reach the mark of 1 billion streams on [[Spotify]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Álbum "Versions Of Me", de Anitta, atinge a marca de 1 bilhão de streams no Spotify |url=https://www.vagalume.com.br/news/2022/10/17/album-de-anitta-versions-of-me-atinge-1-bilhao-de-streams-no-spotify.html |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=Vagalume |language=pt-br |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231164406/https://www.vagalume.com.br/news/2022/10/17/album-de-anitta-versions-of-me-atinge-1-bilhao-de-streams-no-spotify.html |url-status=live }}</ref> The album reached the highest debut by a Brazilian artist on [[iTunes]], [[Apple Music]] and [[Spotify]] in the [[United States]], the album was the most streamed in the world on its debut on Spotify Global upon its release, in addition to being the third-highest debut on Spotify in the United States.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta tem o novo álbum mais ouvido do mundo no Spotify |url=https://expresso.pt/blitz/2022-04-20-Anitta-tem-o-novo-album-mais-ouvido-do-mundo-no-Spotify-a071f09c |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=Jornal Expresso |date=20 April 2022 |language=pt-PT |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231164407/https://expresso.pt/blitz/2022-04-20-Anitta-tem-o-novo-album-mais-ouvido-do-mundo-no-Spotify-a071f09c |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Redação |date=2022-04-19 |title=Álbum de Anitta estreia no #1 Global do Spotify |url=https://rollingstone.uol.com.br/musica/album-de-anitta-estreia-no-1-global-do-spotify/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=pt-br |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231164412/https://rollingstone.uol.com.br/musica/album-de-anitta-estreia-no-1-global-do-spotify/ |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Versions of Me]]'' broke the record for the biggest Spotify debut by a Brazilian artist in the platform's history with over 9.1 million streams. In addition, the album surpassed the debut of [[Camila Cabello]]'s new album, ''[[Familia (Camila Cabello album)|Familia]]'', also being the album by a Latin woman with the highest debut in 2022.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-04-14 |title=Anitta quebra recorde de maior estreia no Spotify com 'Versions Of Me' |url=https://portalrapmais.com/anitta-quebra-recorde-de-maior-estreia-no-spotify-para-um-artista-brasileiro-com-versions-of-me/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=Rap Mais |language=pt-BR |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231164411/https://portalrapmais.com/anitta-quebra-recorde-de-maior-estreia-no-spotify-para-um-artista-brasileiro-com-versions-of-me/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta lança álbum "Version of me" e tem melhor estreia brasileira nos EUA |url=https://www.nsctotal.com.br/noticias/anitta-lanca-album-version-of-me-e-tem-melhor-estreia-brasileira-nos-eua |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=NSC Total |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231171413/https://www.nsctotal.com.br/noticias/anitta-lanca-album-version-of-me-e-tem-melhor-estreia-brasileira-nos-eua |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Forbes]]'', ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', ''[[NME]]'', [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] and ''[[The Line of Best Fit]]'' were some of the portals that positively evaluated ''[[Versions of Me]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Méndez |first=Chris Malone |title=Anitta Shares Her New Trilingual Album 'Versions of Me' |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/cmalone/2022/04/12/anitta-shares-her-new-trilingual-album-versions-of-me/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=Forbes |language=en |archive-date=20 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221220133410/https://www.forbes.com/sites/cmalone/2022/04/12/anitta-shares-her-new-trilingual-album-versions-of-me/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Lopez |first=Julyssa |date=2022-04-12 |title=How Anitta Is Making the Whole World Fall in Love With Her |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/anitta-brazil-coachella-envolver-new-album-1334611/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |archive-date=7 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220507014540/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/anitta-brazil-coachella-envolver-new-album-1334611/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |author=Billboard Staff |date=2022-04-13 |title=Anitta Delivers Her New Trilingual 'Versions of Me' Album: Listen to Editors' Picks |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/anitta-versions-of-me-album-essential-tracks-1235058559/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=21 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220421061959/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/anitta-versions-of-me-album-essential-tracks-1235058559/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Levine |first=Nick |date=2022-04-13 |title=Anitta – Versions of Me' review: filter-free hustler continues her global charm offensive |url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/anitta-versions-of-me-3204049 |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=NME |language=en-GB |archive-date=1 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220501093252/https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/anitta-versions-of-me-3204049}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title="Versions of Me" shows Anitta's best side, even if's not her best music to date |url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/reviews/albums/anitta-versions-of-me |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=The Line of Best Fit |language=en-US |archive-date=25 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220425172606/https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/reviews/albums/anitta-versions-of-me |url-status=live }}</ref> In the same month of April, she became the first Brazilian to perform on the main stage of the [[Coachella (festival)|Coachella festival]].<ref name="instyle" /><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta Becomes the First Female Brazilian Solo Artist to Perform at Coachella: 'This Is My Country' |url=https://people.com/music/anitta-coachella-first-ever-brazilian-solo-artist-to-perform-festival/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=Peoplemag |language=en |archive-date=11 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220511034935/https://people.com/music/anitta-coachella-first-ever-brazilian-solo-artist-to-perform-festival/ }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Leiros |first=Marcela |date=2022-04-16 |title=Coachella: primeira brasileira a se apresentar no festival, Anitta leva hits ao palco principal |url=https://revistacenarium.com.br/coachella-primeira-brasileira-a-se-apresentar-no-festival-anitta-leva-hits-ao-palco-principal/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=Revista Cenarium |language=pt-BR |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231192931/https://revistacenarium.com.br/coachella-primeira-brasileira-a-se-apresentar-no-festival-anitta-leva-hits-ao-palco-principal/}}</ref> In the same month, she got her first nomination at the [[2022 MTV Video Music Awards|MTV Video Music Awards]] for "[[Envolver]]" in the "[[MTV Video Music Award for Best Latin|Best Latin]]" category; a main show performance was also confirmed.<ref name="instyle" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=Aswad |first=Jem |date=26 July 2022 |title=MTV VMA 2022 Nominations Revealed: Kendrick Lamar, Lil Nas X, Jack Harlow, Harry Styles, More |url=https://variety.com/2022/music/news/mtv-vma-2022-kendrick-lamar-harry-styles-1235325240/ |access-date=9 August 2022 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=26 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220726134223/https://variety.com/2022/music/news/mtv-vma-2022-kendrick-lamar-harry-styles-1235325240/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=5 August 2022 |title=Anitta, J Balvin and More Performers Revealed for 2022 MTV Video Music Awards |url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1340892/anitta-j-balvin-and-more-performers-revealed-for-2022-mtv-video-music-awards |access-date=9 August 2022 |website=E! Online |archive-date=27 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220827013315/https://www.eonline.com/news/1340892/anitta-j-balvin-and-more-performers-revealed-for-2022-mtv-video-music-awards |url-status=live }}</ref> By popular vote, the song won the category, making Anitta the first female solo artist to receive the award.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta faz 2ª aparição no 'Guinness World Records' por prêmio no MTV VMA |url=https://www.estadao.com.br/emais/gente/anitta-faz-2-aparicao-no-guinness-world-records-por-premio-no-mtv-vma/ |access-date=2024-09-19 |website=Estadão |language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=First female solo artist to win Best Latin at the MTV Video Music Awards |url=https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/716826-first-female-solo-artist-to-win-best-latin-at-the-mtv-video-music-awards |access-date=2022-12-29 |website=Guinness World Records |date=28 August 2022 |language=en-gb |archive-date=29 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221229214341/https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/716826-first-female-solo-artist-to-win-best-latin-at-the-mtv-video-music-awards |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="vogue">{{cite web|last=Allaire|first=Christian|url=https://www.vogue.com/slideshow/anitta-mtv-vmas-fashion-red-carpet-performance/amp|title=Anitta's Fiery VMAs Wardrobe Was an Ode to Brazil|date=29 August 2022|accessdate=31 August 2022|work=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220902074956/https://www.vogue.com/slideshow/anitta-mtv-vmas-fashion-red-carpet-performance/amp|archive-date=2 September 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> Anitta also became the first artist from Brazil to perform and win an [[American Music Awards]].<ref name="Neira">{{Cite web |title=Anitta becomes the first Brazilian artist in history to win AMA for Favorite Female Latin Artist |date=21 November 2022 |url=https://www.hola.com/us/celebrities/20221121339537/anitta-makes-history-amas/ |first=Daniel |last=Neira |work=HOLA! |access-date=22 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221128220150/https://www.hola.com/us/celebrities/20221121339537/anitta-makes-history-amas/ |archive-date=28 November 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 5 May 2022, Anitta was the [[female lead]] in the [[music video]] for "[[First Class (song)|First Class]]", by [[rapper]] [[Jack Harlow]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=wrmf |date=2022-05-24 |title=Anitta on how her "first hug of the year", Jack Harlow, cast her in "First Class" video |url=https://www.wrmf.com/anitta-on-how-her-first-hug-of-the-year-jack-harlow-cast-her-in-first-class-video/ |access-date=2023-01-31 |website=97.9 WRMF |language=en-US |archive-date=31 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230131183242/https://www.wrmf.com/anitta-on-how-her-first-hug-of-the-year-jack-harlow-cast-her-in-first-class-video/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 13 May 2022, Anitta was one of the international guests at the first ''Billboard MusicCon'' where she spoke with other artists on topics such as the evolution of the music scene in genres and cultures, women in music, among other related topics, she also performed several songs in the event.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Calcagno |first=Michael |date=2022-05-14 |title=2022 Billboard MusicCon: Photos From the Performances |url=https://www.billboard.com/photos/billboard-musiccon-2022-performances-photos-1235070977/ |access-date=2023-01-13 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=17 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220517025738/https://www.billboard.com/photos/billboard-musiccon-2022-performances-photos-1235070977/1-anitta-performance-musiccon-2022-billboard-1-1548/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 15 May, she and [[Michael Bublé]] were one of the presenters at the [[2022 Billboard Music Awards|''Billboard'' Music Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.warnerrecords.com/news/michael-buble-anitta-2022-billboard-music-awards-presenters |title=MICHAEL BUBLÉ & ANITTA 2022 Billboard Music Awards Presenters |access-date=2023-01-13 |website=Warner Records |language=en |archive-date=13 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230113214654/https://www.warnerrecords.com/news/michael-buble-anitta-2022-billboard-music-awards-presenters}}</ref> Dressed by the Italian brand [[Moschino]], led by creative director [[Jeremy Scott]], Anitta attended, for her second time, the annual [[Met Gala|Met Gala 2022]] ball, in May.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.uol.com.br/nossa/noticias/redacao/2022/05/02/anitta-met-gala-look.htm |title=Met Gala 2022: Anitta aposta em decote ombro a ombro para look com pérolas |access-date=May 4, 2025 |website=Nossa Moda |language=pt-br|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230211190829/https://www.uol.com.br/nossa/noticias/redacao/2022/05/02/anitta-met-gala-look.htm |archive-date=11 February 2023}}</ref>

In June 2022, [[Madame Tussauds New York]] unveiled their wax figure of Anitta.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.madametussauds.com/new-york/information/news/global-superstar-anitta-reveals-her-highly-anticipated-wax-figure/|title=Global Superstar Anitta Reveals Her Highly Anticipated Wax Figure|date=2 June 2022|access-date=28 February 2024|archive-date=28 September 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230928074919/https://www.madametussauds.com/new-york/information/news/global-superstar-anitta-reveals-her-highly-anticipated-wax-figure/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Flores |first=Griselda |date=2022-06-02 |title=Anitta Gets Her Own Madame Tussauds Wax Figure: 'I'm Excited for the World to See It' |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/anitta-wax-figure-madame-tussauds-new-york-1235080693/ |access-date=2023-01-12 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=28 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230528221729/https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/anitta-wax-figure-madame-tussauds-new-york-1235080693/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Still in June 2022, Anitta started a promotional tour at the main music festivals in [[Europe]]. Anitta started the series of concerts in [[Spain]] and ended with a super concert in [[Portugal]]. The promotional tour went through nine European countries ([[Spain]], [[Ireland]], [[Portugal]], [[Denmark]], [[Sweden]], [[Holland]], [[Switzerland]], [[Italy]] and [[France]]).<ref>{{Cite web |last=Redação |date=2022-06-17 |title=Anitta anuncia turnê na Europa com shows no Rock in Rio Lisboa e Lollapalooza |url=https://rollingstone.uol.com.br/musica/anitta-anuncia-turne-na-europa-com-shows-no-rock-in-rio-lisboa-e-lollapalooza/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=Rollingstone |language=pt-br |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231192918/https://rollingstone.uol.com.br/musica/anitta-anuncia-turne-na-europa-com-shows-no-rock-in-rio-lisboa-e-lollapalooza/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The show in [[Poland]] was canceled due to the ongoing [[Russian invasion of Ukraine]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Trapeton Summer Bash 2022 at Plaża Stogi (Gdansk) on 8 Jul 2022 |url=https://www.last.fm/festival/4627609+Trapeton+Summer+Bash+2022 |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=Last.fm |language=en |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231192917/https://www.last.fm/festival/4627609+Trapeton+Summer+Bash+2022 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 18 June, Anitta performed in one of the largest stadiums in France, [[Parc des Princes|Le Parc de Princes]], in [[Paris]] for an audience of more than 50 thousand people together with [[Dadju]], with the song "Mon Soleil".<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-06-19 |title=Anitta canta com Dadju em show em estádio lotado na França |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-canta-com-dadju-em-show-em-estadio-lotado-na-franca/ |access-date=2023-01-13 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=20 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230120003342/https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-canta-com-dadju-em-show-em-estadio-lotado-na-franca/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 23 June, she gave [[interview]]s in French territory for [[NRJ|NRJ Hit Music Only]] and for the [[Quotidien]] program, in addition to performing "[[Envolver]]".<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-06-24 |title=Invitée : l'icône brésilienne Anitta qui cartonne avec son album "Versions of me" |url=https://www.tf1.fr/tmc/quotidien-avec-yann-barthes/videos/invitee-licone-bresilienne-anitta-qui-cartonne-avec-son-album-versions-of-me-07179297.html |access-date=2023-01-13 |website=MYTF1 |language=fr |archive-date=13 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230113214652/https://www.tf1.fr/tmc/quotidien-avec-yann-barthes/videos/invitee-licone-bresilienne-anitta-qui-cartonne-avec-son-album-versions-of-me-07179297.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-06-24 |title=Anitta canta "Envolver" e critica Bolsonaro em programa de TV francês |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-canta-envolver-critica-bolsonaro-programa-tv-frances/ |access-date=2023-01-13 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=4 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221204153347/https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-canta-envolver-critica-bolsonaro-programa-tv-frances/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 6 July 2022, Argentine singer [[Tini (singer)|Tini]] released "[[La Loto]]", a collaboration with Anitta and American singer [[Becky G]], which served as the seventh single from Tini's upcoming fourth album.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Mier |first=Tomás |date=7 July 2022 |title=Latina Reinas Tini, Becky G, and Anitta Join Forces on 'La Loto' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-latin/tini-becky-g-anitta-la-loto-song-video-1379425/ |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |language=en-US |access-date=7 July 2022 |archive-date=7 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220707223602/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-latin/tini-becky-g-anitta-la-loto-song-video-1379425/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The song became Anitta's highest peak on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] [[Argentina]], at number seven.<ref name="Anitta" /> On 8 July 2022, the song on "No Más" was released in collaboration with [[Murda Beatz]], [[J Balvin]], [[Quavo]] and [[Pharrell Williams|Pharrell]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last1=Zemler |first1=Kat Bouza, Emily |last2=Bouza |first2=Kat |last3=Zemler |first3=Emily |date=2022-07-08 |title=Murda Beatz's Summer Banger 'No Más' Features Quavo, Anitta and J Balvin |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/murda-beatz-no-mas-single-1379740/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |archive-date=23 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230323072849/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/murda-beatz-no-mas-single-1379740/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The song became the best position for a Brazilian artist in the history of [[iTunes]] in the United States, at 4th position, it also reached the first position on [[Amazon Music|Amazon Best Sellers]] in the United States and its highest position on [[Deezer|Deezer US]] in 14th, in addition to reaching the first position on ''Billboard'' Rap Digital Song Sales and the 13th on the [[Digital Song Sales|Billboard Digital Song Sales]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-07-26 |title=Anitta atinge sua melhor marca no iTunes dos EUA após colaboração com Murda Beatz, Quavo, J Balvin e Pharrel |url=https://portalrapmais.com/anitta-atinge-sua-melhor-marca-no-itunes-dos-eua-apos-colaboracao-com-murda-beatz-quavo-j-balvin-e-pharrel/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=Rap Mais |language=pt-BR |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231192921/https://portalrapmais.com/anitta-atinge-sua-melhor-marca-no-itunes-dos-eua-apos-colaboracao-com-murda-beatz-quavo-j-balvin-e-pharrel/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-07-09 |title=Com "No Más", Anitta se torna a primeira artista brasileira da história a atingir top 5 do iTunes US - Portal Famosos Brasil {{!}} PFBR |url=https://portalfamosos.com.br/com-no-mas-anitta-se-torna-a-primeira-artista-brasileira-da-historia-a-atingir-top-5-do-itunes-us/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |language=pt-BR |archive-date=9 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220709163731/https://portalfamosos.com.br/com-no-mas-anitta-se-torna-a-primeira-artista-brasileira-da-historia-a-atingir-top-5-do-itunes-us/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="Anitta" />

In August 2022, Anitta released the deluxe version of ''[[Versions of Me]]'', which featured collaborations with [[Maluma]], "El Que Espera", and [[Missy Elliott|Missy Elliot]], "Lobby", in addition to the trilingual version of "Dançarina Remix" with [[Pedro Sampaio]], [[Dadju]], [[Nicky Jam]] and [[MC Pedrinho]]. "Dançarina Remix" reached number 11 on the France Single Charts, Anitta's second highest position, behind only "Mon Soleil" number eight, and becoming Anitta's song with the most days in the top 50 on [[Spotify]] [[France]], in addition to receiving a platinum certificate in French territory, also reaching first place on the French [[Shazam (music app)|Shazam]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=lescharts.com - Les charts français |url=https://lescharts.com/search.asp?search=anitta&cat=s |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=lescharts.com |archive-date=12 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210712225644/https://lescharts.com/search.asp?search=anitta&cat=s |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Les certifications |url=https://snepmusique.com/les-certifications/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=SNEP |language=fr-FR |archive-date=18 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150218192953/https://snepmusique.com/les-certifications/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=The Pedro Sampaio {{!}} Fan Account's tweet - "UAU! "DANÇARINA (Remix), de Pedro Sampaio em parceria com Anitta, MC pedrinho, Dadju e Nicky Jam, alcançou o 1º lugar das músicas mais buscadas no Shazam França. " |website=Trendsmap |url=https://www.trendsmap.com/twitter/tweet/1568445899424276480 |access-date=2022-12-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231194424/https://www.trendsmap.com/twitter/tweet/1568445899424276480 |archive-date=31 December 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-08 |title=Dançarina Remix se torna a música de Anitta com mais dias no top 50 do Spotify França |url=https://bcharts.com.br/t/dancarina-remix-se-torna-a-musica-de-anitta-com-mais-dias-no-top-50-do-spotify-franca/361081 |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=BCharts Fórum |language=pt-BR |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231192918/https://bcharts.com.br/t/dancarina-remix-se-torna-a-musica-de-anitta-com-mais-dias-no-top-50-do-spotify-franca/361081 |url-status=dead }}</ref> "Lobby" earned Anitta her first entry on [[Japan]]'s largest streaming platform, [[Line Music]], making her the first artist from Brazil to achieve this milestone.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.trendsmap.com/twitter/tweet/1563979785604399104 |title=Anitta Charts {{!}} Fan Account's tweet - "🇯🇵 LINE MUSIC Pop Chart (24-25 August): #36. "Lobby" (@Anitta & @MissyElliott) [NEW] — This is her 1st entry on the country's chart and in genre. It's Japan's biggest streaming platform. She became the first Brazilian pop artist in history to have this milestone. " |website=Trendsmap |access-date=2022-12-31 |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231192919/https://www.trendsmap.com/twitter/tweet/1563979785604399104}}</ref>

On 28 October 2022, the [[Black Eyed Peas]] released "Simply the Best" the opening track and the second single from their album ''Elevation'', a collaboration with Anitta and [[El Alfa]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=HUB |first=YOUR CULTURE |date=2022-11-07 |title=BLACK EYED PEAS UNVEIL NEW SINGLE & MUSIC VIDEO "SIMPLY THE BEST" WITH ANITTA & EL ALFA |url=https://imprintent.org/black-eyed-peas-unveil-new-single-music-video-simply-the-best-with-anitta-el-alfa/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=IMPRINT |language=en-US |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231192918/https://imprintent.org/black-eyed-peas-unveil-new-single-music-video-simply-the-best-with-anitta-el-alfa/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In November 2022, in addition to being nominated in two categories at the [[23rd Annual Latin Grammy Awards|Latin Grammy Awards]], Anitta also performed a performance of "[[Envolver]]" and a Funk Dance Medley, she was also one of the hosts of the night.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Villa |first=Lucas |date=2022-11-18 |title=Anitta Does It All At The Latin Grammys |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-latin/anitta-latin-grammys-performance-1234632928/ |access-date=2022-12-31 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |archive-date=31 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221231192913/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-latin/anitta-latin-grammys-performance-1234632928/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In November, she still performed at [[Rihanna]]'s [[Savage X Fenty Show]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-10-25 |title=Rihanna Reveals the 'Savage X Fenty Show Vol. 4' Cast in New Teaser |url=https://hypebeast.com/2022/10/rihanna-savage-x-fenty-show-vol-4-teaser-cast-announcement |access-date=2022-12-31 |website=Hypebeast |archive-date=3 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230203145154/https://hypebeast.com/2022/10/rihanna-savage-x-fenty-show-vol-4-teaser-cast-announcement |url-status=live }}</ref> Anitta was listed by [[Forbes 30 Under 30]] [[North America]] 2023, in the music category, as one of the leaders of the next generation of [[Music of Latin America|Latin American music]]. The list aims to recognize artists who make a significant contribution to the world's recording industry.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Almeida |first=Fernanda |date=2022-11-30 |title=Anitta é destaque na lista 30 Under 30 da Forbes USA |url=https://forbes.com.br/forbeslife/2022/11/anitta-e-destaque-na-lista-30-under-30-da-forbes-usa/ |access-date=2024-09-19 |website=Forbes Brasil |language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta |url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/anitta/ |access-date=30 November 2022 |website=Forbes |language=en |archive-date=30 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221130212242/https://www.forbes.com/profile/anitta/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Burney |first=Charlotte |title=Trilingual Albums, Music Tech And TikTok: Meet The 30 Under 30 In Music 2023 |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/charlotteburney/2022/11/29/trilingual-albums-music-tech-and-tiktok-meet-the-30-under-30-in-music-2023/ |access-date=30 November 2022 |website=Forbes |language=en |archive-date=12 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221212121219/https://www.forbes.com/sites/charlotteburney/2022/11/29/trilingual-albums-music-tech-and-tiktok-meet-the-30-under-30-in-music-2023/ |url-status=live }}</ref> After successful releases, nominations for dozens of world awards and accomplishments achieved throughout the year, she was nominated for the [[65th Annual Grammy Awards|2023 Grammy Awards]] in the [[Best New Artist]] category.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Best New Artist 2023 - Grammy Nominations|url=https://www.grammy.com/news/best-new-artist-2023-grammy-nominations-65th-grammys-awards|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221115230456/https://www.grammy.com/news/best-new-artist-2023-grammy-nominations-65th-grammys-awards|archive-date=15 November 2022|url-status=live|access-date=16 November 2022}}</ref><ref name="Revelação">{{Cite web |title=Anitta pode ser 1ª latina a ganhar Grammy de 'Revelação' em mais de 50 anos |url=https://www.uol.com.br/splash/noticias/2022/11/15/grammy-awards.htm |date=15 November 2022 |access-date=May 4, 2025 |website=Splash |language=pt-br |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221128220145/https://www.uol.com.br/splash/noticias/2022/11/15/grammy-awards.htm |archive-date=28 November 2022 }}</ref>

On 2 November, Anitta joined [[Lil Nas X]], [[BTS]] and [[Tyler, the Creator|Tyler the Creator]] and was honored with the [[WSJ magazine|WSJ Magazine Innovator Awards 2022]], held by ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'', which honors visionaries in various areas of entertainment.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2022 Innovator Awards - The Wall Street Journal Magazine |url=https://wsjinnovators.com/ |access-date=2023-01-13 |website=2022 Innovator Awards |language=en-US |archive-date=27 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221027011624/https://wsjinnovators.com/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Meet All the 2022 WSJ. Magazine Innovators |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/margot-robbie-anitta-maya-rudolph-jony-ive-innovators-11668100513 |access-date=2023-01-13 |newspaper=Wall Street Journal |date=11 November 2022 |language=en-US |archive-date=14 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230114204346/https://www.wsj.com/articles/margot-robbie-anitta-maya-rudolph-jony-ive-innovators-11668100513 |url-status=live }}</ref> In November, she performed at the [[Los 40 Music Awards 2022|Los 40 Music Awards]], becoming one of the most talked about subjects in [[Spain]] due to her performance of "[[Envolver]]".<ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta le perrea a Ayuso: el momento más comentado de los 40 Music Awards |url=https://www.expreso.ec/ocio/anitta-le-perrea-ayuso-momento-comentado-40-music-awards-140288.html |access-date=2023-01-13 |website=www.expreso.ec |archive-date=3 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230203132203/https://www.expreso.ec/ocio/anitta-le-perrea-ayuso-momento-comentado-40-music-awards-140288.html |url-status=live }}</ref> On 15 November 2022, Anitta released a version of "Practice" ("Prooshtis" in the game's language) entirely in [[Simlish]], for [[The Sims|The Sims Sessions]] global campaign in ''[[The Sims 4]]'', thus being the sixth language in which she sings.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Arts |first=Electronic |date=2022-11-16 |title=Reimaginando o Sims Sessions |url=https://www.ea.com/games/the-sims/the-sims-4/news/reimagining-sims-sessions |access-date=2023-01-31 |website=www.ea.com |language=pt-br |archive-date=27 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230127082919/https://www.ea.com/games/the-sims/the-sims-4/news/reimagining-sims-sessions |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Dhawan |first=Nishka |date=2022-11-16 |title=Anitta Releases New Single in 'Simlish,' Inspired by Her Love for the Popular Video Game |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/product-recommendations/lifestyle/anitta-sims-collab-launch-sims-sessions-1234630902/ |access-date=2023-01-31 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |archive-date=31 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230131182951/https://www.rollingstone.com/product-recommendations/lifestyle/anitta-sims-collab-launch-sims-sessions-1234630902/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 30 November, Anitta released her third EP, ''À procura da Anitta perfeita'', on the [[Warner Music Brasil]] label. It is Anitta's first project entirely in [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] since the album [[Bang! (Anitta album)|''Bang!'']]. The EP was leaked ahead of time, some songs were made available on some digital platforms, without prior disclosure and by surprise.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-01 |title=EP de Anitta vaza horas antes do lançamento e cantora lamenta: 'Era surpresa' |url=https://www.ofuxico.com.br/musica-e-shows/ep-de-anitta-vaza-antes-do-lancamento-e-cantora-lamenta-era-surpresa/ |access-date=2023-01-12 |website=OFuxico |language=pt-br |archive-date=12 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230112155731/https://www.ofuxico.com.br/musica-e-shows/ep-de-anitta-vaza-antes-do-lancamento-e-cantora-lamenta-era-surpresa/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta lança EP "À Procura da Anitta Perfeita" após vazamento |url=https://glamour.globo.com/entretenimento/musica/noticia/2022/11/anitta-lanca-ep-apos-vazamento-era-uma-surpresa-pra-voces.ghtml |access-date=2023-01-12 |website=Glamour |date=30 November 2022 |language=pt-br |archive-date=5 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221205015111/https://glamour.globo.com/entretenimento/musica/noticia/2022/11/anitta-lanca-ep-apos-vazamento-era-uma-surpresa-pra-voces.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> All songs debuted in the top 60 of Spotify [[Brazil]] and [[Portugal]], with approximately 2 million streams in 24 hours.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-02 |title=Com quase 2 MILHÕES de reproduções, confira como foi a estreia do EP "À Procura da Anitta Perfeita" - Portal Famosos Brasil {{!}} PFBR |url=https://portalfamosos.com.br/com-quase-2-milhoes-de-reproducoes-confira-como-foi-a-estreia-do-ep-a-procura-da-anitta-perfeita/ |access-date=2023-01-12 |language=pt-BR |archive-date=2 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221202174411/https://portalfamosos.com.br/com-quase-2-milhoes-de-reproducoes-confira-como-foi-a-estreia-do-ep-a-procura-da-anitta-perfeita/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=themusicjournalbrazil |title=Anitta estreia novo EP no Spotify com quase 2 milhões de streams |url=https://www.terra.com.br/diversao/musica/anitta-estreia-novo-ep-no-spotify-com-quase-2-milhoes-de-streams,0f209790776538b6c76a11424e0b3719lzkmyysi.html |access-date=2023-01-12 |website=Terra |language=pt-BR |archive-date=12 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230112155723/https://www.terra.com.br/diversao/musica/anitta-estreia-novo-ep-no-spotify-com-quase-2-milhoes-de-streams,0f209790776538b6c76a11424e0b3719lzkmyysi.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 18 December, she performed at [[IHeartRadio|iHeartradio y100's]] [[Jingle Ball]] at the [[FLA Live Arena]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Y100's Jingle Ball - Y100 |url=https://y100.iheart.com/featured/y100-jingle-ball/ |access-date=2023-01-13 |website=Y100's Jingle Ball |language=en |archive-date=6 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230506135128/https://y100.iheart.com/featured/y100-jingle-ball/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 27 December 2022, [[Guinness World Records]] chose to highlight the top six music artists of 2022, Anitta joined [[Taylor Swift]], [[BTS]], [[Harry Styles]], [[Billie Eilish]], [[Adele]] and were named in a list of 2022's Iconic Record Breakers.<ref name="instyle" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-28 |title=Anitta And BTS Are Guinness World Records' 'Iconic' Record Breakers |url=https://uproxx.com/pop/anitta-bts-taylor-swift-guinness-world-records-iconic-record-breakers/ |access-date=2022-12-29 |website=UPROXX |language=en-US |archive-date=25 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230325172021/https://uproxx.com/pop/anitta-bts-taylor-swift-guinness-world-records-iconic-record-breakers/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-27 |title=Taylor Swift, Harry Styles, BTS and more: 2022's iconic record breakers |url=https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2022/12/taylor-swift-harry-styles-bts-and-more-2022s-iconic-record-breakers |access-date=2022-12-29 |website=Guinness World Records |language=en-gb |archive-date=2 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230402120428/https://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2022/12/taylor-swift-harry-styles-bts-and-more-2022s-iconic-record-breakers}}</ref>

=== 2023–2024: Acting debut and ''Funk Generation'' ===
On 20 January, Anitta won the "Best Global Act" award at the [[All Africa Music Awards]], the largest award ceremony in the [[African continent]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Premiados AFRIMA 2022 [1/2]: Brasil e Nigéria - Rádio Câmara |url=https://www.camara.leg.br/radio/programas/936253-premiados-afrima-2022-1-2-brasil-e-nigeria/ |access-date=2023-02-22 |website=Portal da Câmara dos Deputados |language=pt-br |archive-date=22 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230222175218/https://www.camara.leg.br/radio/programas/936253-premiados-afrima-2022-1-2-brasil-e-nigeria/ |url-status=live }}</ref> This achievement made her the first Latin artist to receive this honor.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Past Winners {{!}} AFRIMA |url=https://afrima.org/afrimawebsite/past-winners |access-date=2023-02-22 |website=afrima.org |language=en |archive-date=22 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230222175220/https://afrima.org/afrimawebsite/past-winners |url-status=live }}</ref> On 23 January, Anitta received 6 nominations at [[Lo Nuestro Awards]], one of the most important Latin music awards.<ref>{{Cite web |last=themusicjournalbrazil |title=Anitta recebe seis indicações ao Premio Lo Nuestro 2023 |url=https://www.terra.com.br/diversao/musica/anitta-recebe-seis-indicacoes-ao-premio-lo-nuestro-2023,ebddf14651d8e729292a96a887242418ztc445qz.html |access-date=2023-02-22 |website=Terra |language=pt-BR |archive-date=22 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230222175219/https://www.terra.com.br/diversao/musica/anitta-recebe-seis-indicacoes-ao-premio-lo-nuestro-2023,ebddf14651d8e729292a96a887242418ztc445qz.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Furthermore, Anitta also became an ambassador for [[Lay's]] on 17 January, one of the most well-known snack brands in the world.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Lay's and Brazilian superstar Anitta power campaign with potato electricity |url=https://www.marketingdive.com/news/lays-anitta-potato-electricity-marketing/640528/ |access-date=2023-02-22 |website=Marketing Dive |language=en-US |archive-date=17 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230817231527/https://www.marketingdive.com/news/lays-anitta-potato-electricity-marketing/640528/ |url-status=live }}</ref> She starred in a post-[[Super Bowl]] [[TV spot]] for the "Beat of Joy" campaign, which featured a remix of the song "[[Envolver]]" recorded in a studio powered by electricity from more than 6,000 potatoes.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Our Favorite Super Bowl LVII Commercials Featuring JLo, Diana Flores & More |url=https://remezcla.com/lists/film/our-favorite-super-bowl-lvii-commercials-featuring-jlo-diana-flores-more/ |access-date=2023-02-22 |website=Remezcla |date=13 February 2023 |language=en-US |archive-date=22 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230222175219/https://remezcla.com/lists/film/our-favorite-super-bowl-lvii-commercials-featuring-jlo-diana-flores-more/ |url-status=live }}</ref> This campaign set a [[Guinness World Records|Guinness World Record]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=US Ad of the Day: Lay's remixes Anitta's single, Envolver, using 6,000 potatoes |url=https://www.thedrum.com/news/2023/01/18/us-ad-the-day-lay-s-remixes-anitta-s-single-envolver-using-6000-potatoes |access-date=2023-02-22 |website=The Drum |archive-date=22 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230222175222/https://www.thedrum.com/news/2023/01/18/us-ad-the-day-lay-s-remixes-anitta-s-single-envolver-using-6000-potatoes |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 25 February, after the official end of the [[Brazilian Carnival|2023 Carnival]], Anitta held a gathering of more than 1 million people in her street parade, "[[Bloco da Anitta]]" at 7 a.m. in [[Rio de Janeiro]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Carnaval não acabou! Anitta arrasta mais de 1 milhão de pessoas em bloco - Varela Net |url=https://varelanet.com.br/noticias/entretenimento/carnaval-nao-acabou-anitta-arrasta-mais-de-1-milhao-de-pessoas-em-bloco |access-date=2023-05-12 |website=Carnaval não acabou! Anitta arrasta mais de 1 milhão de pessoas em bloco - Varela Net |language=pt-BR |archive-date=12 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230512194833/https://www.varelanet.com.br/noticias/entretenimento/carnaval-nao-acabou-anitta-arrasta-mais-de-1-milhao-de-pessoas-em-bloco |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-02-25 |title=Bloco da Anitta tem show de Jason Derulo, calor extremo e um milhão de foliões |url=https://f5.folha.uol.com.br/celebridades/carnaval/2023/02/bloco-da-anitta-tem-show-de-jason-derulo-calor-extremo-e-um-milhao-de-folioes.shtml |access-date=2023-05-12 |website=F5 |language=pt-BR |archive-date=24 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230324200354/https://f5.folha.uol.com.br/celebridades/carnaval/2023/02/bloco-da-anitta-tem-show-de-jason-derulo-calor-extremo-e-um-milhao-de-folioes.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 2 March, Anitta was elected by [[Variety (magazine)|''Variety'' magazine]] as the seventh most impactful international woman of 2023, being the only Brazilian artist on the list.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Vourlias |first1=Alexis Benveniste, Nick Clement, Anna Marie de la Fuente, Shalini Dore, Sharareh Drury, Charna Flam, Diane Garrett, John Hopewell, Karen Idelson, Todd Longwell, Julia MacCary, Lily Moayeri, Tariq Raouf, Katie Reul, Mark Sutherland, Christopher |last2=Benveniste |first2=Alexis |last3=Clement |first3=Nick |last4=Fuente |first4=Anna Marie de la |last5=Dore |first5=Shalini |last6=Drury |first6=Sharareh |last7=Flam |first7=Charna |last8=Garrett |first8=Diane |last9=Hopewell |first9=John |date=2023-03-01 |title=From Abby Ajayi to Rosalía: Meet Variety's Impactful International Women of 2023 |url=https://variety.com/lists/abby-ajayi-kerry-condon-rosalia-international-women-impact-report/ |access-date=2023-03-09 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=16 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230316123743/https://variety.com/lists/abby-ajayi-kerry-condon-rosalia-international-women-impact-report/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 8 March, Anitta was once again highlighted by international media, being elected by [[Bloomberg News|Bloomberg Línea]]  as one of the women with the most impact in 2023, alongside names like [[Shakira]], [[Karol G]] and others.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Las 50 mujeres de impacto en América Latina en 2023 |url=https://www.bloomberglinea.com/especiales/50-mujeres-latinoamerica-2023/ |access-date=2023-03-09 |website=Bloomberg Línea |language=es |archive-date=8 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230308183705/https://www.bloomberglinea.com/especiales/50-mujeres-latinoamerica-2023/ |url-status=live }}</ref> This honor reinforces the relevance and commitment of the artist to themes such as female empowerment and diversity, as well as highlighting her artistic talent. On 9 March, she was confirmed as part of the cast of the seventh season of the popular Spanish [[Netflix series]], [[Elite (TV series)|''Élite'']].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=2023-03-09 |title=Netflix's Elité: Anitta joins the cast for season 7 |url=https://www.gaytimes.co.uk/culture/netflixs-elite-anitta-joins-the-cast-for-season-7/ |access-date=2023-03-09 |website=GAY TIMES |language=en-GB |archive-date=9 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230309163255/https://www.gaytimes.co.uk/culture/netflixs-elite-anitta-joins-the-cast-for-season-7/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=David |title=Anitta will participate in the 7th season of Elite on Netflix |url=https://techmarkup.com/anitta-will-participate-in-the-7th-season-of-elite-on-netflix/ |access-date=2023-03-09 |website=Tech Markup |language=en-US |archive-date=9 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230309163255/https://techmarkup.com/anitta-will-participate-in-the-7th-season-of-elite-on-netflix/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 12 March, Anitta and [[Jão]] released their first collaboration, "Pilantra",<ref>{{Cite web |title=Jão lança 'Pilantra', primeiro feat com Anitta: 'Junção dos nossos universos' |url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/noticia/2023/03/13/jao-lanca-pilantra-primeiro-feat-com-anitta-juncao-dos-nossos-universos.ghtml |access-date=2023-03-14 |website=G1 |date=13 March 2023 |language=pt-br |archive-date=14 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230314192031/https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/noticia/2023/03/13/jao-lanca-pilantra-primeiro-feat-com-anitta-juncao-dos-nossos-universos.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> which debuted at the top of all streaming platforms in Brazil, occupying the 1st position in [[iTunes]], [[YouTube Music|YouTube]], [[Apple Music]] and the 4th position on Spotify Brazil and the 28th position in [[Portugal]]. The song also achieved the highest debut of a pop song on the Spotify Brazil Charts in 2023, with 1,162,003 streams.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta estreia nova música com mais de 1,1 milhão de streams em 24 horas |url=https://gshow.globo.com/tudo-mais/pop/noticia/anitta-estreia-nova-musica-com-mais-de-11-milhao-de-streams-em-24-horas.ghtml |access-date=2023-03-15 |website=gshow |date=14 March 2023 |language=pt-br |archive-date=15 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230315055512/https://gshow.globo.com/tudo-mais/pop/noticia/anitta-estreia-nova-musica-com-mais-de-11-milhao-de-streams-em-24-horas.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Sabino |first=Ana |date=2023-03-14 |title=Jão lança "PILANTRA", em parceria com Anitta e estreia em 4 lugar no Spotify |url=https://www.latinosbrasil.com/jao-lanca-pilantra-em-parceria-com-anitta-e-estreia-em-4-lugar-no-spotify/ |access-date=2023-03-15 |website=Latinos Brasil |language=pt-BR |archive-date=15 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230315055512/https://www.latinosbrasil.com/jao-lanca-pilantra-em-parceria-com-anitta-e-estreia-em-4-lugar-no-spotify/ |url-status=live }}</ref> With this, Anitta reached her 34th entry in the top 5 most listened-to songs in Brazil.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-03-14 |title=Em #4 no Spotify, Jão tem a maior estreia da carreira com "Pilantra" |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/4-spotify-jao-anitta-estreia-pilantra/ |access-date=2023-03-14 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=14 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230314203545/https://portalpopline.com.br/4-spotify-jao-anitta-estreia-pilantra/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 13 March, the singer received two nominations at the [[Latin American Music Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Univision |title=Nominados Latin American Music Awards 2023: Lista completa de artistas |url=https://www.univision.com/shows/latin-american-music-awards/latin-american-music-awards-2023-lista-completa-nominados |access-date=2023-03-14 |website=Univision |language=spanish |archive-date=15 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230315215858/https://www.univision.com/shows/latin-american-music-awards/latin-american-music-awards-2023-lista-completa-nominados |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 4 April 2023, Anitta terminated her contracts with [[Warner Music Group]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-04-04 |title=Anitta exits Warner Music after claiming she'd 'auction off' organs to end deal |url=https://nypost.com/2023/04/04/anitta-exits-warner-music-after-claiming-shed-auction-off-organs-to-end-deal/ |access-date=2023-04-06 |language=en-US |archive-date=6 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230406145833/https://nypost.com/2023/04/04/anitta-exits-warner-music-after-claiming-shed-auction-off-organs-to-end-deal/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 20 April, the [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] reported that the Brazilian singer has signed a contract with [[Republic Records]] in partnership with [[Universal Music Latin Entertainment]].<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Aswad |first1=Shirley Halperin, Jem |last2=Halperin |first2=Shirley |last3=Aswad |first3=Jem |date=2023-04-20 |title=Anitta Signs With Republic Records (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2023/music/news/anitta-signs-republic-records-1235590261/ |access-date=2023-04-20 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=20 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230420211014/https://variety.com/2023/music/news/anitta-signs-republic-records-1235590261/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Aswad |first=Jem |date=2023-04-27 |title=It's Official: Anitta Is a Republic Recording Artist |url=https://variety.com/2023/music/news/anitta-signs-republic-recording-artist-1235597171/ |access-date=2023-11-29 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=9 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230509035028/https://variety.com/2023/music/news/anitta-signs-republic-recording-artist-1235597171/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 1 May, the singer attended her third [[Met Gala]], representing the brand [[Marc Jacobs]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta escolhe look assinado por Marc Jacobs e jóias Tiffany para o MET Gala 2023 |url=https://extra.globo.com/estilo/noticia/2023/05/anitta-escolhe-look-assinado-por-marc-jacobs-e-joias-tiffany-para-o-met-gala-2023.ghtml |access-date=2023-05-12 |website=extra |date=May 2023 |language=pt-br |archive-date=12 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230512182454/https://extra.globo.com/estilo/noticia/2023/05/anitta-escolhe-look-assinado-por-marc-jacobs-e-joias-tiffany-para-o-met-gala-2023.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> and according to data from [[Sprinklr]], Anitta was the third most mentioned celebrity during the red carpet.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Reply |first=Zara |title=JENNIE Topped NetBase Quid's List of the Top 5 Most Mentioned Women at the 2023 Met Gala – BLACKPINK CAFÉ |url=https://blackpink.cafe/news/jennie-topped-netbase-quids-list-of-the-top-5-most-mentioned-women-at-the-2023-met-gala/ |access-date=2023-05-12 |language=en-US |archive-date=12 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230512182457/https://blackpink.cafe/news/jennie-topped-netbase-quids-list-of-the-top-5-most-mentioned-women-at-the-2023-met-gala/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 25 May, the Brazilian singer joined forces with Spanish singer RVFV and Italian singer and rapper [[Sfera Ebbasta]] to release the bilingual song, in Spanish and Italian, "Capitán".<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=2023-05-26 |title="Capitán": l'unione esplosiva di RVFV, Sfera Ebbasta e Anitta per rompere le frontiere musicali |url=https://www.shmag.it/show/musica/26_05_2023/capitan-lunione-esplosiva-di-rvfv-sfera-ebbasta-e-anitta-per-rompere-le-frontiere-musicali/ |access-date=2023-05-26 |website=SH Magazine |language=it |archive-date=26 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230526161615/https://www.shmag.it/show/musica/26_05_2023/capitan-lunione-esplosiva-di-rvfv-sfera-ebbasta-e-anitta-per-rompere-le-frontiere-musicali/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-05-26 |title=Anitta, RVFV e Sfera Ebbasta celebram a cultura com funk italiano em 'CAPITÁN'; veja! |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-rvfv-sfera-ebbasta-funk-capitan/ |access-date=2023-05-26 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=26 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230526161613/https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-rvfv-sfera-ebbasta-funk-capitan/ |url-status=live }}</ref> This is Anitta's third song singing in Italian.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Dourado |first=Catharina |date=2023-05-25 |title=Anitta, RVFV e Sfera Ebbasta celebram Brasil, Espanha e Itália no clipe de "Capitán" |url=https://www.papelpop.com/2023/05/anitta-rvfv-e-sfera-ebbasta-celebram-brasil-espanha-e-italia-no-clipe-de-capitan/ |access-date=2023-05-26 |website=PAPELPOP |language=pt-br |archive-date=26 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230526161615/https://www.papelpop.com/2023/05/anitta-rvfv-e-sfera-ebbasta-celebram-brasil-espanha-e-italia-no-clipe-de-capitan/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 10 June, Anitta became the first artist from [[South America]] to perform at the [[2023 UEFA Champions League final|UEFA Champions League Final]] Kick Off Show by [[Pepsi]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-06-10 |title=Com homenagem a Vini Jr, Anitta se apresenta na abertura da final da Champions League 2022/23 |url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/liga-dos-campeoes/noticia/2023/06/10/anitta-se-apresenta-na-abertura-da-final-da-champions-league-202223.ghtml |access-date=2023-06-14 |website=ge |language=pt-br |archive-date=14 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230614014745/https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/liga-dos-campeoes/noticia/2023/06/10/anitta-se-apresenta-na-abertura-da-final-da-champions-league-202223.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Iluyomade |first=Simi |date=2023-05-24 |title=Anitta is Ready to Take the World by Storm |url=https://versus.uk.com/2023/05/anitta-is-ready-to-take-the-world-by-storm/ |access-date=2023-05-24 |website=VERSUS |language=en-GB |archive-date=24 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230524113928/https://versus.uk.com/2023/05/anitta-is-ready-to-take-the-world-by-storm/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The singer took the stage at the [[Atatürk Olympic Stadium]] in [[Istanbul]], [[Turkey]], in front of more than 71,412 supporters and an audience of over 700 million people,<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-06-10 |title=Anitta mira a Europa com show na Champions League, palco que já foi de Dua Lipa |url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2023/06/anitta-mira-a-europa-com-show-na-champions-league-palco-que-ja-foi-de-dua-lipa.shtml |access-date=2023-06-14 |website=Folha de S.Paulo |language=pt-BR |archive-date=14 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230614014744/https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2023/06/anitta-mira-a-europa-com-show-na-champions-league-palco-que-ja-foi-de-dua-lipa.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-06-10 |title=Anitta na final da Champions: show pode impulsionar a carreira da cantora na Europa? |url=https://exame.com/pop/anitta-final-champions-estourar-europa/ |access-date=2023-06-14 |website=Exame |language=pt-br |archive-date=14 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230614014745/https://exame.com/pop/anitta-final-champions-estourar-europa/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Rodri beschert ManCity den ersehnten Champions-League-Titel |url=https://www.kicker.de/mancity-gegen-inter-2023-champions-league-4839326/spielinfo |access-date=2023-06-14 |website=kicker |language=de-DE |archive-date=14 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230614014744/https://www.kicker.de/mancity-gegen-inter-2023-champions-league-4839326/spielinfo |url-status=live }}</ref> surpassing the global viewership of the [[Super Bowl halftime show]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-06-10 |title=Zapping - Cristina Padiglione: Alcance de Anitta na Champions supera intervalo do Super Bowl |url=https://f5.folha.uol.com.br/colunistas/cristina-padiglione/2023/06/alcance-de-anitta-na-champions-supera-intervalo-do-super-bowl.shtml |access-date=2023-06-14 |website=F5 |language=pt-BR |archive-date=14 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230614014744/https://f5.folha.uol.com.br/colunistas/cristina-padiglione/2023/06/alcance-de-anitta-na-champions-supera-intervalo-do-super-bowl.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref> During her performance, she showcased the song "[[Envolver]]" and debuted the first single, titled "[[Funk Rave]]", from her sixth studio album, which also marks her debut on [[Republic Records]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-06-11 |title=Anitta lança o single 'Funk rave' em 22 de junho |url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/blog/mauro-ferreira/post/2023/06/11/anitta-lanca-o-single-funk-rave-em-22-de-junho.ghtml |access-date=2023-06-14 |website=G1 |language=pt-br |archive-date=12 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230612113442/https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/blog/mauro-ferreira/post/2023/06/11/anitta-lanca-o-single-funk-rave-em-22-de-junho.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta Announces New Single 'Funk Rave' |url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2023-06-11-anitta-announces-new-single-funk-rave/ |access-date=2023-06-14 |website=iHeart |language=en |archive-date=14 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230614014745/https://www.iheart.com/content/2023-06-11-anitta-announces-new-single-funk-rave/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 14 June, [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] reported that Anitta parted ways with her longtime manager, [[Brandon Silverstein]], the founder/CEO of S10 Entertainment.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Aswad |first1=Thania Garcia, Jem |last2=Garcia |first2=Thania |last3=Aswad |first3=Jem |date=2023-06-14 |title=Anitta Parts Ways With Longtime Manager Brandon Silverstein |url=https://variety.com/2023/music/news/anitta-parts-ways-brandon-silverstein-management-1235644615/ |access-date=2023-06-16 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=16 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230616224342/https://variety.com/2023/music/news/anitta-parts-ways-brandon-silverstein-management-1235644615/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Then, on 16 June, Variety announced that Rebeca León, founder/CEO of Lionfish Entertainment and former manager of [[J Balvin]] and [[Rosalía]], became Anitta's new manager.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Garcia |first=Thania |date=2023-06-16 |title=Anitta Joins Forces With Former Rosalía and J Balvin Manager Rebeca León |url=https://variety.com/2023/music/news/anitta-new-manager-rebeca-leon-1235647119/ |access-date=2023-06-16 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=16 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230616224343/https://variety.com/2023/music/news/anitta-new-manager-rebeca-leon-1235647119/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 22 June, the singer released the first lead single, "[[Funk Rave]]", from her upcoming album under [[Republic Records]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Garcia |first=Thania |date=2023-06-23 |title=Anitta Throws a Joyful 'Funk Rave' in Video for 'Intentionally International' New Single |url=https://variety.com/2023/music/news/anitta-funk-rave-new-single-video-1235651283/ |access-date=2023-06-25 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=25 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230625064711/https://variety.com/2023/music/news/anitta-funk-rave-new-single-video-1235651283/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The track debuted, allowing Anitta to extend her record as the artist with the highest number of songs at number one on [[Apple Music]] and [[iTunes]] in Brazil, making "Funk Rave" her 29th and 88th song, respectively, to achieve this feat.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-04-14 |title=Anitta estende recorde histórico e emplaca 70 faixas no topo do iTunes Brasil |url=https://portalfamosos.com.br/anitta-estende-recorde-historico-e-emplaca-70-faixas-no-topo-do-itunes-brasil/ |access-date=2023-06-25 |website=Portal Famosos Brasil {{!}} PFBR |language=pt-BR |archive-date=5 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220705073630/https://portalfamosos.com.br/anitta-estende-recorde-historico-e-emplaca-70-faixas-no-topo-do-itunes-brasil/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In [[Spotify]] Brazil, it debuted in the top 5, becoming the artist's 35th song to reach that position, maintaining her record as the artist with the most songs to enter the top 5 on Spotify Brazil.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Minas |first=Estado de |date=2023-06-24 |title=Com 'Funk Rave', Anitta quebra próprio recorde no Spotify |url=https://www.em.com.br/app/noticia/cultura/2023/06/24/interna_cultura,1511876/com-funk-rave-anitta-quebra-proprio-recorde-no-spotify.shtml |access-date=2023-06-25 |website=Estado de Minas |language=pt-BR |archive-date=25 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230625044306/https://www.em.com.br/app/noticia/cultura/2023/06/24/interna_cultura,1511876/com-funk-rave-anitta-quebra-proprio-recorde-no-spotify.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref> The release garnered a debut of 2,110,515 unfiltered streams on Spotify and reached the #85 position on the global Spotify chart, keeping the singer as the Brazilian artist with the highest debut on Spotify Global for the seventh consecutive year.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-06-24 |title=Anitta estreia 'Funk Rave' no Top 5 do Spotify Brasil com recorde no Global |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-estreia-funk-rave-no-top-5-do-spotify-brasil-com-recorde-no-global/ |access-date=2023-06-25 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=25 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230625044254/https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-estreia-funk-rave-no-top-5-do-spotify-brasil-com-recorde-no-global/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-06-24 |title=Com 'Funk Rave', Anitta quebra próprio recorde de maior estreia por um artista brasileiro no Spotify |url=https://vogue.globo.com/celebridades/noticia/2023/06/com-funk-rave-anitta-quebra-proprio-recorde-de-maior-estreia-por-um-artista-brasileiro-no-spotify.ghtml |access-date=2023-06-25 |website=Vogue |language=pt-br |archive-date=25 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230625044306/https://vogue.globo.com/celebridades/noticia/2023/06/com-funk-rave-anitta-quebra-proprio-recorde-de-maior-estreia-por-um-artista-brasileiro-no-spotify.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> The music video also premiered on the [[YouTube]] trending charts in several countries.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-06-24 |title=Funk Rave: Anitta quebra próprio recorde de maior estreia por um artista brasileiro no Spotify |url=https://f5.folha.uol.com.br/celebridades/2023/06/funk-rave-anitta-quebra-proprio-recorde-de-maior-estreia-por-um-artista-brasileiro-no-spotify.shtml |access-date=2023-06-25 |website=F5 |language=pt-BR |archive-date=25 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230625044306/https://f5.folha.uol.com.br/celebridades/2023/06/funk-rave-anitta-quebra-proprio-recorde-de-maior-estreia-por-um-artista-brasileiro-no-spotify.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref> On 17 August, Anitta released a "bumper," comprising three singles from her upcoming studio album (Funk Rave, Casi Casi and Used to Be). The project is titled "Funk Generation: A Favela Love Story".<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Madarang |first=Charisma |date=2023-08-18 |title=Anitta's 'Funk Generation: A Favela Story' Showcases Brazilian Funk |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/anitta-funk-generation-a-favela-story-1234808678/ |access-date=2023-08-19 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |archive-date=19 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230819013557/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/anitta-funk-generation-a-favela-story-1234808678/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-08-18 |title=Anitta Drops Funk Generation: A Favela Love Story: Stream |url=https://consequence.net/2023/08/anitta-funk-generation-stream/ |access-date=2023-08-19 |language=en-US |archive-date=19 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230819013557/https://consequence.net/2023/08/anitta-funk-generation-stream/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 12 September, Anitta won the [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Latin|Best Latin]] category at the [[Vmas|VMAs]] for the second consecutive year, with [[Brazilian Funk]], "[[Funk Rave]]", establishing herself as the only female Latin artist to receive this honor, as well as the only artist to win with a solo song.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Atkinson |first=Katie |date=2023-09-13 |title=Here Are the 2023 MTV VMAs Winners: Full List |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/2023-mtv-vmas-winners-list-1235411480/ |access-date=2023-09-13 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=13 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230913050201/https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/2023-mtv-vmas-winners-list-1235411480/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Grein |first=Paul |date=2023-09-13 |title=Taylor Swift, Nicki Minaj & More Record-Setters at 2023 MTV VMAs |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/taylor-swift-nicki-minaj-mtv-vmas-records-1235411276/ |access-date=2023-09-13 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US |archive-date=13 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230913051138/https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/taylor-swift-nicki-minaj-mtv-vmas-records-1235411276/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In addition to performing songs from her "Funk Generation: A Favela Love Story" project, and a snippet of her upcoming song, "Grip",<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Mier |first=Tomás |date=2023-09-13 |title=Anitta Transforms the 2023 VMAs Into a 'Funk Rave' With Help From Tomorrow X Together |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/anitta-performs-funk-rave-2023-mtv-vmas-1234820923/ |access-date=2023-09-13 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |archive-date=13 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230913210750/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/anitta-performs-funk-rave-2023-mtv-vmas-1234820923/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-13 |title=Anitta Performs "Funk Rave" and "Used to Be" at VMAs 2023: Watch |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/anitta-performs-funk-rave-and-used-to-be-at-vmas-2023-watch/ |access-date=2023-09-13 |website=Pitchfork |language=en-US |archive-date=24 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230924002616/https://pitchfork.com/news/anitta-performs-funk-rave-and-used-to-be-at-vmas-2023-watch/ |url-status=live }}</ref> the singer took to the main stage once again to perform alongside the [[Koreans|South Korean]] group [[Tomorrow X Together]] in their live debut for "[[Back for More (Tomorrow X Together and Anitta Song)|Back for More]]", the artist's first collaboration with [[K-pop music]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-13 |title=Tomorrow X Together and Anitta Made VMAs History With Their Live Debut of "Back for More" |url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/music/a45085049/tomorrow-x-together-anitta-2023-vmas-performance/ |access-date=2023-09-13 |website=Cosmopolitan |language=en-US |archive-date=13 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230913191941/https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/music/a45085049/tomorrow-x-together-anitta-2023-vmas-performance/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Daly |first=Rhian |date=2023-09-13 |title=Watch Tomorrow X Together and Anitta debut infectious collaboration 'Back For More' |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/tomorrow-x-together-anitta-debut-back-for-more-mtv-vmas-3497000 |access-date=2023-09-13 |website=NME |language=en-GB |archive-date=13 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230913035115/https://www.nme.com/news/music/tomorrow-x-together-anitta-debut-back-for-more-mtv-vmas-3497000 |url-status=live }}</ref>

With "[[Back for More (Tomorrow X Together and Anitta Song)|Back for More]]" Anitta extended her record as a Brazilian artist with the biggest peak on the [[Melon (online music service)|MelOn]] and [[Bugs! (streaming service)|Bugs!]] charts, the biggest music platforms in [[South Korea]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta |url=http://www.melon.com/artist/timeline.htm?artistId=775668 |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=멜론 |language=ko |archive-date=4 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240204191700/https://www.melon.com/artist/timeline.htm?artistId=775668 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Marinho |first1=Vinicius |last2=TI |first2=Brainatwork |date=2023-09-16 |title="Back For More" do TXT e Anitta debuta no Spotify Global |url=https://poptivo.com.br/back-for-more-do-txt-e-anitta-debuta-no-spotify-global/ |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=Poptivo |language=pt-BR |archive-date=4 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240204191820/https://poptivo.com.br/back-for-more-do-txt-e-anitta-debuta-no-spotify-global/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The singer also debuted with the song in the top 10 on the biggest streaming platform in [[China]], [[QQ Music]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta - QQ音乐-千万正版音乐海量无损曲库新歌热歌天天畅听的高品质音乐平台！ |url=https://y.qq.com/n/ryqq/singer/001F2ZoZ3UfEYX |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=y.qq.com |archive-date=7 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107161021/https://y.qq.com/n/ryqq/singer/001F2ZoZ3UfEYX |url-status=live }}</ref> The artist also entered the official charts in [[Indonesia]], South Korea, China and the [[United Kingdom]] for the first time in her career, being the first artist from Brazil to achieve this feat.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Official Charts |website=[[Official Charts Company|Official Charts]] |url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/tomorrow-x-togetheranitta/ |access-date=7 January 2024 |archive-date=7 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107161017/https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/tomorrow-x-togetheranitta/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The song also reached the top of iTunes Global and European iTunes.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-15 |title=Anitta conquista seu primeiro #1 no iTunes Global |url=https://bcharts.com.br/t/anitta-conquista-seu-primeiro-1-no-itunes-global/65247 |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=BCharts Fórum |language=pt-BR |archive-date=4 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240204191830/https://bcharts.com.br/t/anitta-conquista-seu-primeiro-1-no-itunes-global/65247 |url-status=live }}</ref> The singer became the first Latin artist in history to reach #1 on the APMA Charts (Overseas) with "[[Back for More (Tomorrow X Together and Anitta Song)|Back for More]]", a ranking for the one of China's biggest awards, the ''Asian Pop Music Awards'', she was the first Latin artist in history to be nominated for this award in "Best Collaboration" and "Best Producer".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sai |first=Aishwarya |date=2023-11-30 |title=From BTS' V to Straykids: A complete list of KPop nominations at Asian Pop Music Awards 2023 |url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/pop-culture/from-bts-v-straykids-a-complete-list-kpop-nominations-asian-pop-music-awards-2023 |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=www.sportskeeda.com |language=en-us |archive-date=2 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231202223001/https://www.sportskeeda.com/pop-culture/from-bts-v-straykids-a-complete-list-kpop-nominations-asian-pop-music-awards-2023 |url-status=live }}</ref> Anitta also became the first Latin artist to win one of China's biggest awards, the ''China Year End Awards'' in the "Best Selling Latin Single" category with "Back for More".<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-26 |title=China Year End Awards 2023: BTS' Jungkook, BLACKPINK's Jisoo win big, check out full list of winners |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/music/china-year-end-awards-2023-bts-jungkook-blackpinks-jisoo-win-big-check-out-full-list-of-winners-101703591553672.html |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=Hindustan Times |language=en |archive-date=6 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240106185234/https://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/music/china-year-end-awards-2023-bts-jungkook-blackpinks-jisoo-win-big-check-out-full-list-of-winners-101703591553672.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 23 September, Anitta was one of the headliners at the [[Global Citizen Festival]] in [[New York City|New York]], performing for more than 60 thousand people in [[Central Park]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-23 |title=Anitta se apresenta no Global Citizen Festival com as cores da bandeira do Brasil |url=https://gshow.globo.com/tudo-mais/tv-e-famosos/noticia/anitta-se-apresenta-no-global-citizen-festival-em-nova-york.ghtml |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=gshow |language=pt-br |archive-date=16 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231016025606/https://gshow.globo.com/tudo-mais/tv-e-famosos/noticia/anitta-se-apresenta-no-global-citizen-festival-em-nova-york.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> On 20 October, Anitta debuted as an actress in the Spanish [[Netflix series]], [[Elite (TV series)|Elite]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=A verdade não dita sobre a atuação de Anitta na série 'Elite' {{!}} Tela Plana |url=https://veja.abril.com.br/coluna/tela-plana/a-verdade-nao-dita-sobre-a-atuacao-de-anitta-na-serie-elite/ |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=VEJA |language=pt-BR |archive-date=7 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107161522/https://veja.abril.com.br/coluna/tela-plana/a-verdade-nao-dita-sobre-a-atuacao-de-anitta-na-serie-elite/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The series debuted in the top 10 globally and in 40 countries on [[Netflix]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=themusicjournalbrazil |title=Netflix lista as 10 séries internacionais mais vistas em outubro |url=https://www.terra.com.br/diversao/entre-telas/netflix-lista-as-10-series-internacionais-mais-vistas-em-outubro,4105a11ddcb0c7440d27e28558c54a87p07mtdm9.html |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=Terra |language=pt-BR |archive-date=7 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107163025/https://www.terra.com.br/diversao/entre-telas/netflix-lista-as-10-series-internacionais-mais-vistas-em-outubro,4105a11ddcb0c7440d27e28558c54a87p07mtdm9.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Torres |first=Leonardo |date=2023-10-24 |title="Elite" em queda livre: série perde audiência e fica pra trás em ranking de popularidade. |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/elite-queda-serie-perde-audiencia/ |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=7 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107161522/https://portalpopline.com.br/elite-queda-serie-perde-audiencia/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 5 November, Anitta won for the second consecutive year in the "[[MTV Europe Music Award for Best Latin|Best Latin]]" category at the [[MTV Europe Music Awards|Europe Music Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Teixeira |first=Rafael Farias |title=MTV EMAs 2023 revela vencedores; Anitta leva na categoria Melhor Artista Latino |url=https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/entretenimento/mtv-emas-2023-revela-vencedores-anitta-leva-na-categoria-melhor-artista-latino/ |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=CNN Brasil |date=7 November 2023 |archive-date=13 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231113045227/https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/entretenimento/mtv-emas-2023-revela-vencedores-anitta-leva-na-categoria-melhor-artista-latino/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Making the singer the most awarded artist in this category.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-05 |title=MTV EMA 2023: Taylor Swift, Anitta e Matuê estão entre vencedores da premiação |url=https://glamour.globo.com/lifestyle/noticia/2023/11/mtv-ema-2023-taylor-anitta-e-matue-estao-entre-vencedores-da-premiacao.ghtml |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=Glamour |language=pt-br |archive-date=4 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240204191822/https://glamour.globo.com/lifestyle/noticia/2023/11/mtv-ema-2023-taylor-anitta-e-matue-estao-entre-vencedores-da-premiacao.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> On 25 November, the singer was the headliner of the biggest music festival in [[Colombia]], Megaland Music Fest, performing for more than 40 thousand people.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Gaitán |first=Por Iván |date=2023-11-26 |title=La sensual presentación de Anitta y Greeicy en Megaland que calentó las redes sociales |url=https://www.infobae.com/colombia/2023/11/26/la-sensual-presentacion-de-anitta-y-greeicy-en-megaland-que-calento-las-redes-sociales/ |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=infobae |language=es-ES |archive-date=13 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231213190328/https://www.infobae.com/colombia/2023/11/26/la-sensual-presentacion-de-anitta-y-greeicy-en-megaland-que-calento-las-redes-sociales/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 2 December, the singer was one of the headliners at the Mega Bash 2023 festival in [[New Jersey]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Carvalho |first=Matheus de |date=2023-12-05 |title=Mulher tenta sair de penetra em foto de Anitta; veja a reação da cantora!. |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/mulher-tenta-sair-penetra-foto-anitta-veja-reacao/ |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=7 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107161017/https://portalpopline.com.br/mulher-tenta-sair-penetra-foto-anitta-veja-reacao/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 7 December, the [[Mexicans|mexican]] singer [[Peso Pluma]] and Anitta released the song "[[Bellakeo]]", the song reached the top 10 of Spotify Global and entered the top 50 of all [[Latin America|Latin American countries]] and the [[United States]], in addition to entering the global top 50 on Apple Music and iTunes.<ref>{{Cite web |last=themusicjournalbrazil |title=Anitta e Peso Pluma chegam ao Top 10 Global no Spotify |url=https://www.terra.com.br/diversao/musica/anitta-e-peso-pluma-chegam-ao-top-10-global-no-spotify,3e60cee81e92f1221a80de07aab0b43dq2stjfz2.html |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=Terra |language=pt-BR |archive-date=2 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240102123639/https://www.terra.com.br/diversao/musica/anitta-e-peso-pluma-chegam-ao-top-10-global-no-spotify,3e60cee81e92f1221a80de07aab0b43dq2stjfz2.html}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/entretenimento/anitta-emplaca-hit-no-top-10-global-do-spotify-e-comemora-e-muito-bom-ser-eu/ |title=Anitta emplaca hit no Top 10 global do Spotify e comemora: "E muito bom ser eu" |last=Ferreira |first=Caroline |date=28 December 2023 |language=pt-br |website=CNN Brasil |access-date=May 4, 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240104153212/https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/entretenimento/anitta-emplaca-hit-no-top-10-global-do-spotify-e-comemora-e-muito-bom-ser-eu/ |archive-date=January 4, 2024}}</ref> With the song Anitta reached the top of Brazilian music streaming platforms, extending the singer's record as the artist with the most #1 on these streaming services.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-20 |title=Com 'BELLAKEO', Anitta celebra sétima música de sucesso global: 'Muito feliz' |url=https://gshow.globo.com/tudo-mais/tv-e-famosos/noticia/com-bellakeo-anitta-celebra-setima-musica-de-sucesso-global-muito-feliz.ghtml |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=gshow |language=pt-br |archive-date=4 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240204191816/https://gshow.globo.com/tudo-mais/tv-e-famosos/noticia/com-bellakeo-anitta-celebra-setima-musica-de-sucesso-global-muito-feliz.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> The song also debuted simultaneously on Spotify's viral songs chart in 50 countries.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Lagoas |first=Renato |title="BELLAKEO" de Anitta e Peso Pluma retorna ao Top 10 do Spotify |url=https://inmagazine.ig.com.br/categoria/musica/BELLAKEO-de-Anitta-e-Peso-Pluma-retorna-ao-Top-10-do-Spotify |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=inmagazine.ig.com.br |date=2 January 2024 |language=pt-br |archive-date=4 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240204191819/https://inmagazine.ig.com.br/musica/categoria-musica-BELLAKEO-de-Anitta-e-Peso-Pluma-retorna-ao-Top-10-do-Spotify/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In addition to extending Anitta's third entry on the [[Hot 100]], which made the singer the Brazilian woman, and the third overall, with the most entries in the history of the [[Billboard Hot 100]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=themusicjournalbrazil |title=Anitta é a brasileira com mais entradas na Hot 100 da Billboard |url=https://www.terra.com.br/diversao/musica/anitta-e-a-brasileira-com-mais-entradas-na-hot-100-da-billboard,c5b3bcc3b96b921f36b34046304c9668zi0zlbxn.html |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=Terra |language=pt-BR |archive-date=4 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240204191833/https://www.terra.com.br/diversao/musica/anitta-e-a-brasileira-com-mais-entradas-na-hot-100-da-billboard,c5b3bcc3b96b921f36b34046304c9668zi0zlbxn.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Sant'Ana |first=Manuela |date=2023-12-27 |title=Anitta se torna brasileira com mais entradas na Billboard; entenda |url=https://tracklist.com.br/anitta-billboard-hot-100/172779 |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=Tracklist |language=pt-BR |archive-date=3 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240103075229/https://tracklist.com.br/anitta-billboard-hot-100/172779 |url-status=live }}</ref> In addition to extending the record for the fifth consecutive year for a Brazilian artist with the biggest peak on spotify globally.<ref>{{Cite web |title='Bellakeo': Anitta emplaca hit no top 10 do Spotify Global e estende recorde na carreira |url=https://observatoriodosfamosos.uol.com.br/noticias/bellakeo-anitta-emplaca-hit-no-top-10-do-spotify-global-e-estende-recorde-na-carreira |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=observatoriodosfamosos.uol.com.br |date=28 December 2023 |archive-date=7 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107161018/https://observatoriodosfamosos.uol.com.br/noticias/bellakeo-anitta-emplaca-hit-no-top-10-do-spotify-global-e-estende-recorde-na-carreira |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Morais |first=Mariana |date=2023-12-28 |title=Anitta alcança Top 10 Global de novo e mostra choro de hater |url=https://www.correiobraziliense.com.br/colunistas/mariana-morais/2023/12/6776631-anitta-alcanca-top-10-global-de-novo-e-mostra-choro-de-hater.html |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=Mariana Morais |language=pt-BR |archive-date=28 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231228230902/https://www.correiobraziliense.com.br/colunistas/mariana-morais/2023/12/6776631-anitta-alcanca-top-10-global-de-novo-e-mostra-choro-de-hater.html |url-status=live }}</ref> On 10 December, Anitta performed at [[TikTok]] in the Mix 2023, the first edition of the platform's music festival, in [[Arizona]]. The festival was broadcast worldwide and broke the record for the most watched live with more than 33.5 million viewers and a crowd of 17 thousand people.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-08-16 |title=TikTok In The Mix Breaks Record for Biggest Ever LIVE Event on TikTok |url=https://newsroom.tiktok.com/en-us/tiktok-in-the-mix-breaks-record-for-biggest-ever-live-event-on-tiktok |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=Newsroom {{!}} TikTok |language=en-us |archive-date=26 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231226195703/https://newsroom.tiktok.com/en-us/tiktok-in-the-mix-breaks-record-for-biggest-ever-live-event-on-tiktok |url-status=live }}</ref> On 28 December,  the singer was the headliner at the Virada Salvador Festival, performing in front of more than 200 thousand people.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-29 |title=Com repertório dançante, Anitta agita público no primeiro dia do Festival Virada Salvador |url=https://g1.globo.com/ba/bahia/verao/noticia/2023/12/29/anitta-agita-publico-no-primeiro-dia-do-festival-virada-salvador.ghtml |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=G1 |language=pt-br |archive-date=7 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107163746/https://g1.globo.com/ba/bahia/verao/noticia/2023/12/29/anitta-agita-publico-no-primeiro-dia-do-festival-virada-salvador.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 6 January 2024, the singer started her [[Brazilian Carnival|carnival]] tour in 10 Brazilian cities. With all dates sold out,<ref>{{Cite web |last=JP |date=2023-10-26 |title=ENSAIOS DA ANITTA ESGOTA LOTES DE INGRESSOS EM MINUTOS |url=https://bahiaeconomica.com.br/wp/2023/10/26/ensaios-da-anitta-esgota-lotes-de-ingressos-em-minutos/ |access-date=2024-02-26 |website=Bahia Economica |language=pt-br |archive-date=26 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240226194123/https://bahiaeconomica.com.br/wp/2023/10/26/ensaios-da-anitta-esgota-lotes-de-ingressos-em-minutos/ |url-status=live }}</ref> the tour set a record for summer revenue in Brazil, with a profit of over 30 million reais.<ref>{{Cite web |last=themusicjournalbrazil |title='Ensaios da Anitta' deve bater recorde de faturamento |url=https://www.terra.com.br/diversao/carnaval/ensaios-da-anitta-deve-bater-recorde-de-faturamento,314a31adb3fb6a34d0cbbfc215d1fb93pe68xwan.html |access-date=2024-02-26 |website=Terra |language=pt-BR |archive-date=26 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240226194121/https://www.terra.com.br/diversao/carnaval/ensaios-da-anitta-deve-bater-recorde-de-faturamento,314a31adb3fb6a34d0cbbfc215d1fb93pe68xwan.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Carvalho |first=Matheus de |date=2024-01-22 |title="Ensaios da Anitta": Cantora bate recorde de faturamento e explica participações {{!}} |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/ensaios-da-anitta-cantora-bate-recorde-faturamento-explica-participacoes/ |access-date=2024-02-26 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR |archive-date=26 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240226194120/https://portalpopline.com.br/ensaios-da-anitta-cantora-bate-recorde-faturamento-explica-participacoes/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 17 February, Anitta closed the Brazilian Carnival, hosting a street block party for over 1 million people in the morning and performing at the opening show of the "Desfile das Campeãs" in honor of the 40 years of the [[Marquês de Sapucaí]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Dias |first=Ana Beatriz |title=Pós-Carnaval 2024: Anitta comanda bloco com multidão no centro do Rio; veja |url=https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/entretenimento/pos-carnaval-2024-anitta-comanda-bloco-com-multidao-no-centro-do-rio-veja/ |access-date=2024-02-26 |website=CNN Brasil |date=17 February 2024 |archive-date=26 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240226194121/https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/entretenimento/pos-carnaval-2024-anitta-comanda-bloco-com-multidao-no-centro-do-rio-veja/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Dias |first=Ana Beatriz |title=Sapucaí recebe show de Anitta, Alcione e Zeca Pagodinho neste sábado (17) |url=https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/entretenimento/sapucai-recebe-show-de-anitta-alcione-e-zeca-pagodinho-neste-sabado-17/ |access-date=2024-02-26 |website=CNN Brasil |date=17 February 2024 |archive-date=26 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240226194120/https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/entretenimento/sapucai-recebe-show-de-anitta-alcione-e-zeca-pagodinho-neste-sabado-17/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 22 February, Anitta performed twice at the [[Lo Nuestro Awards|Premios Lo Nuestro]], being the most talked-about artist of the edition on social media.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ismerim |first=Flávio |title=Veja as apresentações de Anitta no prêmio Lo Nuestro |url=https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/entretenimento/veja-as-apresentacoes-de-anitta-no-premio-lo-nuestro/ |access-date=2024-02-26 |website=CNN Brasil |date=23 February 2024 |archive-date=26 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240226194122/https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/entretenimento/veja-as-apresentacoes-de-anitta-no-premio-lo-nuestro/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-02-22 |title=Anitta chega ao Prêmio Lo Nuestro, em Miami |url=https://vogue.globo.com/celebridades/noticia/2024/02/anitta-chega-ao-premio-lo-nuestro-em-miami.ghtml |access-date=2024-02-26 |website=Vogue |language=pt-br |archive-date=26 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240226194120/https://vogue.globo.com/celebridades/noticia/2024/02/anitta-chega-ao-premio-lo-nuestro-em-miami.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> On 28 February, the singer performed at the largest festival in [[Latin America]], [[Viña del Mar International Song Festival|Viña del Mar]] in [[Chile]]. She closed the night and became the most talked-about artist on all social media platforms. She received the award for the Most Popular Artist of the edition and the [[Gaviota (award)|Silver Seagull]]. The singer was supposed to receive the [[Gaviota (award)|Golden Seagull]], but due to a miscommunication between the event organization and the singer's team, she left the stage before "[[El monstruo (audience)|''El Monstruo'']]" could present the award to her.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Macías |first=Emilia |date=2024-02-29 |title=Estaba en pijama: ¿por qué Anitta no recibió la Gaviota de Oro? |url=https://www.latercera.com/culto/2024/02/29/estaba-en-pijama-por-que-anitta-no-recibio-la-gaviota-de-oro/ |access-date=2024-02-29 |website=La Tercera |archive-date=29 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240229150113/https://www.latercera.com/culto/2024/02/29/estaba-en-pijama-por-que-anitta-no-recibio-la-gaviota-de-oro/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Hermosilla |first=Ignacio |date=2024-02-29 |title="Ay que mierda": Anitta se enteró que había Gaviota de oro en el backstage tras terminar show en Viña |url=https://www.biobiochile.cl/especial/vina/noticias/2024/02/29/ay-que-mierda-perdona-anitta-se-entero-que-habia-una-segunda-gaviota-en-el.shtml |access-date=2024-02-29 |website=BioBioChile - La Red de Prensa Más Grande de Chile |language=es |archive-date=29 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240229150021/https://www.biobiochile.cl/especial/vina/noticias/2024/02/29/ay-que-mierda-perdona-anitta-se-entero-que-habia-una-segunda-gaviota-en-el.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref>

Anitta and [[Peso Pluma]] performed "[[Bellakeo]]" on the main stage at [[Coachella 2024]] during the second weekend.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Garcia |first=Thania |date=2024-04-20 |title=Peso Pluma Welcomes Anitta, Eslabon Armado and More as Coachella Guests for Weekend 2 |url=https://variety.com/2024/music/news/peso-pluma-anitta-eslabon-armado-coachella-weekend-two-1235977179/ |access-date=2024-05-05 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=23 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240423045547/https://variety.com/2024/music/news/peso-pluma-anitta-eslabon-armado-coachella-weekend-two-1235977179/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 26 April, the singer released her sixth studio album, ''[[Funk Generation]]'', her first under her new label [[Republic Records]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Garcia |first=Thania |date=2024-03-22 |title=Anitta Announces New 'Funk Generation' Album, Drops Bad Gyal-Featuring 'Double Team' Single and Video |url=https://variety.com/2024/music/news/anitta-funk-generation-album-bad-gyal-double-team-1235949228/ |access-date=2024-05-02 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=8 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240408142353/https://variety.com/2024/music/news/anitta-funk-generation-album-bad-gyal-double-team-1235949228/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Maia |first=Felipe |date=2024-04-27 |title=Anitta Embraces Her Roots, But Could've Taken More Risks, On 'Funk Generation' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/anitta-funk-generation-review-1235011638/ |access-date=2024-05-02 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US |archive-date=2 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240502144059/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/anitta-funk-generation-review-1235011638/ |url-status=live }}</ref> All the songs from the album debuted in the Top 50 on Spotify Brazil, marking the second album by the artist to achieve this.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Alves |first=Naara |title="Funk Generation": Anitta domina o Spotify com seu novo álbum |url=https://lorena.r7.com/categoria/M%C3%BAsica/Funk-Generation-Anitta-domina-o-Spotify-com-seu-novo-album |access-date=2024-05-02 |website=lorena.r7.com |date=28 April 2024 |language=pt-br}}</ref> ''Funk Generation'' charted on Apple Music in over 65 countries, making it the Brazilian album with the widest global reach. Within just three days, the album accumulated 26 million streams on Spotify Brazil, setting a record for the biggest weekly debut by a Brazilian album on the platform in 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta conquista novo recorde com 'Funk Generation' no Spotify Brasi |url=https://www.michellemarie.com.br/bacanerrimo/anitta-conquista-novo-recorde-com-funk-generation-no-spotify-brasi.html |access-date=2024-05-02 |website=Michelle Marie - Navegue com estilo |language=pt-br}}</ref> Globally, the album debuted at second place on Spotify Global within four days, with notable debuts in the United States (8th place) and the [[United Kingdom]] (9th place).<ref>{{Cite web |last=Carvalho |first=Matheus de |date=2024-05-01 |title="Funk Generation": Anitta estreia o novo álbum em parada global do Spotify {{!}} #Noticias |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/funk-generation-anitta-estreia-album-parada-global-spotify/ |access-date=2024-05-02 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR}}</ref> Anitta broke her own record by becoming the first artist to have 100 songs reach number one on iTunes Brazil. The singer also extended her record as the artist with the most songs entering the top 10 on Spotify Brazil, with a total of 49 songs achieving this feat. Additionally, ''Funk Generation'' achieved the biggest debut for a Brazilian album on the charts in Portugal.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sousa |first=Silvana |date=2024-04-27 |title=Anitta bate recorde de streams com "Funk Generation" e desabafa |url=https://tracklist.com.br/anitta-recorde-funk-generation/182838 |access-date=2024-05-02 |website=Tracklist |language=pt-BR}}</ref>

On 2 May,  Anitta was honored alongside [[Shonda Rhimes]], [[Amy Schumer]], and [[Mariska Hargitay]] at the [[Variety (magazine)|Variety's Power of Women]] event, in recognition of her contribution to the music world and for representing the [[CUFA]] (Central Única das Favelas).<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Shanfeld |first1=Thania Garcia, Ethan |last2=Garcia |first2=Thania |last3=Shanfeld |first3=Ethan |date=2024-05-02 |title=Anitta Reflects on Dreaming Big in Brazil and Breaking the 'Rules' of Being a Woman: 'I Wanted to Shake My Ass. I Wanted to Be Free' |url=https://variety.com/2024/music/news/anitta-speech-power-of-women-1235988611/ |access-date=2024-05-02 |website=Variety |language=en-US}}</ref> On the same day, Anitta spoke as one of the delegates at [[Global Citizen (organization)|Global Citizen Now]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=themusicjournalbrazil |title=Anitta fala sobre cuidado com o planeta em evento |url=https://www.terra.com.br/diversao/anitta-fala-sobre-cuidado-com-o-planeta-em-evento,36cbbf1c30e1c7925bce40536170fc2b2odzjvat.html |access-date=2024-05-05 |website=Terra |language=pt-BR}}</ref> On 4 May, the singer made history as the final guest judge at the [[Ballroom dance|ballroom]], featured in the song "[[Vogue (Madonna song)|Vogue]]",<ref>{{Cite web |last=Grigori |first=Pedro |date=2024-05-05 |title=Madonna transforma show em ballroom e recebe Anitta no palco de Copacabana |url=https://www.correiobraziliense.com.br/diversao-e-arte/2024/05/6851150-madonna-transforma-show-em-ballroom-e-recebe-anitta-no-rio.html |access-date=2024-05-05 |website=Diversão e Arte |language=pt-BR}}</ref> during the grand finale of [[Madonna]]'s [[The Celebration Tour]], [[List of most-attended concerts|the largest solo artist concert ever held]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Kreps |first=Daniel |date=2024-05-05 |title=Madonna Closes Out Celebration Tour in Front of Record-Setting 1.6 Million Fans in Brazil |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/madonna-celebration-tour-record-setting-1-6-million-fans-brazil-1235015393/ |access-date=2024-05-05 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US}}</ref> The event took place in [[Copacabana, Rio de Janeiro|Copacabana]], gathering over 1.6 million people.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Madonna's Final Celebration Tour Stop in Rio de Janeiro Draws Record-Breaking Audience of 1.6 Million |url=https://people.com/madonna-celebration-tour-rio-de-janeiro-draws-record-audience-8643456 |access-date=2024-05-05 |website=Peoplemag |language=en}}</ref> On 18 May, the singer began her first entirely international tour to promote her sixth studio album, [[Funk Generation]]: [[Baile Funk Experience]]. The tour started in [[Mexico]] and will visit the [[United States]], [[Canada]], [[Colombia]], [[Peru]], [[Chile]], [[Argentina]], [[Germany]], the [[Netherlands]], [[England]], [[France]], [[Italy]], and will end in [[Spain]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Garcia |first=Thania |date=2024-05-22 |title=Anitta's 'Baile Funk Experience' Fulfills Its Promise With Sweltering U.S. Debut: Concert Review |url=https://variety.com/2024/music/news/anitta-baile-funk-experience-concert-review-1236012481/ |access-date=2024-05-24 |website=Variety |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Cano |first=Natalia |date=2024-05-19 |title=Anitta's Baile Funk Experience Tour Setlist: Here's Every Song From Her Kick-Off Show |url=https://www.billboard.com/lists/anitta-setlist-baile-funk-experience-tour-first-show/ |access-date=2024-05-24 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US}}</ref> On 24 May, Anitta appeared as a guest judge on the third episode of the [[RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars season 9|ninth season of RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars]], with the song "[[Banana (Anitta song)|Banana]]" featuring [[Becky G]] being the [[Lip sync|Lip Sync]] song.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ismerim |first=Flávio |title=Anitta elogia Pabllo e Gloria Groove durante participação em RuPaul's Drag Race |url=https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/entretenimento/anitta-elogia-pabllo-e-gloria-groove-durante-participacao-em-rupauls-drag-race/ |access-date=2024-05-24 |website=CNN Brasil|date=24 May 2024 }}</ref>

On 25 July, Anitta received an honor at the [[Premios Juventud]] for being an activist in the defense of [[LGBTQIA+ rights]], as well as being a defender of humanitarian causes and the protection of the [[Amazon rainforest]]. She is also an exponent of Brazilian pop and funk to the rest of the world.<ref>{{Cite web |last=LOS40 |date=2024-07-26 |title=Ganadores Premios Juventud 2024: Karol G y Peso Pluma arrasan en galardones y Anitta y Emilia en la alfombra {{!}} Música |url=https://los40.com/2024/07/26/ganadores-premios-juventud-2024-karol-g-y-peso-pluma-arrasan-en-galardones-y-anitta-y-emilia-en-la-alfombra/ |access-date=2024-07-26 |website=LOS40 |language=es-ES}}</ref> The singer was nominated in three categories at the [[2024 MTV Video Music Awards]], making her the most nominated Latin woman. She received two nominations for [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Latin|Best Latin]] for her songs "[[Bellakeo]]" and "[[Mil Veces]]", and one nomination for [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Editing|Best Editing]] for "Mil Veces".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Willman |first=Chris |date=2024-08-06 |title=Taylor Swift Leads MTV VMAs Nominations With 10, as Post Malone, Sabrina Carpenter, Ariana Grande and Eminem Also Get a Big Look |url=https://variety.com/2024/music/news/mtv-vmas-nominations-taylor-swift-post-malone-awards-1236096620/ |access-date=2024-08-06 |website=Variety |language=en-US}}</ref>

On 6 September, Anitta performed during the [[halftime show]] of the [[NFL International Series|NFL]] [[NFL Kickoff Game|Kickoff Game]] for the [[2024 NFL season|2024 regular season]], the first ever held in [[South America]]. The singer took the stage for an audience of over 55,000 at the [[Neo Química Arena]] in [[São Paulo]], with all tickets sold out.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-06 |title=Temperatura para jogo da NFL em SP pode estar mais baixa do que em Green Bay e Filadélfia |url=https://www.uol.com.br/esporte/ultimas-noticias/agencia/2024/09/06/temperatura-para-jogo-da-nfl-em-sp-pode-estar-mais-baixa-do-que-em-green-bay-e-filadelfia.htm |access-date=2024-09-07 |website=UOL |language=pt-br}}</ref> The performance occurred during the game between the [[Philadelphia Eagles]] and the [[Green Bay Packers]], marking the first time in history that a Week 1 NFL game was held outside the [[United States]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Raygoza |first=Isabela |date=2024-08-20 |title=Anitta Set to Perform at Historic NFL Halftime Show in São Paulo: 'It's Really a Dream Come True' |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/anitta-to-perform-nfl-halftime-show-sao-paulo-brazil-interview-1235756309/ |access-date=2024-09-07 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Garcia |first=Thania |date=2024-08-20 |title=Anitta to Headline the NFL's First Game in São Paulo |url=https://variety.com/2024/music/news/anitta-headline-nfl-game-sao-paulo-1236111604/#:~:text=The%20NFL%20has%20tapped%20Anitta,off%20to%20the%202024%20season. |access-date=2024-09-07 |website=Variety |language=en-US}}</ref> On 7 September, the singer made a surprise appearance at [[The Weeknd]]'s ''São Paulo Concert'', held at [[Morumbi Stadium]] in [[São Paulo]]. The two artists performed together the song "[[São Paulo (song)|São Paulo]]", from the singer-songwriter's album, ''[[Hurry Up Tomorrow]]'', a collaboration with her.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-08 |title=Anitta sobe ao palco de surpresa com The Weeknd durante show em São Paulo |url=https://gshow.globo.com/tudo-mais/pop/noticia/anitta-sobe-ao-palco-de-surpresa-e-lanca-musica-com-the-weeknd-durante-show-em-sao-paulo.ghtml |access-date=2024-09-08 |website=gshow |language=pt-br}}</ref> Anitta won the [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Latin|Best Latin]] award at the [[MTV Video Music Awards]] for the third consecutive year, with her song "[[Mil Veces]]", becoming the Latin female artist with the most awards overall.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Horowitz |first=Steven J. |date=2024-09-11 |title=Taylor Swift, Chappell Roan and Megan Thee Stallion Win Big at MTV Video Music Awards, Plus Full List of Winners |url=https://variety.com/2024/awards/news/2024-vmas-winners-list-mtv-1236141425/ |access-date=2024-09-12 |website=Variety |language=en-US}}</ref> With this achievement, she tied with [[J Balvin]], both now holding the record for the most Latin wins at the awards. Additionally, Anitta performed at the ceremony for the fourth consecutive year, delivering performances of the songs "Paradise" with [[Fat Joe]] and [[DJ Khaled]], "[[Alegría (Tiago PZK, Anitta and Emilia song)|Alegría]]" with [[Tiago PZK]], and "[[Savage Funk]]".<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Paul |first=Charisma Madarang, Larisha |date=2024-09-12 |title=Anitta Performs Party-Ready Medley With DJ Khaled, Fat Joe, and Tiago PZK at 2024 MTV VMAs |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/anitta-performance-2024-mtv-vma-awards-1235096363/ |access-date=2024-09-12 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US}}</ref> On 12 September, Anitta was nominated for the [[Billboard Latin Music Awards]] in the [[Billboard Latin Music Award for Hot Latin Songs Artist of the Year|Hot Latin Songs Artist of the Year, Female]]  category.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Ratner-Arias |first=Sigal |date=2024-09-12 |title=Karol G Tops 2024 Billboard Latin Music Awards Finalists: Complete List |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/billboard-latin-music-awards-2024-finalists-complete-list-1235772510/ |access-date=2024-09-21 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US}}</ref> On 17 September, the singer received two [[Latin Grammy Awards|Latin Grammy]] nominations: one in the Best Portuguese Language Urban Performance category for the song "Joga pra Lua," in collaboration with [[Pedro Sampaio]], and another for [[Latin Grammy Award for Record of the Year|Record of the Year]] with the song "[[Mil Veces|Mil Vezes]]".<ref>{{Cite web |title=Lista Completa de Nominaciones {{!}} Nominados Latin GRAMMY 2024 {{!}} LatinGRAMMY.com |url=https://www.latingrammy.com/premiacion/nominados-25a-entrega-anual-del-latin-grammy |access-date=2024-09-21 |website=www.latingrammy.com |language=es}}</ref> Additionally, with the song "[[La Tóxica (Alejandro Fernández and Anitta Song)|La Tóxica]]", in partnership with Mexican singer [[Alejandro Fernández]], Anitta set a record by becoming the first Brazilian to top the Billboard [[Regional Mexican Airplay]] chart, after the song accumulated 6.3 million impressions on U.S. radio during the week of 6 to 12 September, earning the title of "Biggest Gainer" of the week.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Brasil |first=Billboard |date=2024-09-18 |title=Anitta faz estreia inédita em chart mexicano da Billboard |url=https://billboard.com.br/anitta-chart-mexicano-billboard/ |access-date=2024-09-21 |website=billboard.com.br |language=pt-BR}}</ref> Anitta also stood out as the tenth solo female artist to reach the top of the chart, and as the fifth solo artist outside the [[Regional Mexican|regional mexican]] genre to achieve this number one position.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Bustios |first=Pamela |date=2024-09-17 |title=Anitta Becomes First Brazilian to Top a Regional Mexican Chart With Alejandro Fernández Collab 'La Tóxica' |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/anitta-first-brazilian-to-top-a-regional-mexican-chart-with-alejandro-fernandez-collab-la-toxica-1235778120/ |access-date=2024-09-21 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US}}</ref>

On 30 October, Anitta and [[The Weeknd]] released the collaboration "[[São Paulo (song)|São Paulo]]", a [[Brazilian funk]] track.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Strauss |first=Matthew |date=2024-10-31 |title=The Weeknd and Anitta Release Video for New Song "São Paulo" |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/the-weeknd-and-anitta-release-video-for-new-song-sao-paulo-watch/ |access-date=2024-11-01 |website=Pitchfork |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Mamo |first=Heran |date=2024-10-31 |title=The Weeknd & Anitta Deliver 'São Paulo' Song & Video: Stream It Now |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/the-weeknd-anitta-sao-paulo-video-song-1235814850/ |access-date=2024-11-01 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US}}</ref> The song debuted in the top 10 on [[Spotify]] Global, setting a new record for Anitta as the Brazilian artist with the most chart entries across multiple countries, appearing in 71 nations.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Araujo |first=Guilherme |date=2024-11-01 |title="São Paulo": funk de The Weeknd e Anitta estreia direto no Top 10 do Spotify Global |url=https://www.papelpop.com/2024/11/sao-paulo-funk-de-the-weeknd-e-anitta-estreia-direto-no-top-10-do-spotify-global/ |access-date=2024-11-01 |website=PAPELPOP |language=pt-br}}</ref> "São Paulo" also achieved the biggest debut for a Brazilian act in Spotify Global history and became the largest debut by a Latin artist in 2024, surpassing [[Bad Bunny]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-11-01 |title=Anitta comemora estreia de sucesso de 'São Paulo' resgatando mensagem sobre o Funk ser respeitado no mundo |url=https://gq.globo.com/cultura/musica/noticia/2024/11/anitta-comemora-estreia-de-sucesso-de-sao-paulo-resgatando-mensagem-sobre-sucesso-do-funk-no-mundo.ghtml |access-date=2024-11-01 |website=GQ |language=pt-br}}</ref> This release marked the third consecutive year Anitta secured a spot in Spotify’s global top 10.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Carvalho |first=Matheus de |date=2024-11-01 |title=São Paulo: parceria de The Weeknd e Anitta estreia no Top 10 do Spotify Global - veja os números! {{!}} #Noticias |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/sao-paulo-the-weeknd-anitta-estreia-top-10-spotify-global-numeros/ |access-date=2024-11-01 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR}}</ref>

At [[67th Annual Grammy Awards]], ''Funk Generation'' was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best Latin Pop Album|Best Latin Pop Album]], becoming the first funk album in history to be nominated for a Grammy.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |title=Anitta é indicada ao Grammy 2025; veja lista |url=https://www.terra.com.br/diversao/musica/anitta-e-indicada-ao-grammy-2025-veja-lista,e986793c14ef10ed0a08b84734bf48d9wxc5li6i.html |access-date=2024-11-09 |website=Terra |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Ratner-Arias |first=Sigal |date=2024-11-08 |title=Edgar Barrera Snags Songwriter of the Year Nod & More Latin Artists With 2025 Grammy Nominations |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/2025-grammy-awards-latin-artists-nominations-1235823716/ |access-date=2024-11-09 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US}}</ref>

On 3 December 2024, Anitta was honored with the ''[[Vanguard Trophy]]'' at the [[Multishow Brazilian Music Awards]], the biggest [[music award]] in Brazil, in recognition of her impact and contribution to Brazilian and international music.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ismerim |first=Flávio |title=Prêmio Multishow 2024: Anitta receberá primeiro Troféu Vanguarda; entenda |url=https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/entretenimento/premio-multishow-2024-anitta-recebera-primeiro-trofeu-vanguarda-entenda/ |access-date=2025-01-06 |website=CNN Brasil |date=3 December 2024 |language=pt-BR}}</ref> This newly introduced category highlighted her status as the most prominent Brazilian artist on the global stage.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-12-01 |title=Entenda o novo Troféu Vanguarda que Anitta receberá no Prêmio Multishow 2024 |url=https://gshow.globo.com/multishow/premio-multishow/2024/noticia/entenda-o-novo-trofeu-vanguarda-que-anitta-recebera-no-premio-multishow-2024.ghtml |access-date=2025-01-06 |website=gshow |language=pt-br}}</ref> With this achievement, Anitta also became the [[List of Nominations and Winners of the Multishow Brazilian Music Award|most awarded artist]] in the history of the event and the most nominated.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-12-04 |title=Anitta se torna artista mais premiada na história do Prêmio Multishow - Diário do Grande ABC - Notícias e informações do Grande ABC: anitta se torna artista mais premiada na história do prêmio multishow |url=https://www.dgabc.com.br/Noticia/4179809/anitta-se-torna-artista-mais-premiada-na-historia-do-premio-multishow |access-date=2025-01-06 |website=Jornal Diário do Grande ABC |language=pt-BR}}</ref> On 31 December 2024, Anitta headlined the [[New Year's Eve in Copacabana]], which gathered over 2.6 million people.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-01-01 |title=De vermelho, Anitta se apresenta no Show da Virada em Copacabana |url=https://gshow.globo.com/tv/show-da-virada/noticia/de-vermelho-anitta-se-apresenta-no-show-da-virada-em-copacabana.ghtml |access-date=2025-01-06 |website=gshow |language=pt-br}}</ref>

=== 2025–present: Release of Anitta's documentary ===
On January 11, the singer kicked off her series of shows across Brazil, titled ''[[Ensaios da Anitta]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ensaios de Anitta - Billboard Brasil |url=https://billboard.com.br/tag/ensaios-de-anitta/ |access-date=2025-03-15 |website=billboard.com.br |language=pt-BR}}</ref>

On February 1, Anitta reached a new milestone by placing the song "[[São Paulo (song)|São Paulo]]," in collaboration with [[The Weeknd]], in the Top 10 on Spotify in the [[United States]], [[Canada]], and the [[United Kingdom]]. With this, she became the Brazilian act with the highest peak on these charts.<ref name=":2">{{Cite web |last=Torres |first=Leonardo |date=2025-02-11 |title=Anitta está de volta à Billboard Hot 100, com sua melhor posição até hoje {{!}} #Internacional |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-billboard-hot-100-melhor-posicao/ |access-date=2025-03-15 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR}}</ref> Additionally, the track stood out for being one of the few by any artist worldwide to enter the Top 10 in every country in the [[Americas]]. On February 10, she achieved her highest peak on the ''[[Billboard Hot 100]]'', reaching position #43, extending her personal record.<ref name=":2" /> The song also solidified Anitta's record as the Brazilian artist with the most #1s on [[Apple Music]], in more than 28 countries. "São Paulo" remained in the Top 9 of the Apple Music Global chart, breaking and maintaining her record for the highest peak by a Brazilian act and expanding her position as the most successful Brazilian on global charts, including the [[UK singles chart|UK Official Singles Chart]], [[Official Finnish Charts|Finland Singles Chart]], [[Sweden Singles Chart]], [[Canadian Hot 100|Canada Hot 100]], [[France Singles Chart]], among others.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ismerim |first=Flávio |title=Funk está no top global como prometi, diz Anitta após hit com The Weeknd |url=https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/entretenimento/funk-esta-no-top-global-como-prometi-diz-anitta-apos-hit-com-the-weeknd/ |access-date=2025-03-15 |website=CNN Brasil |date=14 February 2025 |language=pt-BR}}</ref>

In February, Anitta also expanded her record as the Brazilian act with the most monthly listeners on Spotify.<ref>{{Cite web |title=O impressionante recorde que coloca Anitta entre as maiores do Spotify {{!}} O Som e a Fúria |url=https://veja.abril.com.br/coluna/o-som-e-a-furia/o-impressionante-recorde-que-coloca-anitta-entre-as-maiores-do-spotify#:~:text=Cantora%20foi%20a%20brasileira%20mais,que%20nenhum%20outro%20conterr%C3%A2neo%20conquistou&text=A%20cantora%20Anitta%20alcan%C3%A7ou%20os,escutada%20do%20mundo%20no%20aplicativo. |access-date=2025-03-15 |website=VEJA |language=pt-BR}}</ref> Additionally, she extended her record as the Brazilian artist with the most #1s on Spotify, reaching the top in several countries, such as [[Brazil]], [[Portugal]], [[Panama]], [[Argentina]], [[Uruguay]], [[Latvia]], [[Luxembourg]], [[Estonia]], [[Switzerland]], and [[Lithuania]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Carvalho |first=Matheus de |date=2024-09-25 |title=Anitta se torna a 1ª artista brasileira a chegar ao topo do Spotify da Argentina {{!}} #Noticias |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-1a-artista-brasileira-topo-spotify-argentina/#:~:text=Anitta%20acaba%20de%20se%20tornar,duas%20posi%C3%A7%C3%B5es%20at%C3%A9%20o%20#1. |access-date=2025-03-15 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR}}</ref> On February 20, Anitta made history by becoming the first Brazilian to win an award at the ''[[Premios Lo Nuestro]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Brasil |first=Billboard |date=2025-02-20 |title=Anitta ganha o Premio Lo Nuestro; saiba mais - Billboard Brasil |url=https://billboard.com.br/anitta-ganha-o-premio-lo-nuestro-com-bellakeo/ |access-date=2025-03-15 |website=billboard.com.br |language=pt-BR}}</ref>

On March 1, Anitta set a new record, achieving the highest number of streams in a single month on Spotify for a Brazilian pop artist, with 324 million streams. On March 6, the documentary ''[[Larissa: The Other Side of Anitta]]'' premiered.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Clarke |first=Stewart |date=2025-01-30 |title=Netflix Documentary 'Larissa: The Other Side Of Anitta' Promises To Show Brazilian Superstar's Journey Of Self Discovery |url=https://deadline.com/2025/01/larissa-the-other-side-of-anitta-netflix-documentary-on-brazilian-superstar-1236272714/ |access-date=2025-03-15 |website=Deadline |language=en-US}}</ref> In its first four days of release, the film reached 2.5 million views and totaled 1.5 million hours watched.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Torres |first=Leonardo |date=2025-03-12 |title=Revelada audiência da estreia do documentário da Anitta na Netflix {{!}} #Geek |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/revelada-audiencia-estreia-documentario-anitta-netflix/ |access-date=2025-03-15 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR}}</ref> The documentary entered the Top 3 on [[Netflix]] Brazil, topped the charts in Portugal, and reached the global Top 10 on the platform among non-English language productions during its debut week.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Oliveira |first=Eduardo |date=2025-03-09 |title=Documentário intimista sobre Anitta já é o mais visto na Netflix em Portugal |url=https://newinoeiras.nit.pt/cultura/documentario-intimista-sobre-anitta-ja-e-o-mais-visto-na-netflix-em-portugal/#:~:text=Bastou%20um%20dia%20para%20%E2%80%9CLarissa,in%20Rio%20Lisboa,%20em%202022. |access-date=2025-03-15 |website=New in Oeiras |language=pt-PT}}</ref> On March 8, Anitta held her traditional post-[[Brazilian Carnival|Carnival]] street party in Rio de Janeiro, attracting a crowd of 1,100,000 people.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Bloco da Anitta leva 1,1 milhão de pessoas no Rio |url=https://g1.globo.com/jornal-hoje/video/bloco-da-anitta-leva-11-milhao-de-pessoas-no-rio-13402793.ghtml |access-date=2025-03-15 |website=G1 |language=pt-br}}</ref>

On April 22, the singer and entrepreneur was announced as the new ambassador for [[Mercado Pago]], starring in a campaign at [[Pacaembu Stadium]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-04-25 |title="Are you going to get purple with desire?", says Anitta in an indirect message to Nubank |url=https://ground.news/article/are-you-going-to-get-purple-with-desire-says-anitta-in-an-indirect-message-to-nubank |access-date=2025-04-25 |website=Ground News |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Torres |first=Leonardo |date=2025-04-22 |title=Show em estádio? Vem ver o que a Anitta anunciou em coletiva de imprensa {{!}} #Nacional |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/show-em-estadio-anitta-coletiva-imprensa/ |access-date=2025-04-25 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR}}</ref> On April 24, she was honored at the [[Billboard Latin Women in Music]] event in Miami with the Vanguard Award,<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Cobo |first=Leila |date=2025-04-14 |title=Latin Women in Music 2025 |url=https://www.billboard.com/p/latin-women-music-2025/ |access-date=2025-04-25 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US}}</ref> becoming the first artist to receive this award in that category.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Raygoza |first=Isabela |date=2025-04-23 |title=Anitta Opens Up About the Woman Behind the Superstar: 'We Need to Embrace All Parts of Ourselves' |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/latin/anitta-latin-women-in-music-2025-interview-1235946447/ |access-date=2025-04-25 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US}}</ref> The award was presented by [[Shakira]], who, in her speech, referred to Anitta as the "Queen of Funk".<ref>{{Cite web |title=Shakira homenageia Anitta e entrega prêmio à amiga: "Rainha do funk" |url=https://www.cnnbrasil.com.br/entretenimento/shakira-homenageia-anitta-e-entrega-premio-a-amiga-rainha-do-funk-brasile/ |access-date=2025-04-25 |website=CNN Brasil |date=25 April 2025 |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Brasil |first=Billboard |date=2025-04-24 |title=Shakira exalta Anitta no Billboard Latin Women in Music: 'Rainha do funk' - Billboard Brasil |url=https://billboard.com.br/shakira-anitta-billboard-latin-women-in-music/ |access-date=2025-04-25 |website=billboard.com.br |language=pt-BR}}</ref>

==Artistry==
===Musical style===
Anitta's music is generally [[Pop music|pop]],<ref name="g1">{{cite web |last=Lorentz |first=Braulio |date=13 August 2013 |title=Primeiro disco de Anitta após fama foge do funk e busca ser pop 'colante' |url=http://g1.globo.com/musica/noticia/2013/07/primeiro-disco-de-anitta-apos-fama-foge-do-funk-e-busca-ser-pop-colante.html |access-date=15 December 2013 |publisher=[[G1 (website)|G1]] |language=pt |archive-date=25 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125174736/http://g1.globo.com/musica/noticia/2013/07/primeiro-disco-de-anitta-apos-fama-foge-do-funk-e-busca-ser-pop-colante.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.redetv.uol.com.br/tvfama/blog/celebridades/de-volta-ao-funk-anitta-lanca-clipe-de-vai-malandra-gravado-no-vidigal |title=De volta ao funk: Anitta lança clipe de "Vai Malandra", gravado no Vidigal |date=12 August 2013 |access-date=31 March 2018 |work=[[Rede TV]] |archive-date=5 March 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305063920/http://www.redetv.uol.com.br/tvfama/blog/celebridades/de-volta-ao-funk-anitta-lanca-clipe-de-vai-malandra-gravado-no-vidigal |url-status=live }}</ref> [[funk carioca]], [[funk melody]]<ref>{{Cite news |title=Anitta planeja funk melody 'em inglês com sonoridade brasileira': 'Resolvendo essa equação' |url=https://extra.globo.com/tv-e-lazer/anitta-planeja-funk-melody-em-ingles-com-sonoridade-brasileira-resolvendo-essa-equacao-rv1-1-25562955.html |access-date=2023-02-23 |website=Extra Online |date=30 August 2022 |language=pt-BR |archive-date=23 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230223193744/https://extra.globo.com/tv-e-lazer/anitta-planeja-funk-melody-em-ingles-com-sonoridade-brasileira-resolvendo-essa-equacao-rv1-1-25562955.html |url-status=live }}</ref> and [[Latin pop]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.latinpopbrasil.com.br/noticias/anitta-vai-lancar-novo-single-em-espanhol-paradinha |title=Anitta vai lançar novo single em espanhol: Paradinha |date=12 August 2013 |access-date=31 March 2018 |work=LatinPop Brasil |archive-date=5 March 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305202508/https://www.latinpopbrasil.com.br/noticias/anitta-vai-lancar-novo-single-em-espanhol-paradinha/ |url-status=live |author1=Redacao }}</ref> but she also incorporates [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.virgula.com.br/musica/anitta-lanca-clipe-com-partipacao-de-projota-e-levada-rb/ |title=Anitta lança clipe com partipação de Projota e levada R&B |date=12 August 2013 |access-date=12 August 2013 |work=Virgula |archive-date=5 March 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305202424/http://www.virgula.com.br/musica/anitta-lanca-clipe-com-partipacao-de-projota-e-levada-rb/ |url-status=live }}</ref> [[dance-pop]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://musica.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2015/10/09/anitta-lanca-o-clipe-de-bang.htm |title=Anitta lança clipe de "Bang" com referências de pop art |access-date=12 August 2013 |work=RICTV |archive-date=5 March 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305064208/https://musica.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2015/10/09/anitta-lanca-o-clipe-de-bang.htm |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Electronic music|electronic]],<ref name="dance"/> [[electronic dance music|EDM]],<ref name="dance">{{cite web |url=http://g1.globo.com/musica/blog/mauro-ferreira/post/anitta-lanca-single-com-alesso-para-se-impor-na-cena-eletronica-mundial.html |title=Anitta lança single com Alesso para se impor na cena eletrônica mundial |access-date=15 December 2013 |language=pt |date=13 August 2013 |publisher=[[G1 (website)|G1]] |archive-date=5 March 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305063103/http://g1.globo.com/musica/blog/mauro-ferreira/post/anitta-lanca-single-com-alesso-para-se-impor-na-cena-eletronica-mundial.html |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Reggae fusion|reggae]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://pr.ricmais.com.br/musica/noticias/anitta-lanca-musica-com-batidas-de-reggae |title=Anitta lança música com batidas de reggae |access-date=12 August 2013 |work=RICTV |archive-date=5 March 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305124650/https://pr.ricmais.com.br/musica/noticias/anitta-lanca-musica-com-batidas-de-reggae/ |url-status=live }}</ref> and [[reggaeton]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.papelpop.com/2017/11/anitta-lanca-o-reggaeton-sexy-downtown-com-j-balvin |title=Anitta lança o reggaeton sexy "Downtown" com J Balvin |access-date=12 August 2013 |work=Papel Pop |archive-date=24 February 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180224185214/http://www.papelpop.com/2017/11/anitta-lanca-o-reggaeton-sexy-downtown-com-j-balvin/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In addition to having songs in five different languages in her discography, such as [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]], [[Spanish language|Spanish]], [[English language|English]], [[Italian language|Italian]]<ref name="instyle" /><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta arrisca italiano em 'Paloma', parceria com Fred De Palma; ouça |url=https://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2020/07/03/anitta-arrisca-italiano-em-paloma-parceria-com-fred-de-palma-ouca.htm |access-date=28 November 2022 |website=entretenimento.uol.com.br |language=pt-br |archive-date=28 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221128220150/https://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2020/07/03/anitta-arrisca-italiano-em-paloma-parceria-com-fred-de-palma-ouca.htm}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta apresenta 'Un altro ballo', single em que refaz a conexão com o rapper italiano Fred de Palma |url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/blog/mauro-ferreira/post/2021/06/21/anitta-apresenta-un-altro-ballo-single-em-que-refaz-a-conexao-com-o-rapper-italiano-fred-de-palma.ghtml |access-date=28 November 2022 |website=G1 |date=21 June 2021 |language=pt-br |archive-date=28 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221128220152/https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/blog/mauro-ferreira/post/2021/06/21/anitta-apresenta-un-altro-ballo-single-em-que-refaz-a-conexao-com-o-rapper-italiano-fred-de-palma.ghtml}}</ref> and [[French language|French]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Rocha |first=Lucas |date=3 June 2021 |title=Poliglota é ela! Anitta ARRASA cantando em francês pela primeira vez em "Mon Soleil", parceria com Dadju; vem escutar! |url=https://hugogloss.uol.com.br/musica/poliglota-e-ela-anitta-arrasa-cantando-em-frances-pela-primeira-vez-em-mon-soleil-parceria-com-dadju-vem-escutar/ |access-date=28 November 2022 |website=Hugo Gloss |language=pt-BR |archive-date=28 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221128220147/https://hugogloss.uol.com.br/musica/poliglota-e-ela-anitta-arrasa-cantando-em-frances-pela-primeira-vez-em-mon-soleil-parceria-com-dadju-vem-escutar/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Influences===
Anitta cited [[Mariah Carey]] as major artist influence and named her as "one of the main reasons I started singing": "She was the first introduction I had to music. With her, I understood what it was like to be a singer, what it was like to follow by a artist's album and work for so long time. It's as if she had taught me how to sing".<ref name="influencias3">{{cite web|url=https://archive.today/20240303203532/https://glamour.globo.com/videos/noticia/2017/11/anitta-sobre-mariah-carey-e-como-se-ela-tivesse-me-ensinado-cantar.ghtml |title=Anitta sobre Mariah Carey: "É como se ela tivesse me ensinado a cantar"|access-date=2023-04-06 |website=[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]|date=
November 30, 2017}}</ref> Anitta's other major influences include [[Katy Perry]], [[Beyoncé]] and [[Rihanna]].<ref name=carey>{{cite web|url=https://archive.today/20240303195224/https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-diz-que-e-inspirada-por-beyonce-rihanna-e-katy-perry-mas-mariah-carey-e-sua-maior-diva/|title=Anitta diz que é inspirada por Beyoncé, Rihanna e Katy Perry, mas Mariah Carey é sua maior diva|author=Caian Nunes|date=October 21, 2020|access-date=2023-04-06 |website=[[Popline]]}}</ref> Shes expressed her admiration for [[Shakira]], who she credited with opening the door for female artists of Latin Music,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://extra.globo.com/tv-e-lazer/musica/anitta-sobre-pabllo-vittar-nao-somos-mais-amigas-mas-admiro-trabalho-23812162.html|title=Anitta sobre Pabllo Vittar: 'Não somos mais amigas, mas admiro o trabalho' |date=July 16, 2019|work=[[Extra (newspaper)|Extra]]|language=pt-br}}</ref> as well as [[Carmen Miranda]] for opening the door for Brazilian artists in global entertainment industry.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta se inspira em Carmen Miranda último dia de Carnaval com o 'Bloco da Anitta' |url=https://revistaquem.globo.com/eventos/carnaval/noticia/2023/02/anitta-mostra-look-para-ultimo-dia-de-carnaval-com-o-bloco-da-anitta.ghtml |access-date=2023-04-06 |website=Quem |date=25 February 2023 |language=pt-br |archive-date=6 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230406145832/https://revistaquem.globo.com/eventos/carnaval/noticia/2023/02/anitta-mostra-look-para-ultimo-dia-de-carnaval-com-o-bloco-da-anitta.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> {{Quote box
| width = 30%
| align = right
| quote = Of course I have my inspirations, I love it, I grew up listening to Mariah Carey, Rihanna. I love Beyoncé with passion, who has no way, the whole of Brazil, the whole world is a fan. So we do have our references, always. And it's super important for you to have an inspiration. (...) I really enjoy looking at my divas.
| source = {{mdash}} Anitta about her influences.<ref name = "Beyoncé">{{cite web |url=http://www.rockblogs.net/adimitiu-anitta-fala-sobre-beyonce-ser-sua-inspiracao/ |title=Anitta fala sobre Beyoncé ser sua inspiração |access-date=2 July 2015 |archive-date=3 July 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150703064735/http://www.rockblogs.net/adimitiu-anitta-fala-sobre-beyonce-ser-sua-inspiracao/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>
}}

Songs and concerts of female pop artists such as [[The Pussycat Dolls]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.estacaodanoticia.com/main/2013/09/anitta-copia-beyoince-e-as-pussycat-dolls |title=Anitta: Beyoncé e Pussycat Dolls |work=Estação Notícia |access-date=27 October 2017 |archive-date=5 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170805100912/http://www.estacaodanoticia.com/main/2013/09/anitta-copia-beyoince-e-as-pussycat-dolls/ |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Madonna]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://g1.globo.com/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2013/10/no-rio-anitta-chama-meninos-no-palco-e-diz-que-e-investimento.html |title=No Rio, Anitta chama meninos no palco e diz que é 'investimento' |work=G1 |access-date=18 April 2013 |archive-date=20 February 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180220152656/http://g1.globo.com/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2013/10/no-rio-anitta-chama-meninos-no-palco-e-diz-que-e-investimento.html |url-status=live }}</ref> and [[Britney Spears]],<ref name="comenta">{{cite web |url=http://g1.globo.com/musica/noticia/2013/07/em-desafio-musical-anitta-comenta-idolos-dancava-britney-no-espelho.html |title=Em desafio musical, Anitta comenta ídolos: 'Dançava Britney no espelho' |work=O Globo |date=16 July 2013 |access-date=27 October 2017 |archive-date=20 February 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180220212242/http://g1.globo.com/musica/noticia/2013/07/em-desafio-musical-anitta-comenta-idolos-dancava-britney-no-espelho.html |url-status=live|language=pt-br}}</ref> often influences her work. Shes expressed his admiration by Brazilian female singers [[Rita Lee]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gshow.globo.com/novelas/mania-de-voce/noticia/anitta-comenta-desafio-de-regravar-hit-de-rita-lee-para-mania-de-voce-e-relacao-com-a-cantora.ghtml|title=Anitta comenta desafio de regravar ''hit'' de Rita Lee para abertura de Mania de Você e relação com a cantora|date=August 21, 2024|access-date=27 October 2017|work=[[GShow]]|language=pt-br}}</ref> [[Marisa Monte]] and [[Ivete Sangalo]].<ref name=elpais2>{{cite web|url=https://www.elmundo.es/cultura/musica/2018/05/04/5aeca37d268e3edc648b4596.html|title=Anitta, la estrella de ''pop'' brasileña: "Con o sin polémicas, digo lo que pienso"|last=Zani|first=Alejandra|date=May 4, 2018|work=[[El País]]|language=es-es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.today/20240423223705/https://revistaquem.globo.com/QUEM-News/noticia/2013/07/anitta-canta-com-ivete-sangalo-no-salvador-fest.html|title=Anitta canta com Ivete Sangalo no Salvador Fest|date=July 14, 2013 |access-date=27 October 2024|work=[[Quem (magazine)|Quem]]|language=pt-br}}</ref>

==Public image==
[[File:Anitta Heat Latin Music Awards 2021.jpg|140px|thumb|Anitta at the [[Coca-Cola]] Jeans parade in November 2014]]
Soon after reaching stardom, Anitta was described by the media as a [[sex symbol]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.purepeople.com.br/noticia/anitta-reclama-de-sua-imagem-de-simbolo-sexual-tenho-obrigacao-de-ser-gostosa_a16178/1 |title=Anitta reclama de sua imagem de símbolo sexual: "tenho obrigação de ser gostosa" |date=11 February 2014 |publisher=Purepeople |access-date=17 March 2018 |archive-date=8 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180708193026/http://www.purepeople.com.br/noticia/anitta-reclama-de-sua-imagem-de-simbolo-sexual-tenho-obrigacao-de-ser-gostosa_a16178/1 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://noticias.bol.uol.com.br/fotos/entretenimento/2013/06/27/confira-imagens-na-trajetoria-da-funkeira-anitta.htm?fotoNav=340 |date=14 August 2013 |access-date=17 March 2018 |publisher=[[Universo Online|UOL]] |quote="Novo símbolo sexual do país, a funkeira Anitta revelou à seção 20P da revista "Playboy" que, no momento, não tem pretensões de posar nua e o que não pode faltar entre quatro paredes para a transa ser perfeita" |title=Veja imagens da funkeira Anitta |archive-date=18 September 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130918134948/http://noticias.bol.uol.com.br/fotos/entretenimento/2013/06/27/confira-imagens-na-trajetoria-da-funkeira-anitta.htm?fotoNav=340 |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2015, she was voted the sexiest woman by readers of [[VIP (magazine)|VIP magazine]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://vip.abril.com.br/mulheres/ensaio-vip-a-presenca-de-anitta/ |title=Ensaio VIP: A presença de Anitta |author=Só, Pedro |date=31 May 2017 |access-date=17 March 2018 |publisher=Vip |work=Editora Abril |archive-date=17 March 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180317232937/https://vip.abril.com.br/mulheres/ensaio-vip-a-presenca-de-anitta/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Anitta has expressed that by working "with the sensuality thing," her work is not always taken seriously by some critics and the public. She voiced her frustration, stating, "[...] people think you have no talent, no intelligence. I can be intelligent and have the desire to be sensual."<ref>{{cite web |url=https://capricho.abril.com.br/famosos/anitta-no-superbonita-posso-ser-inteligente-e-sensual/ |title=Anitta no Superbonita: "Posso ser inteligente e sensual" |date=8 August 2017 |author=Da Redação |access-date=17 March 2018 |publisher=[[Capricho]] |archive-date=17 March 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180317232918/https://capricho.abril.com.br/famosos/anitta-no-superbonita-posso-ser-inteligente-e-sensual/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

When she was selected as "Woman of the Year" by the Brazilian edition of ''[[GQ]]'' magazine in 2017, Anitta delivered a feminist speech,<ref name="pure">{{cite web |author=Assumpção, Guilherme |date=1 December 2017 |title=Anitta, eleita Mulher do Ano, arranca aplausos com discurso feminista: "Vou continuar lutando" |url=http://www.purebreak.com.br/noticias/anitta-eleita-mulher-do-ano-arranca-aplausos-com-discurso-feminista-vou-continuar-lutando/65512 |access-date=17 March 2018 |publisher=PureBreak |archive-date=18 March 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180318054109/http://www.purebreak.com.br/noticias/anitta-eleita-mulher-do-ano-arranca-aplausos-com-discurso-feminista-vou-continuar-lutando/65512 |url-status=dead }}</ref> speaking out about the differing treatment of female artists compared to their male counterparts.

''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' magazine listed Anitta as one of the 100 most influential and creative people in the world. She was chosen for her "positive engagement with body image," exemplified by her choice to unapologetically display her unretouched appearance in the "[[Vai Malandra]]" music video.<ref>{{cite journal |title=VogueWorld 100 |url=https://www.vogue.com/projects/vogueworld-100-influencers |journal=Vogue |date=27 February 2018 |language=en |access-date=10 April 2018 |archive-date=9 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180409232452/https://www.vogue.com/projects/vogueworld-100-influencers |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com.br/noticias/kcdnfp/anitta-e-mc-soffia-representam-o-brasil-em-lista-da-vogue-das-pessoas-mais-influentes|title=Anitta e Mc Soffia representam o Brasil em lista da Vogue das pessoas mais influentes e criativas do mundo {{!}} MTV Brasil|access-date=14 March 2018|work=MTV Brasil|archive-date=15 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180315004213/http://www.mtv.com.br/noticias/kcdnfp/anitta-e-mc-soffia-representam-o-brasil-em-lista-da-vogue-das-pessoas-mais-influentes|url-status=dead}}</ref>

As one of the most influential celebrities on social media, Anitta ranked 7th in the [[List of Billboard Social 50 number-one artists|Billboard Social 50]] in June 2017, later appearing in the top 10 multiple times, including in December of the same year.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Pernambuco |first=Diario de |date=9 June 2017 |title=Anitta supera Rihanna e Shakira em lista de artistas mais influentes da Billboard |url=http://www.diariodepernambuco.com.br/app/noticia/viver/2017/06/09/internas_viver,708029/anitta-supera-rihanna-e-shakira-em-lista-de-artistas-mais-influentes-d.shtml |url-status=live |journal=Diário de Pernambuco |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180708193637/http://www.diariodepernambuco.com.br/app/noticia/viver/2017/06/09/internas_viver,708029/anitta-supera-rihanna-e-shakira-em-lista-de-artistas-mais-influentes-d.shtml |archive-date=8 July 2018 |access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref name=":1" />  In March 2018, she won the [[IHeartRadio Music Awards|iHeart Music Awards]] for [[2018 iHeartRadio Music Awards#Winners & nominees|Social Star]].<ref name="iheart1">{{cite journal |title=Anitta leva prêmio no iHeartRadio Music Awards 2018; veja lista completa de ganhadores |url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/noticia/anitta-leva-premio-no-iheartradio-music-awards-2018-veja-lista-completa-de-ganhadores.ghtml |journal=G1 |date=12 March 2018 |language=pt-BR |access-date=12 April 2018 |archive-date=15 March 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180315003701/https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/noticia/anitta-leva-premio-no-iheartradio-music-awards-2018-veja-lista-completa-de-ganhadores.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref>[[File:Ritmos musicais diversos agitam festa de 59º de Brasília (47663895771).jpg|140px|left|thumb|Anitta in 2015]]
Following her rise to fame, Anitta has associated her image with numerous [[brand]]s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.meioemensagem.com.br/home/marketing/2017/12/21/os-dez-principais-fatos-de-marketing-de-2017.html |title=Os dez principais fatos de marketing de 2017 |date=21 December 2017 |website=Meio & Mensagem |access-date=25 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222211301/http://www.meioemensagem.com.br/home/marketing/2017/12/21/os-dez-principais-fatos-de-marketing-de-2017.html |archive-date=22 December 2017}}</ref> Often referred to as a "marketing case",<ref>{{cite web |url=http://adnews.com.br/adarticles/anitta-um-caso-de-marketing-que-vale-pena-ser-estudado.html |title=Anitta, um caso de marketing que vale a pena ser estudado |last=Sampaio |first=Pedro |date=12 June 2017 |website=AD News |access-date=25 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180408091357/http://adnews.com.br/adarticles/anitta-um-caso-de-marketing-que-vale-pena-ser-estudado.html |archive-date=8 April 2018 }}</ref> Anitta views this as a compliment, stating: "I'm happy when people say that I'm a marketing case because I'm the one who handles my marketing. I studied marketing; I [[Graduation|graduated]] in pre-college administration and took marketing classes. All my marketing is planned and executed by me. I feel flattered when people acknowledge that."<ref name="bbc.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.com/portuguese/brasil-40748587 |title='Gosto quando dizem que sou caso de marketing': 20 minutos na presença de Anitta |last=Mendonca |first=Renata |date=28 July 2017 |language=Portuguese |website=BBC Brasil |access-date=25 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170801032946/http://www.bbc.com/portuguese/brasil-40748587 |archive-date=1 August 2017}}</ref> She also described co-branding as a strategy she uses when collaborating with foreign artists to introduce her work to other markets.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/musica/anitta-fala-da-investida-no-mercado-internacional-eu-que-faco-acontecer-21462676 |title=Anitta fala da investida no mercado internacional: "eu que faço acontecer" |last=Oliveira |first=Luccas |date=6 November 2017 |language=Portuguese |website=[[O Globo]] |access-date=25 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170611172811/https://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/musica/anitta-fala-da-investida-no-mercado-internacional-eu-que-faco-acontecer-21462676 |archive-date=11 June 2017}}</ref>

Early in her career, Anitta's style featured colorful printed dresses, [[Crop top|cropped tops]], denim shorts, plaid shirts, and caps. After the release of her album ''[[Bang! (Anitta album)|Bang]]'' (2015), her style began to incorporate pop art references. She has expressed a preference for clothing from brands like [[Moschino]] and [[Givenchy]].<ref>{{cite web |date=16 October 2015 |title=Looks de Anitta: veja 100 fotos e inspire-se no estilo sexy e divertido da cantora! |url=http://www.fiquediva.com.br/noticia/looks-de-anitta-veja-100-fotos-e-inspire-se-no-estilo-sexy-e-divertido-da-cantora_a721/1 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170627060709/http://www.fiquediva.com.br/noticia/looks-de-anitta-veja-100-fotos-e-inspire-se-no-estilo-sexy-e-divertido-da-cantora_a721/1 |archive-date=27 June 2017 |access-date=6 July 2017 |publisher=Niely.com}}</ref> In an interview with ''EGO.com'', Anitta stated, "Being stylish is having an attitude, having an uncommon sense of authenticity. To have style is to be in a good mood".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ego.globo.com/moda/noticia/2016/03/anitta-fala-de-estilo-ser-cafona-e-vestir-algo-que-todo-mundo-espera.html |title=Anitta fala de estilo: 'Ser cafona é vestir algo que todo mundo espera' |publisher=EGO.com |date=10 March 2016 |access-date=6 July 2017}}</ref>

===Anal tattoo===
In February 2021, a video of Anitta getting a tattoo on her anus, which allegedly says "love" or "I lov you", leaked online.<ref name="1 June 2022 O GLOBO">{{Cite news|last=Júnior|first=Gilberto|date=1 June 2022|title=Lucas Maffei fala sobre tatuagem íntima de Anitta: 'Não foi a coisa mais normal do mundo'|language=Portuguese|work=[[O Globo|O GLOBO]]|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/ela/gente/noticia/2022/06/lucas-maffei-fala-sobre-tatuagem-intima-de-anitta-nao-foi-a-coisa-mais-normal-do-mundo.ghtml|url-status=live|access-date=11 December 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220717043248/https://oglobo.globo.com/ela/gente/noticia/2022/06/lucas-maffei-fala-sobre-tatuagem-intima-de-anitta-nao-foi-a-coisa-mais-normal-do-mundo.ghtml|archive-date=17 July 2022}}</ref><ref name="21 February 2021 Marie Claire">{{Cite news|date=21 February 2021|title=Anitta fala sobre tatuagem nas partes íntimas: "Foi retocada"|language=Portuguese|work=[[Marie Claire]]|url=https://revistamarieclaire.globo.com/Celebridades/noticia/2021/02/anitta-fala-do-video-em-que-aparece-fazendo-tatuagem-anal-foi-retocada.html|url-status=live|access-date=11 December 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221006135150/https://revistamarieclaire.globo.com/Celebridades/noticia/2021/02/anitta-fala-do-video-em-que-aparece-fazendo-tatuagem-anal-foi-retocada.html|archive-date=6 October 2022}}</ref><ref name="22 February 2021 ISTOÉ Independente">{{Cite news|date=22 February 2021|title=Anitta revela frase de tatuagem no ânus após vídeo vazar na rede social|language=Portuguese|work=[[Istoé|ISTOÉ Independente]]|url=https://istoe.com.br/anitta-revela-frase-de-tatuagem-no-anus-apos-video-vazar-na-rede-social/|url-status=live|access-date=11 December 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220705025350/https://istoe.com.br/anitta-revela-frase-de-tatuagem-no-anus-apos-video-vazar-na-rede-social/|archive-date=5 July 2022}}</ref><ref name="18 August 2022 UOL">{{Cite news|last=Pavão|first=Filipe|date=18 August 2022|title=Vídeo, 'CPI', perfume: a linha do tempo da tatuagem no tororó de Anitta|language=Portuguese|work=[[Universo Online|UOL]]|url=https://www.uol.com.br/splash/noticias/2022/08/18/anitta-tatuagem.htm|url-status=live|access-date=11 December 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230225163345/https://www.uol.com.br/splash/noticias/2022/08/18/anitta-tatuagem.htm|archive-date=25 February 2023}}</ref> In May 2022, the sertanejo singer Zé Neto, part of the duo with Cristiano, made a controversial statement during a concert, claiming he didn't need resources from the [[Rouanet Law]], nor a tattoo on his "toba" (slang for anus)<ref name="Michaelis On-line">{{Cite web|title=Toba|url=https://michaelis.uol.com.br/palavra/qOwqV/toba-2|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231211042610/https://michaelis.uol.com.br/palavra/qOwqV/toba-2|archive-date=11 December 2023|access-date=11 December 2023|website=[[Michaelis (dictionary)|Michaelis On-line]]|language=Portuguese}}</ref> to show success, in an apparent dig at Anitta.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Braziliense' |first='Correio |date=2022-05-13 |title=Sertanejo manda indireta para Anitta em show e vídeo viraliza |url=https://www.correiobraziliense.com.br/diversao-e-arte/2022/05/5007766-sertanejo-manda-indireta-para-anitta-em-show-e-video-viraliza.html |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=Diversão e Arte |language=pt-BR}}</ref> The comment sparked a conflict with the singer's fans and led to the exposure of million-dollar contracts for Zé Neto and other [[Sertanejo music|sertanejo]] artists for shows in small towns, triggering the opening of the "CPI dos Sertanejos," an investigation into the use of public funds for these events.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Mais de 35 cidades têm shows investigados; Gusttavo Lima é o mais citado |url=https://www.uol.com.br/splash/noticias/2022/06/12/cpi-do-sertanejo-shows-investigados.htm |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=www.uol.com.br |language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Minas' |first='Bernardo Estillac-Estado de |date=2022-06-01 |title=Contratos de pequenas prefeituras de MG com sertanejos superam R$ 7 mi |url=https://www.correiobraziliense.com.br/brasil/2022/06/5012144-contratos-de-pequenas-prefeituras-de-mg-com-sertanejos-superam-rs-7-mi.html |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=Brasil |language=pt-BR}}</ref> In addition to the duo Zé Neto & Cristiano, the investigations involved actions from the Public Prosecutor's Office in [[Mato Grosso]] and 24 of the 26 municipalities under suspicion, as well as controversies involving [[Gusttavo Lima]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-02-12 |title=Cachê milionário, 'CPI do sertanejo': Gusttavo Lima teve shows investigados |url=https://www.uol.com.br/splash/noticias/2024/02/12/gusttavo-lima.htm |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=UOL |language=pt-br}}</ref> one of Brazil's highest-paid artists and a staunch supporter of [[Jair Bolsonaro]], who promised to end the "mamata" of the Rouanet cultural incentive law.<ref name="18 August 2022 UOL"/><ref name="31 May 2022 g1">{{Cite news|date=31 May 2022|title=Sertanejos e prefeituras: como polêmica foi de 'tororó' de Anitta a shows investigados de Gusttavo Lima|language=Portuguese|work=[[G1 (website)|g1]]|url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/noticia/2022/05/31/sertanejos-e-prefeituras-como-polemica-foi-de-tororo-de-anitta-a-shows-investigados-de-gusttavo-lima.ghtml|url-status=live|access-date=11 December 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230130145044/https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/noticia/2022/05/31/sertanejos-e-prefeituras-como-polemica-foi-de-tororo-de-anitta-a-shows-investigados-de-gusttavo-lima.ghtml|archive-date=30 January 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Entenda a treta Zé Neto x Anitta que levou a uma crise do sertanejo |url=https://www.uol.com.br/splash/noticias/2022/05/29/entenda-a-treta-ze-neto-x-anitta-que-levou-a-uma-crise-do-sertanejo.htm |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=www.uol.com.br |language=pt-br}}</ref>

The crisis in the sertanejo world intensified when the [[Public Prosecutor's Office (Brazil)|Public Prosecutor's Office]] opened inquiries to investigate the origins of the exorbitant contracts.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-05-31 |title=De Gusttavo Lima a Anitta: entenda a brecha que permite contratar famosos com dinheiro público |url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/noticia/2022/05/31/de-gusttavo-lima-a-anitta-entenda-a-brecha-que-permite-contratar-de-famosos-com-dinheiro-publico.ghtml |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=G1 |language=pt-br}}</ref> Gusttavo Lima was the first target, after his fee of R$800,000 for a performance in [[São Luiz, Roraima|São Luiz]], [[Roraima]], was disclosed.<ref>{{Cite web |last=redacaoterra |title=Ministério Público de Roraima investiga show de Gusttavo Lima em São Luiz |url=https://www.terra.com.br/noticias/ministerio-publico-de-roraima-investiga-show-de-gusttavo-lima-em-sao-luiz,02217cd2267d7c3fb7cdd453c52f3c98araewk2i.html |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=Terra |language=pt-BR}}</ref> In another instance, the singer faced criticism again when it was revealed that he would receive R$1.2 million from the municipal government of [[Conceição do Mato Dentro]], [[Minas Gerais]], funds allegedly meant for the health and education sectors.<ref>{{Cite web |last=NINJA |date=2022-05-29 |title=Conceição do Mato Dentro cancela show milionário de Gusttavo Lima após polêmica |url=https://midianinja.org/conceicao-do-mato-dentro-cancela-show-milionario-de-gusttavo-lima-apos-polemica/ |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=Mídia NINJA |language=pt-br}}</ref> Due to the negative fallout, the municipality canceled the performances of Gusttavo Lima and the duo [[Bruno & Marrone]], stating that the traditional 30th Cavalcade of the [[Jubilee]] of Lord Bom Jesus de Matosinhos was being embroiled in a "political and party war".<ref>{{Cite web |title=Polêmica de Anitta com a 'CPI dos sertanejos' chega à imprensa estrangeira {{!}} O Som e a Fúria |url=https://veja.abril.com.br/coluna/o-som-e-a-furia/polemica-de-anitta-com-a-cpi-dos-sertanejos-chega-a-imprensa-estrangeira |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=VEJA |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Por que Gusttavo Lima virou símbolo de crise que começou com Zé Neto |url=https://www.uol.com.br/splash/noticias/2022/05/31/crise-sertanejos-simbolo-gusttavo-lima-ze-neto.htm |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=www.uol.com.br |language=pt-br}}</ref>

With so many allegations and the exposure of public contracts, Gusttavo Lima turned to Instagram on the night of 30 May 2022, to go live and try to explain himself.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mendes |first=Sandy |date=2022-05-31 |title=Gusttavo Lima chora: "Pelo amor de Deus, para de me perseguir" |url=https://congressoemfoco.uol.com.br/area/pais/gusttavo-lima-chora-pelo-amor-de-deus-para-de-me-perseguir/ |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=Congresso em Foco |language=pt-BR}}</ref> During the live video, he cried and vented, stating that he was not a "criminal" and lamented being the target of investigations.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Gusttavo Lima chora e se diz "cansado" de críticas a cachês milionários {{!}} O Som e a Fúria |url=https://veja.abril.com.br/coluna/o-som-e-a-furia/gusttavo-lima-chora-e-se-diz-cansado-de-criticas-a-caches-milionarios |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=VEJA |language=pt-BR}}</ref> During the broadcast, Zé Neto left supportive comments, saying, "Who needs to explain themselves is me, brother. I'm going through a rough phase, I'm your brother. You don't need to explain yourself, just pass it to me. It has nothing to do with you".<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-08-28 |title=CPI dos sertanejos: A treta de Anitta e Zé Neto que revelou cachês milionários pagos por prefeituras |url=https://revistaquem.globo.com/QUEM-News/noticia/2022/05/cpi-dos-sertanejos-treta-de-anitta-e-ze-neto-que-revelou-caches-milionarios-pagos-por-prefeituras.html |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=Quem |language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Prado |first=Maria Alice |date=2022-05-31 |title=Zé Neto 'invade' live de Gusttavo Lima e quebra silêncio sobre polêmica envolvendo sertanejos e dinheiro público: 'Estou atravessando uma fase ruim'; assista |url=https://hugogloss.uol.com.br/musica/ze-neto-invade-live-de-gusttavo-lima-e-quebra-silencio-sobre-polemica-envolvendo-sertanejos-e-dinheiro-publico-estou-atravessando-uma-fase-ruim-assista/ |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=Hugo Gloss |language=pt-BR}}</ref>

Later, Zé Neto apologized to Anitta for his criticisms about the singer's intimate tattoo, admitting that he was wrong to make the comment.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-02-21 |title=Zé Neto se desculpa com Anitta após polêmica sobre tatuagem íntima |url=https://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/musica/noticia/2023/02/ze-neto-se-desculpa-com-anitta-apos-polemica-sobre-tatuagem-intima.ghtml |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=O Globo |language=pt-br}}</ref> "I was going through a very tumultuous moment, and today I sincerely say that I didn't need to say that. I'm speaking from the heart as a request for forgiveness for any possible wrong comment I made," declared the singer.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Zé Neto pede desculpas para Anitta após críticas e pretende conversar com cantora: 'Só eu e ela' |url=https://www.estadao.com.br/emais/gente/ze-neto-pede-desculpas-para-anitta-apos-criticas-e-pretende-conversar-com-cantora-so-eu-e-ela/ |access-date=2024-10-07 |website=Estadão |language=pt-br}}</ref>

The controversy gained international attention, being featured in an article by the American magazine [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] on 9 June 2022.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Miranda |first=Beatriz |date=2022-06-09 |title=Is Anitta's Butt Tattoo Getting a Bum Rap in Debate Over Brazil's Taxpayer-Funded Shows? |url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/anitta-butt-tattoo-brazil-tax-payer-funded-concerts-debate/ |access-date=2024-10-07 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US}}</ref> In April 2023, rappers MC Daniel and Nog released a song titled "* da Anitta," which, despite its provocative title, was received with good humor by the singer herself.<ref name="14 April 2023 Folha de S.Paulo">{{Cite news|date=14 April 2023|title=Anitta reage a rap viral que questiona sua tatuagem íntima: 'morrendo de rir'|language=Portuguese|work=[[Folha de S.Paulo]]|url=https://f5.folha.uol.com.br/musica/2023/04/anitta-reage-a-rap-viral-que-questiona-sua-tatuagem-intima.shtml|url-status=live|access-date=11 December 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230523102045/https://f5.folha.uol.com.br/musica/2023/04/anitta-reage-a-rap-viral-que-questiona-sua-tatuagem-intima.shtml|archive-date=23 May 2023}}</ref><ref name="14 April 2023 g1">{{Cite news|date=14 April 2023|title=Rap que pergunta 'o que tem tatuado no * da Anitta' viraliza; cantora diz que morreu de rir|language=Portuguese|work=[[G1 (website)|g1]]|url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/noticia/2023/04/14/rap-que-pergunta-o-que-tem-tatuado-no-da-anitta-viraliza-cantora-diz-que-morreu-de-rir-e-manda-presente-para-mc.ghtml|url-status=live|access-date=11 December 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230421185010/https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/musica/noticia/2023/04/14/rap-que-pergunta-o-que-tem-tatuado-no-da-anitta-viraliza-cantora-diz-que-morreu-de-rir-e-manda-presente-para-mc.ghtml|archive-date=21 April 2023}}</ref>

== Legacy and impact ==
[[File:COMBATCHY - Espaço das Américas (37663558155).jpg|thumb|225x225px|Anitta at the 'Combatchy' party in 2017]]
Anitta is one of the biggest pop stars in Brazil in recent years and the Brazilian artist with the greatest international exposure, referenced by several magazines, websites, and by the [[Grammy Awards|Grammys]] as the [[Honorific nicknames in popular music|Queen of Brazilian Pop]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Cardi B, Rihanna, Rosalía & More: Which Artist's 2021 Album Are You Looking Forward To The Most? |url=https://www.grammy.com/news/cardi-b-rihanna-rosalia-more-which-artists-2021-album-are-you-looking-forward-most |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=www.grammy.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2020-10-12 |title=Anitta, The queen of Brazilian pop tells all about her global success and future plans, including motherhood |url=https://www.hola.com/us/celebrities/20211122325717/anitta-tells-all-about-her-global-success-and-motherhood-plans/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=HOLA |language=en-US |archive-date=2 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230202201813/https://www.hola.com/us/celebrities/20211122325717/anitta-tells-all-about-her-global-success-and-motherhood-plans/ |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-08-29 |title=Get Into Anitta: the Queen of Brazilian Pop |language=en |work=PAPER |url=https://www.papermag.com/anitta-queen-of-brazilian-pop-2599818510.html#rebelltitem3 |access-date=2023-02-02}}</ref> Additionally, she has become one of the most acclaimed Latin artists.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-03-25 |title=Anitta makes history as first Latin artist to reach #1 on global Spotify chart with a solo song |url=https://www.gaytimes.co.uk/music/anitta-makes-history-as-first-latin-artist-to-reach-1-on-global-spotify-chart-with-a-solo-song/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=GAY TIMES |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Meet The First-Time GRAMMY Nominee: Anitta On The "Insane" Success Of "Envolver," Representing Brazil & Reshaping Global Pop |url=https://www.grammy.com/news/anitta-envolver-versions-of-me-2023-grammys-interview-best-new-artist-meet-first-time-nominee-video |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=www.grammy.com}}</ref>  In 2018, she was elected by [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] as the 7th most influential artist in the world on the [[Billboard Social 50]] list, which ranks the 50 most influential artists on [[social media]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |title=Anitta |url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/anitta/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-06-09 |title=Billboard elege Anitta como 15ª artista mais influente do mundo |url=https://exame.com/casual/anitta-e-eleita-a-15a-artista-mais-influente-do-mundo-pela-billboard/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Exame |language=pt-br}}</ref> In 2022, she received a recognition award for her cultural impact and for being the ambassador of Brazilian music at [[WSJ. Magazine]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-10-25 |title=Anitta is being honored for her cultural impact on entertainment by the WSJ. Magazine |url=https://www.hola.com/us/entertainment/20221025338591/anitta-is-being-honored-for-her-cultural-impact-on-entertainment/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=HOLA |language=en-US}}</ref>

She is often cited as the leading name in [[Brazilian funk]] and pop, being recognized as the exponent of the rhythm worldwide.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ferreira |first=Karine |date=2022-08-29 |title=Anitta faz história e leva o funk para o palco do VMA - |url=https://kondzilla.com/anitta-faz-historia-e-e-a-primeira-brasileira-a-se-apresentar-e-ser-premiada-no-vma/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=KondZilla |language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Franulovic |first=Redação Latinos Brasil-Guilherme |date=2022-08-30 |title=Noite histórica: Anitta leva o funk para o mundo e ganha prêmio no VMA |url=https://www.latinosbrasil.com/noite-historica-anitta-leva-o-funk-para-o-mundo-e-ganha-premio-no-vma/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Latinos Brasil |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Valle (@duduvalle) |first=Eduardo do |date=2022-04-15 |title=Com baile no Coachella 2022, Anitta cumpre promessa de levar funk para o mundo |url=https://rollingstone.uol.com.br/musica/coachella-anitta-acerta-ao-levar-versoes-de-si-palco-do-festival/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta Leva o Funk raiz ao Grammy Latino com 'Envolver' e 'Vai Malandra' |url=https://observatoriodosfamosos.uol.com.br/colunas/thiago-sodre/anitta-leva-o-funk-raiz-ao-grammy-latino-com-envolver-e-vai-malandra |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=observatoriodosfamosos.uol.com.br|date=18 November 2022 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Castro |first=Luiz Eugenio De |date=2022-12-16 |title=Anitta faz performance PERFEITA cheia de funk e leva público dos EUA à loucura com 'Movimento da Sanfoninha' no Amazon Music Live; assista |url=https://hugogloss.uol.com.br/musica/anitta-faz-performance-perfeita-cheia-de-funk-e-leva-publico-dos-eua-a-loucura-com-movimento-da-sanfoninha-no-amazon-music-live-assista/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Hugo Gloss |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Flávia |first=Kátia |date=2022-02-25 |title=Do Rio para o mundo: Anitta leva funk para prêmio Lo Nuestro |url=https://jornaldebrasilia.com.br/entretenimento/katia-flavia/anitta-premio-lo-nuestro-2022/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Jornal de Brasília |language=pt-BR}}</ref> Billboard credits her with prompting the [[The Latin Recording Academy|Latin Grammys]] to update their understanding of [[urban music]] and to include Brazilian funk for the first time among the genres that comprise this concept.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-10-14 |title=Billboard credita Anitta pelo "Funk Brasileiro" ter entrado nas categorias do Grammy Latino |url=https://portalrapmais.com/billboard-credita-anitta-pelo-funk-brasileiro-ter-entrado-nas-categorias-do-grammy-latino/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Rap Mais |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Funk ganha destaque no Grammy Latino e Anitta é celebrada: 'Você venceu' |url=https://www.uol.com.br/splash/noticias/2021/07/18/funk-ganha-destaque-no-grammy-latino-e-anitta-e-celebrada-voce-venceu.htm |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=www.uol.com.br |language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-07-18 |title=Grammy Latino reconhece funk brasileiro como categoria e público atribui conquista ao sucesso de Anitta |url=https://www.ofuxico.com.br/musica/grammy-latino-reconhece-funk-brasileiro/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=OFuxico |language=pt-br}}</ref> In March 2023, [[the Latin Recording Academy]] of the [[Latin Grammy Awards]] announced changes and additions to categories in the awards ceremony, including the Best Portuguese-Language Urban Performance.<ref>{{Cite web |title=The Latin Recording Academy Announces New Latin GRAMMY Award Categories And Field: Best Songwriter Of The Year, Best Singer-Songwriter Song, Best Portuguese-Language Urban Performance & More |url=https://www.grammy.com/news/new-latin-grammy-categories-field-songwriter-of-the-year-singer-songwriter-song-portugese-language-urban-performance |access-date=2023-03-25 |website=www.grammy.com}}</ref> This new category acknowledges the growth of urban music in [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] and the importance of the [[Brazilians|Brazilian]] and [[Portuguese people|Portuguese]] music markets to the global music industry. According to Variety and other magazines, Anitta played a key role in advocating for the inclusion of this new category in the awards ceremony, stating,<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-03-23 |title=Variety destaca importância de Anitta e Pabllo Vittar nas mudanças do Grammy Latino |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/variety-anitta-pabllo-vittar-mudancas-grammy-latino/ |access-date=2023-03-25 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR}}</ref> "[...] With the addition of the Best Portuguese-Language Urban Performance category, the Academy is responding to the rise of music in Brazil and Portugal, where artists like Anitta have gained global recognition. [...]".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Garcia |first=Thania |date=2023-03-21 |title=Latin Grammys Add New Award Categories: Songwriter of the Year, Best Portuguese-Language Urban Performance, More |url=https://variety.com/2023/music/global/latin-grammys-new-awards-songwriter-of-year-1235559978/ |access-date=2023-03-25 |website=Variety}}</ref>

In addition to her musical achievements, the singer became the third most influential personality in politics in Brazil in 2022, following former president [[Jair Bolsonaro]] and influencer [[Felipe Neto]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-06-03 |title=Anitta é 3ª personalidade mais influente na política no Brasil |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/anitta-e-3a-personalidade-mais-influente-na-politica-no-brasil/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR}}</ref> Several news outlets report that Anitta played a key role in pressuring politicians regarding votes on issues involving the [[Environmental protection|environment]], [[culture]], [[racism]] and [[homophobia]], directly opposing Jair Bolsonaro. Along with other artists, she supported the rival candidate of former President Bolsonaro, [[Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva|Lula]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Macedo |first=Nathalí |date=2022-04-16 |title=Como Anitta se tornou a inimiga nº 1 do bolsonarismo. Por Nathalí |url=https://www.diariodocentrodomundo.com.br/anitta-inimiga-bolsonarismo/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Diário do Centro do Mundo |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Grigori |first=Pedro |date=2021-12-13 |title=Anitta fala ao The New York Times sobre Bolsonaro: 'Não está fazendo um bom trabalho' |url=https://www.correiobraziliense.com.br/diversao-e-arte/2021/12/4970484-anitta-fala-ao-the-new-york-times-sobre-bolsonaro-nao-esta-fazendo-um-bom-trabalho.html |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Diversão e Arte |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Anitta critica Bolsonaro em TV francesa: 'Não representa os brasileiros' |url=https://www.uol.com.br/splash/noticias/2022/06/25/anitta-critica-bolsonaro-em-tv-francesa-nao-representa-os-brasileiros.htm |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=www.uol.com.br |language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Lucas Pasin - Como Anitta virou ícone contra Bolsonaro 4 anos após vídeo viral 'Ele Não' |url=https://www.uol.com.br/splash/colunas/lucas-pasin/2022/09/23/anitta-do-timido-video-do-ele-nao-a-icone-pop-contra-jair-bolsonaro.htm |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=www.uol.com.br |language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-07-15 |title=Incomodado com o apoio de Anitta a Lula, Bolsonaro pede que evangélicos deem uma 'chegada' nos jovens |url=https://www.cartacapital.com.br/politica/incomodado-com-o-apoio-de-anitta-a-lula-bolsonaro-pede-que-evangelicos-deem-uma-chegada-nos-jovens/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=CartaCapital |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Anitta apoia Lula: qual é o peso do voto de celebridades na eleição |language=pt-BR |work=BBC News Brasil |url=https://www.bbc.com/portuguese/brasil-62130784 |access-date=2023-02-02}}</ref> Anitta's advocacy was particularly evident when she encouraged young people aged 16 to 18 to obtain their electoral documents. This initiative attracted more than 2 million teenagers, and the youth enlistment campaign, along with the regularization of electoral titles, led the [[Superior Electoral Court]] to register a record of over 8.5 million requests for assistance regarding electoral status.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Efeito Anitta: número de jovens de até 17 anos que tirou título de eleitor cresce 31% em março, na comparação com fevereiro, diz TRE |url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/eleicoes/2022/noticia/2022/04/04/efeito-anitta-numero-de-jovens-de-ate-17-anos-que-tirou-titulo-de-eleitor-cresce-31percent-em-marco-na-comparacao-com-fevereiro-diz-tre.ghtml |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=G1 |date=4 April 2022 |language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-05-05 |title=Com incentivo de Anitta e DiCaprio, Brasil ganha 2 milhões de eleitores |url=https://exame.com/brasil/com-incentivo-de-anitta-e-dicaprio-brasil-ganha-2-milhoes-de-eleitores/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Exame |language=pt-br}}</ref>

In 2021, she was elected one of the most influential personalities in the world by [[Time (magazine)|Time]], joining the [[Time 100 Next]] list, which highlights emerging names globally. In 2022, [[Forbes]] included her in their [[Forbes 30 Under 30|30 Under 30]] North America list, recognizing her as one of the leaders of the next generation of [[Music of Latin America|Latin American music]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |title=2021 TIME100 Next: Anitta |url=https://time.com/collection/time100-next-2021/5937667/anitta/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |magazine=Time |date=17 February 2021 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Almeida |first=Fernanda |date=2022-11-30 |title=Anitta é destaque na lista 30 Under 30 da Forbes USA |url=https://forbes.com.br/forbeslife/2022/11/anitta-e-destaque-na-lista-30-under-30-da-forbes-usa/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Forbes Brasil |language=pt-br}}</ref> She is also considered one of the biggest influences on modern marketing in Brazil's recent history.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Como Anitta influencia o marketing digital? - Opinião |url=https://www.infomoney.com.br/colunistas/dener-lippert/como-anitta-influencia-o-marketing-digital/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=InfoMoney|date=25 March 2022 }}</ref>

Anitta was highlighted in [[Bloomberg Línea]]'s list of the 500 most influential people in [[Latin America]] in 2024, recognized for her ability to generate jobs and make investments that have boosted significant economic activities, showcasing her influence across various sectors.<ref>{{Cite web |title=As 500 Pessoas Mais Influentes da América Latina 2024 |url=https://www.bloomberglinea.com.br/top-500-mais-influentes-america-latina-2024/ |access-date=2024-09-21 |website=Bloomberg Línea Brasil |language=pt-BR}}</ref>

In 2024, a survey conducted by the [[Preply]] platform highlighted Anitta as the second most consumed Brazilian artist in [[Portugal]], behind only [[Ivete Sangalo]], who was mentioned by 9.4% of respondents.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-04-19 |title=Ivete ou Anitta? Lista traz os artistas brasileiros mais populares em Portugal |url=https://virgula.me/musica/ivete-ou-anitta-lista-traz-os-artistas-brasileiros-mais-populares-em-portugal/ |access-date=2025-01-06 |website=Vírgula |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-04-03 |title=Música brasileira em Portugal: os artistas e gêneros mais consumidos em terras lusitanas |url=https://preply.com/pt/blog/musica-brasileira-em-portugal/ |access-date=2025-01-06 |website=preply.com |language=pt}}</ref> The study revealed that 96% of participants stated they regularly listen to Brazilian music, with Anitta being cited by 6%.<ref>{{Cite web |last=OvarNews |date=2024-04-09 |title=Ivete Sangalo, Caetano Veloso e Anitta são os nomes mais conhecidos |url=https://www.ovarnews.pt/ivete-sangalo-caetano-veloso-e-anitta-sao-os-nomes-mais-conhecidos/ |access-date=2025-01-06 |website=OvarNews |language=pt-PT}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-04-10 |title=Estudo revela que funk é o género musical favorito de 40% dos portugueses {{!}} A Verdade |url=https://averdade.com/estudo-revela-que-funk-e-o-genero-musical-favorito-de-40-dos-portugueses/ |access-date=2025-01-06 |language=pt-PT}}</ref> Additionally, 61.8% of residents in the country reported having attended concerts by Brazilian artists, with Anitta and [[Luan Santana]] among the most prominent, and 15.4% of those attendees said they had attended more than one show.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-04-19 |title=Música brasileira em Portugal: sertanejo é o ritmo favorito de 46% dos portugueses |url=https://revistatudo.com.br/entretenimento/musica-brasileira-em-portugal-sertanejo-e-o-ritmo-favorito-de-46-dos-portugueses/23066/ |access-date=2025-01-06 |website=Revista Tudo |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-08-07 |title=A história da "poderosa" Anitta em Portugal: do "5 Para a Meia-Noite" aos grandes festivais de verão |url=https://expresso.pt/blitz/2024-08-07-a-historia-da-poderosa-anitta-em-portugal-do-5-para-a-meia-noite-aos-grandes-festivais-de-verao-2d7252b6 |access-date=2025-01-06 |website=Expresso |language=pt}}</ref>

Many recording artists have cited Anitta as an influence, including [[Tini (singer)|Tini]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-08-26 |title=TINI fala sobre Brasil e celebra parceria com Anitta: 'O sonho se realizou' |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/tini-brasil-anitta-sonho-realizou/ |access-date=2023-05-12 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR}}</ref> [[Christina Aguilera]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Christina Aguilera cita Anitta como inspiração brasileira: "Amo artistas inovadores" |date=8 February 2022 |url=https://osegredo.com.br/christina-aguilera-cita-anitta-como-inspiracao-brasileira-amo-artistas-inovadores/}}</ref> [[Katy Perry]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta recebe elogios de Katy Perry em bate-papo ao vivo: 'Você manda no Brasil' |url=https://gshow.globo.com/Famosos/noticia/anitta-recebe-elogios-de-katy-perry-you-rule-brazil.ghtml |access-date=2023-05-12 |website=gshow |date=15 May 2020 |language=pt-br}}</ref> [[Dua Lipa]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-12-22 |title=Dua Lipa fala sobre retorno ao Brasil e elogia Anitta e Pabllo Vittar |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/dua-lipa-fala-sobre-retorno-ao-brasil-e-elogia-anitta-e-pabllo-vittar/ |access-date=2023-05-12 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR}}</ref> [[Kenia Os]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Asi fue la gran experiencia de Kenia Os al conocer a Anitta |url=https://www.random.news/youtube/Asi-fue-la-gran-experiencia-de-Kenia-Os-al-conocer-a-Anitta-20210210-0011.html}}</ref> [[Karol G]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-06-21 |title=Karol G responde em que pé está parceria com Anitta |url=https://portalpopline.com.br/karol-g-responde-em-que-pe-esta-parceria-com-anitta/ |access-date=2023-05-12 |website=POPline |language=pt-BR}}</ref> [[J Balvin]],<ref>{{Cite web |last=Araujo |first=Guilherme |date=2022-10-08 |title=Entrevista - J Balvin fala de ascensão de Anitta, tretas com Grammy Latino e reggaeton no topo |url=https://www.papelpop.com/2022/10/entrevista-j-balvin-fala-de-ascensao-de-anitta-tretas-com-grammy-latino-e-reggaeton-no-topo/ |acce