== Awards and nominations ==
{{main|List of awards and nominations received by Anitta}}Anitta has been nominated for numerous important awards throughout her career, in [[Brazil]], throughout [[Latin America]], [[North America]], [[Europe]], [[Asia]] and [[Africa]], receiving over 760 nominations and winning over 300 awards. Among them are nominations for the biggest music awards such as the [[Grammy Awards]], [[Latin Grammy Awards]], [[Brazilian Music Awards]], [[American Music Awards]], [[Latin American Music Awards]], [[MTV Video Music Awards]], [[MTV Europe Music Awards]], [[MTV Millennial Awards]], [[MTV Millennial Awards Brazil]], [[All Africa Music Awards]], [[NRJ Music Award]]s, [[Billboard Latin Music Awards]], [[ASCAP Award]], [[People's Choice Awards]], [[WSJ|WSJ. Magazine's Innovator Awards]], [[Associação Paulista de Críticos de Arte|APCA Trophy]], [[GLAAD Media Award]], [[Heat Latin Music Awards]], [[iHeartRadio Music Awards]], Latin Music Italian Awards, [[Los 40 Music Awards|LOS40 Music Awards]], [[Melhores do Ano]], [[Meus Prêmios Nick]], [[Multishow Brazilian Music Award]]s, [[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards]], [[Premios Juventud]], [[Lo Nuestro Awards]], [[Teen Choice Awards]], [[Premios Tu Música Urbano]], among others.{{citation needed|date=February 2025}}

Anitta joined the list of the 50 most awarded musicians in the world of all time, according to The Artist Museum portal. This list is compiled by the portal, which tallies and gathers the awards received by artists throughout their careers, up to the present date.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Braziliense' |first='Correio |date=2022-01-19 |title=Anitta entra para a lista dos 50 artistas mais premiados |url=https://www.correiobraziliense.com.br/diversao-e-arte/2022/01/4978717-anitta-entra-para-a-lista-dos-50-artistas-mais-premiados.html |access-date=2023-07-12 |website=Diversão e Arte |language=pt-BR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Mazzuco |first=Amauri |date=2022-01-19 |title=Anitta entra para a lista dos 50 artistas mais premiados da história |url=https://www.papelpop.com/2022/01/anitta-entra-para-a-lista-dos-50-artistas-mais-premiados-da-historia/ |access-date=2023-07-12 |website=PAPELPOP |language=pt-br}}</ref>

Anitta is one of the [[List of Brazilian musicians|Brazilian]]/[[List of Latin pop artists|Latin]] singers with the most awards and nominations in the world,<ref>{{Cite web |title=Seis celebridades brasileiras que ganharam prêmios internacionais |url=https://cultura.uol.com.br/entretenimento/noticias/2022/05/12/3776_seis-celebridades-brasileiras-que-ganharam-premios-internacionais.html |access-date=2023-03-06 |website=TV Cultura |language=pt-br}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tvprime.ig.com.br/noticia/9699/especiais/5-cantores-brasileiros-mais-premiados-no-exterior-16082019 
|title=5 cantores brasileiros mais premiados no exterior |date=July 27, 2021 |access-date=May 4, 2025 |website=TV Prime |language=pt-BR |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210727051604/https://www.tvprime.ig.com.br/noticia/9699/especiais/5-cantores-brasileiros-mais-premiados-no-exterior-16082019 |archive-date=July 27, 2021}}</ref> being the first Brazilian and Latin artist to win and be nominated for several of these awards.<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=2022-08-29 |title=Anitta Just Made History at the 2022 VMAs |url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/art-books-music/a41012543/anitta-makes-history-for-brazil-vmas-2022/ |access-date=2023-03-06 |magazine=Harper's BAZAAR |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Vargas |first=Chanel |date=2022-08-28 |title=Anitta Makes History at the VMAs as First Brazilian Artist to Win Best Latin Award |url=https://www.popsugar.com/node/48931872 |access-date=2023-03-06 |website=POPSUGAR Entertainment |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta Says the 'Victory' Is Being Nominated at the 2023 Grammys as a Brazilian Artist |url=https://people.com/music/anitta-says-the-victory-is-2023-grammys-nomination-as-a-brazilian-artist/ |access-date=2023-03-06 |website=Peoplemag |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anitta, the Brazilian singer nominated for best new artist, is already a global superstar |url=https://www.today.com/popculture/music/who-is-anitta-brazilian-singer-rcna68581 |access-date=2023-03-06 |website=TODAY |date=5 February 2023 |language=en}}</ref><ref name="Neira" />

