* {{harvnb|Remnick|2010|p=177}}: "In late October 1987, his third year as an organizer, Obama went with Kellman to a conference on the black church and social justice at the Harvard Divinity School."
* {{harvnb|Maraniss|2012|p=557}}: "It would take time for Obama to join and become fully engaged in Wright's church, a place where he would be baptized and married; that would not happen until later, during his second time around in Chicago, but the process started then, in October 1987{{spaces}}... Jerry Kellman: 'He wasn't a member of the church during those first three years, but he was drawn to Jeremiah.'"
